pairs.source: The beginning of the gospel of Jesus Christ, the Son of God;
pairs.target: Itihleh sibungas Gah de’ paguh tentang Yesus Kristus, Onak Topa’.

pairs.source: As it is written in the prophets, Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.
pairs.target:
Gah de’ Paguh inoh mulai koda’ de’ mo’ nulis nabi Yesaya daang
buk-e no’uh-e,
“In Topa’, ‘Ninga’ mey! Oku’ oda’ nya’a de’ pait Ku’ dio’ so’
Mu’u, sa’-e sidia olan sa’an Mu’u.’

pairs.source: The voice of one crying in the wilderness, Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ nya’a de’ lu’ow-lu’ow-e sina de’ padang pasil, in-e, ‘Sidia
olan sa’an Topa’, nongon olan sa’an-E.’ ”

pairs.source: John did baptize in the wilderness, and preach the baptism of repentance for the remission of sins.
pairs.target:
Samah koda’ de’ obuah nulis inoh, wat noh leh Yohanes Pembaptis
nog de’ padang pasil tanon tudu’ nya’a de’ bogo’, “Togan olan de’ ja’at
nye’ mo’ baptis sa’ Topa’ ngapun dosa mu’!” In Yohanes.

pairs.source: And there went out unto him all the land of Judaea, and they of Jerusalem, and were all baptized of him in the river of Jordan, confessing their sins.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a so’
propinsi Yudea duoh sua’ nya’a de’ lo’o de’ kota Yerusalem odi ngojit oni’
de’ tanon Yohanes, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ ngaku’ sua’ dosa-e. Yohanes mo’
baptis odop-e de’ muno’ de’ sungi Yordan.

pairs.source: And John was clothed with camel’s hair, and with a girdle of a skin about his loins; and he did eat locusts and wild honey;
pairs.target:
Yohanes pakai jubah bulun unta duoh soot kupuang kulit, yohmo’
pinguman-e kadis duoh pi’in bonyih.

pairs.source: And preached, saying, There cometh one mightier than I after me, the latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to stoop down and unloose.
pairs.target:
Yohanes mo’ magah tudu’ nya’a de’
bogo’ gah de’ in-e, “Ogi’ nya’a de’ lobih ayuh-E so’ oku’, ya’ nog mokua’
oku’. Nyuduk buka’ tolin kasut-E tuang doi’ geh nyam ku’ patut.

pairs.source: I indeed have baptized you with water: but he shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost.
pairs.target:
Oku’
baptis ingan pakai pi’in, pak-e Iyoh ya’ baptis ingan pakai Iyang Topa’.”

pairs.source: And it came to pass in those days, that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized of John in Jordan.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh Yesus nog so’ kota Nazaret de’ ogi’ de’ propinsi Galilea,
Yohanes mo’ baptis Iyoh daang Sungi Yordan.

pairs.source: And straightway coming up out of the water, he saw the heavens opened, and the Spirit like a dove descending upon him:
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus mo’ ma’ad so’ pi’in ke’ doyoh, Iyoh mo’ ninga’ longit
tibuka’, Iyang Topa’ mo’ muun map de’ tun Yesus mun manuk asang mun-e.

pairs.source: And there came a voice from heaven, [saying], Thou art my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.
pairs.target:
Yohmo’ ogi’ sina so’ longit de’ in-e, “Mu’u leh Onak de’ ngibala’ Ku’, de’
oda’ kila Ku’ munuas.”

pairs.source: And immediately the Spirit driveth him into the wilderness.
pairs.target:
Takal mo’ mokua’ baptis, Iyang Topa’ mo’ toban Yesus de’ padang
pasil.

pairs.source: And he was there in the wilderness forty days, tempted of Satan; and was with the wild beasts; and the angels ministered unto him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ lo’o dano’ pat pulu’ onu, Laja Muat munua mo’ suba-E.
Topat Yoh lo’o inoh bogo’ binatang de’ ogi’ bisa-e duoh de’ gaus lo’o dano’,
malaikat-malaikat mo’ nog tulung-E.

pairs.source: Now after that John was put in prison, Jesus came into Galilee, preaching the gospel of the kingdom of God,
pairs.target: Takal Yohanes Pembaptis mo’ obuah takap, Yesus mo’ odi ke’ propinsi Galilea magah Gah de’ Paguh so’ Topa’.

pairs.source: And saying, The time is fulfilled, and the kingdom of God is at hand: repent ye, and believe the gospel.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Mo’ nog takal Topa’ mo’ ya’ mulai militah jadin Laja.
Togan leh olan de’ ja’at nye’ mo’ bisaya’ tudu’ Gah de’ paguh so’ Topa’!”

pairs.source: Now as he walked by the sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and Andrew his brother casting a net into the sea: for they were fishers.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ponu nuna’ bingon donu Galilea, Iyoh mo’ ninga’ Simon
duoh madih-e Andreas ngijaling ikian, dop-e inoh leh kiloja odop-e de’
duwoh.

pairs.source: And Jesus said unto them, Come ye after me, and I will make you to become fishers of men.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ja’ nuna’ Oku’! De’ dio’
ingan kiloja kalik ikian, pak-e adin Oku’ ngajal oda’ ingan kalik manusia
sa’-a nuna’ Oku’.”

pairs.source: And straightway they forsook their nets, and followed him.
pairs.target:
Simon duoh Andreas lasu’ togan jaling-e yohmo’ odi
nuna’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And when he had gone a little further thence, he saw James the [son] of Zebedee, and John his brother, who also were in the ship mending their nets.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’ lanyut pimonu-e, Iyoh mo’ ninga’ Yakobus duoh Yohanes.
Odop-e de’ duwoh onak Zebedeus. Odop-e de’ duwoh kiloja nopung jaling-e
daang olud.

pairs.source: And straightway he called them: and they left their father Zebedee in the ship with the hired servants, and went after him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mogan odop-e de’ duwoh, odop-e de’ duwoh lasu’
togan sama’-a duoh nya’a de’ kiloja sa’an-e daang olud, yohmo’ lasu’ nuna’
Yesus.

pairs.source: And they went into Capernaum; and straightway on the sabbath day he entered into the synagogue, and taught.
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E nog kota Kapernaum. Takal-e mo’ nog
onu simayang ulang Yahudi de’ nang nya’a onu Sabat, Yesus molot kaang
topat simayang agama Yahudi yohmo’ mulai ngajal.

pairs.source: And they were astonished at his doctrine: for he taught them as one that had authority, and not as the scribes.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a ilan
ninga’ wat Iyoh ngajal, dop-e oni’ de’ ngajal-E tok di’ nya’a ponai ya’
nyakal-e, idoh di’-e koda’ pingajal gulu-gulu agama Yahudi.

pairs.source: And there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit; and he cried out,
pairs.target:
Takal inoh ogi’ nya’a de’ obuah bikalui muat munua, molot kaang
boli simayang agama ulang Yahudi, yohmo’ nang bogan-e,

pairs.source: Saying, Let [us] alone; what have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of Nazareth? art thou come to destroy us? I know thee who thou art, the Holy One of God.
pairs.target:
“Oi Yesus ulang Nazaret, oni nai Ingan kaso ko’ih? Podo Ingan ya’
katuab ko’ih? Pu’an ku’ osi Ingan, Ingan leh de’ kaku’ Topa’, de’ pait
Topa’.”

pairs.source: And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nang muat munua inoh, “Ma’ bidaluag! Buu luah so’ nya’a
itih!”

pairs.source: And when the unclean spirit had torn him, and cried with a loud voice, he came out of him.
pairs.target:
Muat munua inoh mo’ ulih-ulih guyang gusuak gonan nya’a inoh,
muat munua nang bogan-e daang-e buu luah.

pairs.source: And they were all amazed, insomuch that they questioned among themselves, saying, What thing is this? what new doctrine [is] this? for with authority commandeth he even the unclean spirits, and they do obey him.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a dano’ obua’
ilan-e, yohmo’ bisikian duoh dingan-e de’ ogi’ dano’, in-e, “Oni de’ wat
itih? Nya’a itih ngajal pakai punua’ kuasa. Iyoh sina tudu’ muat munua
oda’ buu luah, muat munua mo’ lasu’ luah!”

pairs.source: And immediately his fame spread abroad throughout all the region round about Galilee.
pairs.target: Gah inoh mo’ popah kati’-kanih ke’ sua’ propinsi Galilea.

pairs.source: And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue, they entered into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E buu so’ topat simayang
agama Yahudi inoh, yohmo’ odi ke’ boli Simon duoh Andreas. Yakobus
duoh Yohanes suwa’ odi duoh odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: But Simon’s wife’s mother lay sick of a fever, and anon they tell him of her.
pairs.target:
Takal-e molot kaang
boli, ogi’ nya’a tanon tudu’ Yesus nang tua Simon de’ dayung monam
modud, yoh guling de’ topat bo’os-e.

pairs.source: And he came and took her by the hand, and lifted her up; and immediately the fever left her, and she ministered unto them.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ odi sinok tua Simon inoh
yohmo’ kagong tongan-e tulung oda’ mokat, onam-e mo’ lasu’ mokua’,
iyoh mo’ mokat, yohmo’ ngulia’ pinguman sa’an ayua odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And at even, when the sun did set, they brought unto him all that were diseased, and them that were possessed with devils.
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ya’ ngalom, bogo’ nya’a de’ toban ulang-ulang de’
monam duoh de’ obuah bikalui muat munua nog tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And all the city was gathered together at the door.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’
bogo’ mo’ nog tikuluk de’ bolot tiban-e.

pairs.source: And he healed many that were sick of divers diseases, and cast out many devils; and suffered not the devils to speak, because they knew him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ oda’ nya’a de’ bogo’
de’ bipasia-pasia onam tibo’i-e mokua’ duoh kasig muat munua so’ gonan
nya’a, pak-e Yesus di’-e oda’ muat munua sina, dop-e muat munua pu’an
osi Yesus inoh.

pairs.source: And in the morning, rising up a great while before day, he went out, and departed into a solitary place, and there prayed.
pairs.target:
Onu tia’ pagi-e takal onu alua’ bosow, Yesus mo’ mokat bo’os yohmo’
odi ke’ sopa’ kota de’ doi’ nya’a da’-e. Dano’ Yesus bidoa.

pairs.source: And Simon and they that were with him followed after him.
pairs.target: Simon duoh ayua dingan-e mo’ odi kalik Yesus.

pairs.source: And when they had found him, they said unto him, All [men] seek for thee.
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’
muno’ mo’ tapod Yesus, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ in-e, “Sua’ nya’a bolipotak
kalik Ingan.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Let us go into the next towns, that I may preach there also: for therefore came I forth.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Ja’ oto’ odi ke’ topat de’ bokon de’
sinok-sinok so’ kati’, sa’ Oku’ tanon geh Gah de’ paguh so’ Topa’ dano’.
Dop-e inoh leh ngan Oku’ nog.”

pairs.source: And he preached in their synagogues throughout all Galilee, and cast out devils.
pairs.target:
Yesus ponu kodak sua’ propinsi Galilea, Yoh ngajal nya’a Gah de’
Paguh de’ topat-topat simayang agama Yahudi duoh kasig muat munua
so’ nya’a.

pairs.source: And there came a leper to him, beseeching him, and kneeling down to him, and saying unto him, If thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ ni’ na’an nya’a de’ obuah onam kulit de’ bijakit nog tudu’
Yesus, yohmo’ bikunyug de’ sulung jowin Yesus. Mokua’ inoh yoh mitia’
masi’ tudu’ Yesus, yohmo’ in-e, “Simo’ Ingan la’an, Ingan tapod oda’ oku’
mokua’.”

pairs.source: And Jesus, moved with compassion, put forth [his] hand, and touched him, and saith unto him, I will; be thou clean.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ tok-tok masi’ tudu’-e. Iyoh mo’ toma’ gonan nya’a inoh
daang-e in-e, “La’an Ku’, mokua’ leh!”

pairs.source: And as soon as he had spoken, immediately the leprosy departed from him, and he was cleansed.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh onam kulit-e de’
bijakit lasu’ musuap yohmo’ mokua’.

pairs.source: And he straitly charged him, and forthwith sent him away;
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ oda’ iyoh buu duoh
ulih-ulih jaman-e, in-E,

pairs.source: And saith unto him, See thou say nothing to any man: but go thy way, shew thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing those things which Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.
pairs.target:
“Ma’ mu’u tanon tudu’ osi sija’-a, pak-e odi leh
tudu’ pimipin agama Yahudi sa’-a pilisa mu’u, tok mokua’ ke doh keh mu’u.
Mokua’ inoh nye’ simoliah binatang sa’an Topa’ koda’ de’ tanon Musa, de’
jadin bukti tudu’ nya’a de’ bogo’ dop-e mu’u mo’ bonal-bonal mokua’.”

pairs.source: But he went out, and began to publish [it] much, and to blaze abroad the matter, insomuch that Jesus could no more openly enter into the city, but was without in desert places: and they came to him from every quarter.
pairs.target:
Pak-e nya’a de’ mo’ mokua’ monam inoh odi kati’ kanih di’-e
mokua’-mokua’ silita tanon wat Yesus oda’ iyoh mokua’ so’ onam kulit-e.
Yesus mo’ di’-e tiya’ ponai molot bitanga odop-e daang kota. Iyoh mo’ jok-e
lo’o de’ sopa’ kota de’ doi’ nya’a lo’o da’-a, pak-e nya’a di’-e obua’-obua’
nog so’ ni’-so’ ni’ tudu’-E.

pairs.source: And again he entered into Capernaum, after [some] days; and it was noised that he was in the house.
pairs.target:
Kudu-kudu onu mokua’ inoh, Yesus odi lagi’ ke’ Kapernaum. Nya’a
mo’ ngojit gah nang Iyoh ogi’ de’ boli.

pairs.source: And straightway many were gathered together, insomuch that there was no room to receive [them], no, not so much as about the door: and he preached the word unto them.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ nog
ngubun-E, mulai so’ bolot tiban nog aang boli punua’ oda’ nya’a. Yesus
mo’ tanon Gah so’ Topa’ tudu’ nya’a de’ bogo’ inoh.

pairs.source: And they come unto him, bringing one sick of the palsy, which was borne of four.
pairs.target:
Takal-E alua’ sina, nog pat na’an nya’a tawiak ni’ na’an dali de’ kobos
gonan-e, yoh toban tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And when they could not come nigh unto him for the press, they uncovered the roof where he was: and when they had broken [it] up, they let down the bed wherein the sick of the palsy lay.
pairs.target:
Saai nya’a sikiya bogo’, odop-e de’ pat
inoh di’-e tapod molot bitapod duoh Yesus. Yoh mo’ toban ma’ad ke’
bungan boli, yoh mo’ nglibuang bungan totok Yesus mujuag. Yoh mo’
pimuun nya’a de’ kobos gonan-e inoh de’ sulung jowin Yesus baya topat
guling-e.

pairs.source: When Jesus saw their faith, he said unto the sick of the palsy, Son, thy sins be forgiven thee.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ninga’ odop-e de’ muno’ sukup-sukup bisaya’, Iyoh mo’
sina tudu’ nya’a de’ kobos gonan-e inoh, in-e, “Dosa-dosa mu’ mo’ obuah
ngapun.”

pairs.source: But there were certain of the scribes sitting there, and reasoning in their hearts,
pairs.target:
Pak-e ogi’ kudu-kudu na’an gulu agama ulang Yahudi de’ gulu’ dano’
mo’ in-e daang otin-e,

pairs.source: Why doth this [man] thus speak blasphemies? who can forgive sins but God only?
pairs.target:
“Puus manah Yoh nyamah odop-E duoh Topa’!
Jok-e Topa’ de’ tapod ngapun dosa nya’a neh.”

pairs.source: And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, he said unto them, Why reason ye these things in your hearts?
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh Yesus lasu’ pu’an daang otin-E, oni de’ pikil odop-e
de’ muno’, Yoh mo’ in-e, “Oni nai ingan bipikil de’ in inoh daang otin
ingan?

pairs.source: Whether is it easier to say to the sick of the palsy, [Thy] sins be forgiven thee; or to say, Arise, and take up thy bed, and walk?
pairs.target:
Ki de’ sonang doo’, tanon tudu’ nya’a de’ kobos gonan-e inoh nang,
‘Dosamu’ mo’ obuah ngapun’ keh, ‘Mokat, nye’ mo’ toban topat guling mu’
nye’ mo’ ponu’?

pairs.source: But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (he saith to the sick of the palsy,)
pairs.target:
Pak-e sa’ ingan pu’an-e, daang dunia itih Onak Manusia
ogi’ kuasa-E ngapun dosa manusia.” Yoh mo’ sina tudu’ nya’a de’ kobos  gonan-e inoh,

pairs.source: I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.
pairs.target:
“Mokat nye’ mo’ toban topat guling mu’, nye’ mo’ buu
motas!”

pairs.source: And immediately he arose, took up the bed, and went forth before them all; insomuch that they were all amazed, and glorified God, saying, We never saw it on this fashion.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ mokat daang-e lasu’ mit topat guling-e. Yohmo’ buu luah,
takal inoh geh nya’a de’ bogo’ ninga’ iyoh. Yoh ngan-e sua’ nya’a de’ muno’
ilan-e, yohmo’ mudi Topa’ daang-e in-e, “Mulan to’ ninga’ oni’ de’ wat
itih!”

pairs.source: And he went forth again by the sea side; and all the multitude resorted unto him, and he taught them.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus pali’ odi lagi’ ke’ pang donu Galilea. Bogo’ nya’a
nog tudu’-E, Yoh mo’ ngajal-e.

pairs.source: And as he passed by, he saw Levi the [son] of Alphaeus sitting at the receipt of custom, and said unto him, Follow me. And he arose and followed him.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus alua’ ponu dano’, Yoh ninga’ ogi’ ni’ na’an nya’a de’
tukang nagih suke de’ adon Lewi onak Alfeus, gulu’ de’ topat nya’a bayal
suke sa’an kerajaan Romawi. Yesus mo’ sina tudu’-e, “Ja’ nuna’ Oku’!”
Lewi mo’ mokat mujuag yoh mo’ lasu’ nuna’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And it came to pass, that, as Jesus sat at meat in his house, many publicans and sinners sat also together with Jesus and his disciples: for there were many, and they followed him.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E man de’ boli Lewi, bogo’
ulang-ulang de’ tukang nagih suke duoh nya’a de’ nang nya’a ulang
bidosa suwa’ man samah-samah duoh ayua odop-e de’ muno’, dop-e bogo’
nya’a de’ nuna’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And when the scribes and Pharisees saw him eat with publicans and sinners, they said unto his disciples, How is it that he eateth and drinketh with publicans and sinners?
pairs.target:
Ogi’ kudu-kudu na’an nya’a Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi ninga’ Yesus
suwa’ man duoh ulang-ulang pinagih suke duoh nya’a de’ sobot nya’a nang
ulang de’ bidosa inoh. Yoh mo’ sikian tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus, “Oni
nai gulu mu’ suwa’ man duoh tukang pinagih suke duoh ulang de’ bidosa
inoh?”

pairs.source: When Jesus heard [it], he saith unto them, They that are whole have no need of the physician, but they that are sick: I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ngojit oni’ de’ nang odop-e de’ muno’, Yoh mo’ nyawot-e,
“Nya’a de’ sehat di’-e pilelu doktol, jok-e nya’a de’ monam. Idoh di’ ku’
nog mogan nya’a de’ bonal, pak-e oku’ nog mogan nya’a de’ bidosa.”

pairs.source: And the disciples of John and of the Pharisees used to fast: and they come and say unto him, Why do the disciples of John and of the Pharisees fast, but thy disciples fast not?
pairs.target:
Ogi’ onu-e takal pinuna’-pinuna’ Yohanes Pembaptis duoh gulu-gulu
agama ulang Yahudi puasa. Ogi’ nya’a nog tudu’ Yesus yohmo bisikian,
“Oni nai pinuna’-pinuna’ Yohanes Pembaptis duoh gulu-gulu agama ulang
Yahudi puasa, pak-e pinuna’-pinuna’ Ingan di’-e puasa?”

pairs.source: And Jesus said unto them, Can the children of the bridechamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them? as long as they have the bridegroom with them, they cannot fast.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e pakai nang silita, “Mo’ nya’a biluman kawin,
podo tamu-tamu-e di’-e man? Takal nya’a de’ kawin alua’ ogi’ dano’, totu
nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’ alua’ man.

pairs.source: But the days will come, when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.
pairs.target:
Pak-e ogi’ takal-e nya’a toban nya’a de’ kawin inoh toban buu. Takal
inoh leh di’ nya’a tiya’ man-nuak.

pairs.source: No man also seweth a piece of new cloth on an old garment: else the new piece that filled it up taketh away from the old, and the rent is made worse.
pairs.target:
Doi’-e ogi’ nya’a nopung bojuh de’ oma pakai kain de’ ba’uh. Dop-e
mo’-e kain topung de’ ba’uh inoh bikinyot yoh mo’ notak bojuh de’ mo’
oma, totak-e mo’ bitamah ayuh.

pairs.source: And no man putteth new wine into old bottles: else the new wine doth burst the bottles, and the wine is spilled, and the bottles will be marred: but new wine must be put into new bottles.
pairs.target:
Watnoh geh doi’ nya’a ngisi’ pi’in anggul de’ ba’uh daang topat de’
mo’ oma, dop-e pi’in anggul de’ ba’uh muab, topat-e de’ oma inoh mo’
totak. Luban-e so’ duwoh-e tibuang. Totu leh pi’in anggul de’ ba’uh, nya’a
na’ daang topat de’ ba’uh geh!” In Yesus.

pairs.source: And it came to pass, that he went through the corn fields on the sabbath day; and his disciples began, as they went, to pluck the ears of corn.
pairs.target:
Takal Onu Sabat, Yesus ponu duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E ngilusu’ umoh
gandum. Pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ pilai, yohmo’ tuk kiluang gandum yoh mo’
man-e.

pairs.source: And the Pharisees said unto him, Behold, why do they on the sabbath day that which is not lawful?
pairs.target:
Ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi mo’ sina tudu’ Yesus, “Ninga’,
oni nai pinuna’-pinuna’ Ingan nai oni’ de’ di’ nya’a so’on nai-e daang Onu
Sabat?”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Have ye never read what David did, when he had need, and was an hungred, he, and they that were with him?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Alua’ doi’ keh ingan basa daang Kitab? Oni de’
nai Daud no’uh-e? Takal iyoh duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-e pilai doi’ oni’ de’ ya’
man-e.

pairs.source: How he went into the house of God in the days of Abiathar the high priest, and did eat the shewbread, which is not lawful to eat but for the priests, and gave also to them which were with him?
pairs.target:
Takal Abyatar de’ jadin pimipin de’ paling ayuh-e, Daud molot
kaang topat nya’a nyomah Topa’. Yoh duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-e mo’ man
kueh de’ ngin nya’a tudu’ Topa’, nuna’ atulan agama oto’ jok-e pimipin
agama Yahudi de’ so’on man kueh inoh.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, The sabbath was made for man, and not man for the sabbath:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e lagi’, “Topa’ nai Onu Sabat sa’an manusia, idoh di’-e
manusia sa’an onu Sabat.

pairs.source: Therefore the Son of man is Lord also of the sabbath.
pairs.target:
Onak Manusia leh de’ notu oni de’ so’on duoh
oni’ de’ di’-e so’on nya’a nai-e daang Onu Sabat.”

pairs.source: And he entered again into the synagogue; and there was a man there which had a withered hand.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ pali’ odi lagi’ ke’ topat simayang agama Yahudi. Dano’ ogi’
ni’ na’an nya’a de’ tongan-e kobos ni’ kawa.

pairs.source: And they watched him, whether he would heal him on the sabbath day; that they might accuse him.
pairs.target:
Dano’ ogi’ kudu-kudu
na’an ulang Yahudi de’ ninga’ oni’ de’ nai Yesus, simo’ Yesus oda’ nya’a
de’ tongan-e kobos ni’ kawa inoh mokua’ daang Onu Sabat, odop-e de’
muno’ tapod ya’ nyalah-E.

pairs.source: And he saith unto the man which had the withered hand, Stand forth.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ nya’a de’ tongan-e kobos
ni’ kawa inoh, “Got mokat mujuag kati’, ke’ sulung jowin ko’ih!”

pairs.source: And he saith unto them, Is it lawful to do good on the sabbath days, or to do evil? to save life, or to kill? But they held their peace.
pairs.target:
Yesus
 mo’ sikian tudu’ nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’, “Mo’-e nuna’ atulan agama oto’, oni
de’ patut oto’ nai daang Onu Sabat? Nai oni’ de’ paguh keh, nai oni’ de’
ja’at? Tulung nya’a oda’ idip keh nye’ ngabos-e?”
Pak-e odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ lo’o ja’-e.

pairs.source: And when he had looked round about on them with anger, being grieved for the hardness of their hearts, he saith unto the man, Stretch forth thine hand. And he stretched [it] out: and his hand was restored whole as the other.
pairs.target:
Yesus ninga’ sua’ nya’a de’ muno’ daang-e tiwas, duoh kila-E susah,
dop-e nya’a de’ muno’ obua’ kolas otin-e. Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ nya’a de’
tongan-e kobos ni’ kawa inoh, “Suual tongan mu’.” Nya’a inoh mo’ suual
tongan-e, yohmo’ lasu’ mokua’.

pairs.source: And the Pharisees went forth, and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi buu so’ topat simayang
inoh, yoh mo’ biloneng duoh ulang Yahudi de’ nua’ Laja Herodes ngan-e
ya’ ngabos Yesus.

pairs.source: But Jesus withdrew himself with his disciples to the sea: and a great multitude from Galilee followed him, and from Judaea,
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ buu ke’ pang Donu Galilea. Yohmo’
bogo’ nya’a so’ propinsi Galilea duoh so’ propinsi Yudea bituna’ duoh-E.

pairs.source: And from Jerusalem, and from Idumaea, and [from] beyond Jordan; and they about Tyre and Sidon, a great multitude, when they had heard what great things he did, came unto him.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh de’ so’ kota Yerusalem, so’ Idumea so’ polad Sungi Yordan, so’
kota Tirus, duoh kota Sidon. Sua’ ayua de’ muno’ nog dop-e yoh mo’ ngojit
sua’ oni’ de’ mo’ nai Yesus.

pairs.source: And he spake to his disciples, that a small ship should wait on him because of the multitude, lest they should throng him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ oda’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E sidia olud
sa’an odop-E, dop-e nya’a sikiya bogo’, sa’ Yoh di’-e pisiat oda’ nya’a de’
bitodod-todod duoh Yoh.

pairs.source: For he had healed many; insomuch that they pressed upon him for to touch him, as many as had plagues.
pairs.target:
Bogo’ nya’a de’ mokua’ oda’-E, yoh ngan sua’ nya’a de’ monam
bitodod-todod ngan-e ya’ odi sinok Yesus, sa’-e tapod toma’-E.

pairs.source: And unclean spirits, when they saw him, fell down before him, and cried, saying, Thou art the Son of God.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’
molot muat munua daang gonan-e, takal-e ninga’ Yesus yoh mo’ nyuduk
bikunyug de’ sulung jowin Yesus daang-e nang bogan-e, “Ingan Onak
Topa’!”

pairs.source: And he straitly charged them that they should not make him known.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus isin-isin jaman muat munua inoh tanon nang Iyoh
Onak Topa’.

pairs.source: And he goeth up into a mountain, and calleth [unto him] whom he would: and they came unto him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus ma’ad ke’ tun pungu’. Yesus mo’ ngija’ ulang-ulang de’ ya’ pilih-E, sa’-a odi tudu’ odop-E dano’. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ odi
tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And he ordained twelve, that they should be with him, and that he might send them forth to preach,
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ pilih simoong duwoh na’an so’ odop-e de’ muno’. Iyoh mo’
sobot nang rasul-rasul-E. Yesus mo’ in-e, “Oku’ pilih ingan, sa' ingan suwa’
duoh Oku’, sa’ Ku’ pait ingan oda’ magah Gah de’ Paguh so’ Topa’.

pairs.source: And to have power to heal sicknesses, and to cast out devils:
pairs.target:
Oku’
ya’ ngin kuasa tudu’ ingan oda’ ponai kasig pibuu muat munua.”

pairs.source: And Simon he surnamed Peter;
pairs.target:
De’ muti’ leh adon-adon nya’a de’ pilih-E: Simon de’ sobot Yesus geh
nang Petrus,

pairs.source: And James the [son] of Zebedee, and John the brother of James; and he surnamed them Boanerges, which is, The sons of thunder:
pairs.target:
Yakobus duoh Yohanes, odop-e de’ duwoh itih onak Zebedeus. Odop-e
de’ duwoh itih, Yesus biladon nang Boanerges loti-e “Nya’a de’ koda’ Dudu.”

pairs.source: And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the [son] of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Canaanite,
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh Andreas, Filipus, Bartolomeus, Matius, Tomas, Yakobus onak
Alfeus, Tadeus, Simon so’ uluk ulang Yahudi de’ bijuang oda’ Israel bebas
so’ kerajaan Romawi,

pairs.source: And Judas Iscariot, which also betrayed him: and they went into an house.
pairs.target:
duoh Yudas Iskariot, nya’a de’ ya’ jua Yesus tudu’
nya’a de’ bu’ui da’-E.

pairs.source: And the multitude cometh together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus pali’ ke boli. Pak-e nya’a bogo’ nog tikuluk lagi’
ngubun Iyoh, yoh ngan Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E di’ supot man.

pairs.source: And when his friends heard [of it], they went out to lay hold on him: for they said, He is beside himself.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ in-e, “Iyoh itih mo’ bako’!” Takal madih ayua-e mo’
ngojit gah inoh, yoh mo’ odi mit-E.

pairs.source: And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said, He hath Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils casteth he out devils.
pairs.target:
Gulu-gulu agama Yahudi de’ nog so’ Yerusalem mo’ in-e, “Iyoh itih
obuah nguasa oda’ Beelzebul! Laja sua’ muat munua inoh leh de’ ngin
kuasa da’-E, ngan-e kasig muat munua.”

pairs.source: And he called them [unto him], and said unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mogan nya’a de’ bogo’ inoh, yohmo’ in-e, “Wat ki Laja
Muat munua ponai ya’ kasig Laja Muat munua?”

pairs.source: And if a kingdom be divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.
pairs.target:
Yesus lanyut sina-E pakai nang silita, in-E, “Simo’-e ogi’ negeli de’
di’ layat-e tilukum daang-e silalu bika’i si odop-e idoh di’-e taan tuui.

pairs.source: And if a house be divided against itself, that house cannot stand.
pairs.target: Lawang bo’on de’ silalu bikiing bilawan tipan odop-e idoh di’-e taan tuui.

pairs.source: And if Satan rise up against himself, and be divided, he cannot stand, but hath an end.
pairs.target:
Simo’ Laja Muat munua bilawan si odop-e wat ki wat-e ya’ taan tuui?
Iyoh pasti obua’ mutuab.

pairs.source: No man can enter into a strong man’s house, and spoil his goods, except he will first bind the strong man; and then he will spoil his house.
pairs.target:
Ni’ na’an tuang doi’ geh de’ taan molot kaang
boli nya’a de’ dolas duoh mit halta-e, simo’-e di’-e pasung dio’. Takal-e
mo’ mokua’ pasung-e ke yoh tapod mit halta-e.

pairs.source: Verily I say unto you, All sins shall be forgiven unto the sons of men, and blasphemies wherewith soever they shall blaspheme:
pairs.target:
Oku’ tanon tudu’ ingan: Sua’ dosa de’ nai nya’a duoh sina de’ ja’at
alua’ tapod obuah ngapun.

pairs.source: But he that shall blaspheme against the Holy Ghost hath never forgiveness, but is in danger of eternal damnation:
pairs.target:
Pak-e sina de’ ja’at de’ pija’at Iyang Topa’,
idoh di’ Topa’ tapod ngapun-e. Dosa inoh mo’ lokat nah-nah.”

pairs.source: Because they said, He hath an unclean spirit.
pairs.target:
Yesus
tanon de’ in inoh, dop-e odop-e de’ muno’ nang Yesus obuah nguasa Laja
Muat munua.

pairs.source: There came then his brethren and his mother, and, standing without, sent unto him, calling him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh, sino’ duoh madih Yesus nog ya’ bitapod duoh-E. Odop-e
de’ muno’ kajon de’ sopa’, yoh mo’ oda’ nya’a mogan Yesus.

pairs.source: And the multitude sat about him, and they said unto him, Behold, thy mother and thy brethren without seek for thee.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh,  bogo’ nya’a nog gulu’ sinok Yesus. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ in-e, “Ogi’ sino’
duoh madih Ingan kajon de’ sopa’. Yoh ya’ bitapod duoh Ingan.”

pairs.source: And he answered them, saying, Who is my mother, or my brethren?
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Osi sino’ Ku’? Osi madih Ku’?”

pairs.source: And he looked round about on them which sat about him, and said, Behold my mother and my brethren!
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’
ninga’ sua’ nya’a de’ gulu' sinok odop-E, yohmo’ in-e, “De’ muti’ leh sino’
duoh madih Ku’!

pairs.source: For whosoever shall do the will of God, the same is my brother, and my sister, and mother.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a de’ nai oni' de’ la’an Topa’, de’ muno’ leh
sino’ duoh madih Ku’.”

pairs.source: And he began again to teach by the sea side: and there was gathered unto him a great multitude, so that he entered into a ship, and sat in the sea; and the whole multitude was by the sea on the land.
pairs.target:
Yesus pali’ ngajal lagi’ nya’a de’ bingon Donu Galilea. Nya’a mo’ bogo’
nog ngubun-E. Iyoh odi gulu’ kaang olud de’ ogi’ daang donu. Pak-e
nya’a bogo’ mujuag de’ doyoh bingon donu.

pairs.source: And he taught them many things by parables, and said unto them in his doctrine,
pairs.target: Bogo’ oni' de’ ngajal Yesus pakai nang silita, Iyoh mo’ silita in-E,

pairs.source: Hearken; Behold, there went out a sower to sow:
pairs.target: “Ngojit dio’! Ogi’ nya’a de’ odi dabul binia’.

pairs.source: And it came to pass, as he sowed, some fell by the way side, and the fowls of the air came and devoured it up.
pairs.target:
Takal-e dabul binia’-e,
ogi’ de’ labu’ de’ olan, yohmo’ nog manuk lasu’ man kabua’-e.

pairs.source: And some fell on stony ground, where it had not much earth; and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of earth:
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh
de’ labu’ de’ tun tana’ de’ bibatuh, yoh mo’ lasu’ tumu’ dop-e tana’-e lidia’.

pairs.source: But when the sun was up, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal onu mo’ putiak, tumu’ pimuluah inoh mo’ pisok yoh mo’
kobos layu’, dop-e aat-e di’-e tuluap kaang tana’.

pairs.source: And some fell among thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh de’ labu’ de’
siak duh de’ biloja’. Takal-e tumu’, duh de’ muno’ mo’ molut-e yoh mo’
di’-e ponai mokat tumu’ duoh bibua’.

pairs.source: And other fell on good ground, and did yield fruit that sprang up and increased; and brought forth, some thirty, and some sixty, and some an hundred.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh de’ labu’ de’ tana’ de’
paguh. Yoh mo’ tumu’ yoh mo’ bibua’, ogi’ de’ taluh pulu’ sidoh bogo’,
ogi’ geh de’ nuam pulu’ sidoh bogo’, ogi’ geh de’ silatus sidoh bogo’.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus mo’ mokua’ nang silita inoh, Yoh mo’ in-e, “Osi de’ ogi’
kojit-e sa’-e ngojit-e!”

pairs.source: And when he was alone, they that were about him with the twelve asked of him the parable.
pairs.target:
Takal nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ buu duam Yesus sadi’-e, pinuna’-pinuna’-E
baya simoong duwoh na’an rasul-E mo’ sikian tudu’ Yesus, oni loti silita
de’ nang-E inoh.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Unto you it is given to know the mystery of the kingdom of God: but unto them that are without, all [these] things are done in parables:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot in-E, “Tudu’ ingan Topa’ mo’ tanon tentang oni
wat Iyoh militah jadin Laja. Pak-e tudu’ nya’a de’ bokon Oku’ tanon pakai
nang silita.

pairs.source: That seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest at any time they should be converted, and [their] sins should be forgiven them.
pairs.target:
Oku’ nai wat inoh sa’-e jadi koda’ daang Kitab, de’ in-e,
‘Nya’a de’ muno’ telus ninga’,
pak-e di’-e ngiloti oni-oni-e.
Nya’a de’ muno’ telus ngojit,
pak-e di’-e ngiloti oni-oni-e.   
Simo’-e ngiloti-e, yoh togan olan de’ ja’at,
yohmo’ pali’ tudu’ Oku’,
Oku’ ya’ ngapun dosa-e.’ ”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Know ye not this parable? and how then will ye know all parables?
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Simo’ ingan di’
ingan ngiloti silita de’ nang Ku’ ti’-e, silita de’ bokon tuang idoh geh di’
ingan ngiloti-e.

pairs.source: The sower soweth the word.
pairs.target:
Oku’ ya’ tanon loti silita de’ nang Ku’ ti’-e: Nya’a de’ dabul binia’,
iyoh leh de’ koda’ nya’a de’ tukang magah Pingunang Topa’.

pairs.source: And these are they by the way side, where the word is sown; but when they have heard, Satan cometh immediately, and taketh away the word that was sown in their hearts.
pairs.target:
Binia’ de’
labu’ de’ olan iyoh leh de’ koda’ nya’a de’ ngojit Pingunang Topa’, pak-e
Laja Muat munua lasu’ mit Pingunang Topa’ de’ tuang-e ngojit-e .

pairs.source: And these are they likewise which are sown on stony ground; who, when they have heard the word, immediately receive it with gladness;
pairs.target:
Binia’
de’ labu’ de’ topat de’ bibatuh, samah koda’ nya’a de’ ngojit Pingunang
Topa’ yohmo’ lasu’ tilima’ daang otin de’ doon.

pairs.source: And have no root in themselves, and so endure but for a time: afterward, when affliction or persecution ariseth for the word’s sake, immediately they are offended.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Pingunang Topa’
inoh di’-e tumu’ daang otin osuap-e, yoh mo’ di’-e taan tuui, takal idip-e
susah jola’ iyoh mo’ lasu’ di’-e bisaya’.

pairs.source: And these are they which are sown among thorns; such as hear the word,
pairs.target:
Binia’ de’ labu’ de’ tota’ loja’,
samah koda’ nya’a de’ ngojit Pingunang Topa’,

pairs.source: And the cares of this world, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lusts of other things entering in, choke the word, and it becometh unfruitful.
pairs.target:
pak-e yoh bigaduh natong
pingidip-e, suka ya’ kaya, ngilipuang sua’-sua’ oni' daang dunia. Pingunang
Topa’ inoh mo’ obuah molut, yohmo’ di’-e ponai bibua’.

pairs.source: And these are they which are sown on good ground; such as hear the word, and receive [it], and bring forth fruit, some thirtyfold, some sixty, and some an hundred.
pairs.target:
Binia’ de’ labu’
de’ tana’ de’ paguh, samah koda’ nya’a de’ ngojit Pingunang Topa’, yohmo’
tumu’ daang otin osuap-e, yoh mo’ bibua’. Ogi’ de’ bibua’ taluh pulu’ sidoh
bogo’, ogi’ de’ nuam pulu’ sidoh bogo’, ogi’ geh de’ silatus sidoh bogo’.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Is a candle brought to be put under a bushel, or under a bed? and not to be set on a candlestick?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ lanyut silita-E lagi', “Doi’-e ogi’ nya’a de’ tung lapu yohmo’
ngilokuab-e pakai bona yoh mo’ suan de’ libua’ topat bo’os-e. Pasti nya’a
tung lapu, yohmo’ kajuag de’ topat de’ bigatung, sa’-e oda’ tana' jawa’.

pairs.source: For there is nothing hid, which shall not be manifested; neither was any thing kept secret, but that it should come abroad.
pairs.target:
Oni’ de’ di’ nya’a ponai kilin-e adin, tia’ tuang ponai geh nya’a kilin-e.
Oni’ de’ di’ nya’a pu’an-e adin, tia’ tuang ponai geh nya’a pu’an-e.

pairs.source: If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target: Osi de’ ogi’ kojit-e, sa’-e ngojit bonal-bonal.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Take heed what ye hear: with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you: and unto you that hear shall more be given.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ in-e lagi’, “Ngojit bonal-bonal-e, pingajal de’ tanon Ku’ tudu’
ingan! Oni wat oni’ de’ nai nye’ duoh nya’a de’ bokon, wat inoh leh wat
Topa’ duoh odop nye’, makin lobih so’ inoh.

pairs.source: For he that hath, to him shall be given: and he that hath not, from him shall be taken even that which he hath.
pairs.target:
Dop-e osi de’ mo’ ogi’ oni’
de’ kaku’-e, yoh ya’ so’on lobih bogo’ lagi’, pak-e nya’a de’ doi’ oni’, sit
oni’ de’ ogi’ de’ kaku’-e, ya’ obuah mit geh.”

pairs.source: And he said, So is the kingdom of God, as if a man should cast seed into the ground;
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ngajal lagi’ pakai silita ngan-e tanon oni wat Topa’ militah
jadin Laja. Yoh mo’ in-e, “Ogi’ nya’a de’ dabul binia’-e de’ umoh-e.

pairs.source: And should sleep, and rise night and day, and the seed should spring and grow up, he knoweth not how.
pairs.target:
Takal
onu ngalom iyoh bo’os, onu jawa’ yoh mo’ mokat bo'os, yoh mo’ ninga’
binia’-e mo’ tumu’ luah suk-e bitamah bigatung, pak-e di’-e pu’an oni wat
tumu’-e inoh bitamah ayuh.

pairs.source: For the earth bringeth forth fruit of herself; first the blade, then the ear, after that the full corn in the ear.
pairs.target:
Tana’ umoh inoh leh de’ oda’ binia’ inoh tumu’ nog-e bibua’, sibungas-e
bisuat, yoh mo’ bisala’ yoh mo’ jadin bua’-e.

pairs.source: But when the fruit is brought forth, immediately he putteth in the sickle, because the harvest is come.
pairs.target:
Simo’ gandum inoh mo’
masak, nya’a de’ kaku’ umoh inoh mo’ ngutuam-e, dop-e mo’ nog onu-e
ya’ ngutuam.”

pairs.source: And he said, Whereunto shall we liken the kingdom of God? or with what comparison shall we compare it?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e lagi’, “Samah koda’ oni oto’ ya’ baning Topa’ de’
militah jadin Laja? Silita oni ngan to’ tanon-e?

pairs.source: [It is] like a grain of mustard seed, which, when it is sown in the earth, is less than all the seeds that be in the earth:
pairs.target:
Takal Topa’ militah jadin Laja, inoh samah koda’ silita itih: Luang
sabih de’ sukup alus kiluang-e so’ luang pimuluah de’ ogi’ daang dunia.

pairs.source: But when it is sown, it groweth up, and becometh greater than all herbs, and shooteth out great branches; so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal-e tumu’, yoh mo’ jadin koyuh de’ ayuh so’ pimuluah kuduas
de’ bokon. Yoh mo’ bida’an ayuh, bogo’ manuk de’ bisolin da’-a.”

pairs.source: And with many such parables spake he the word unto them, as they were able to hear [it].
pairs.target:
Wat inoh leh Yesus ngajal nya’a pakai bogo’ silita koda’ inoh, de’
tapod nya’a ngiloti-e.

pairs.source: But without a parable spake he not unto them: and when they were alone, he expounded all things to his disciples.
pairs.target:
Yesus silalu ngajal nya’a de’ bogo’ pakai nang
silita. Pak-e takal-E jok-e duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E, Yoh tanon susua’ loti
pingunang-E tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And the same day, when the even was come, he saith unto them, Let us pass over unto the other side.
pairs.target: Takal ngumi inoh geh, Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, “Ja’ oto’ motas ke’ polad donu.”

pairs.source: And when they had sent away the multitude, they took him even as he was in the ship. And there were also with him other little ships.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ muun kaang olud, pinuna’-pinuna’-E
mo’ suwa’ muat duoh-E ni’ olud. Yoh mo’ togan nya’a de’ bogo’, pak-e ogi’
geh nya’a de’ nuna’ pakai olud de’ bokon.

pairs.source: And there arose a great storm of wind, and the waves beat into the ship, so that it was now full.
pairs.target:
Alua’ di’-e tuui bilakat, sobak
libut mo’ nog. Pi’in gilumang mo’ molot kaang olud-e, olud-e mo’ tado’-e
ya’ kuuam.

pairs.source: And he was in the hinder part of the ship, asleep on a pillow: and they awake him, and say unto him, Master, carest thou not that we perish?
pairs.target:
Takal inoh Yesus bo’os de’ tun tilam de’ butut olud. Yohmo’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E guyang oda’ mokat. Yoh mo’ in-e, “Gulu! Doh di’ Ingan
tolu nang oto’ ya’ kobos kuuam?”

pairs.source: And he arose, and rebuked the wind, and said unto the sea, Peace, be still. And the wind ceased, and there was a great calm.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mokat, Yoh mo’ nang sobak libut duoh sina tudu’ donu
inoh in-E, “Lo’o! Ma’ tiya’ bilaya’!” Sobak duoh gilumang mo’ lasu’ lo’o.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Why are ye so fearful? how is it that ye have no faith?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Oni nai ingan tolu? Oni nai
ingan di’ bisaya’ tudu’ Oku’?”

pairs.source: And they feared exceedingly, and said one to another, What manner of man is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sukup tolu-e, yoh mo’ in-e tipan odop-e, “Osi
sibonal-e Yoh itih, sape sobak libut, gilumang tuang tunuak geh tudu’
sina-E?”

pairs.source: And they came over unto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E nog ke’ polad Donu Galilea,
topat ulang Gerasa lo’o.

pairs.source: And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him out of the tombs a man with an unclean spirit,
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ma’ad so’ aang olud, ogi’ ni’
na’an dali de’ obuah bikalui muat munua de’ lo’o de’ tota’ kubul odi tudu’
Yesus.

pairs.source: Who had [his] dwelling among the tombs; and no man could bind him, no, not with chains:
pairs.target: Dali inoh doi’ nya’a tapod ya’ mokos-e bial-e pakai late.

pairs.source: Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any [man] tame him.
pairs.target:
Mo’ pali’-pali’ nya’a pasung tongan po’on-e, pak-e late ngan nya’a
pasung-e obua’ motod-e, bosi de’ po’on-e tuang mugat-e geh. Dali inoh
sikiya dolas doi’ tiya’ nya’a de’ taan ya’ pasung-e.

pairs.source: And always, night and day, he was in the mountains, and in the tombs, crying, and cutting himself with stones.
pairs.target:
Iyoh singonu singalom motak moli’ de’ tota’ kubul, de’ pungu’-pungu’
simadi-e nang bogan-e daang-e mupu’ gonan-e pakai batuh.

pairs.source: But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him,
pairs.target:
So’ juua’ geh iyoh ninga’ takal Yesus nog, yoh mo’ bikoduh tudu’ Yesus,
yohmo’ nyomah Yesus nog jowin-e sium tana’.

pairs.source: And cried with a loud voice, and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, [thou] Son of the most high God? I adjure thee by God, that thou torment me not.
pairs.target:
Daang-e nang bogan-e,
“Yesus Onak Topa’ de’ sukup ayuh kuasa-E, oni wat Mu’u ya’ duoh oku’?
Daang adon Topa’, oku’ bonal-bonal mitia’ tudu’ Ingan ma’ ya’ kanam
oku’!”

pairs.source: For he said unto him, Come out of the man, [thou] unclean spirit.
pairs.target:
Yoh ngan-e in inoh, dop-e Yesus sina tudu’ muat munua, “Luah leh so’
nya’a itih!”

pairs.source: And he asked him, What [is] thy name? And he answered, saying, My name [is] Legion: for we are many.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’-e, “Osi adon mu’u?” Muat munua daang gonan
nya’a inoh mo’ nyawot-E,
“Adon ku’ Legion, dop-e ko’ih bogo’.”

pairs.source: And he besought him much that he would not send them away out of the country.
pairs.target:
Pali’-pali’ iyoh mitia’ tudu’
Yesus, sa’-E di’-e kasig muat munua luah so’ topat inoh.

pairs.source: Now there was there nigh unto the mountains a great herd of swine feeding.
pairs.target:
Di’-e juua’ so’ odop-e de’ muno’, bogo’ oyua’ de’ kalik man-e de’
tilipang pungu’.

pairs.source: And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them.
pairs.target:
Muat munua mo’ mitia’ tudu’ Yesus, “Oda’ leh ko’ih
molot kaang gonan oyua’ de’ muno’.”

pairs.source: And forthwith Jesus gave them leave. And the unclean spirits went out, and entered into the swine: and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea, (they were about two thousand;) and were choked in the sea.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ oda’ muat munua de’
muno’ luah so’ gonan dali inoh yohmo’ molot daang gonan kaban oyua’
de’ muno’. Sua’ oyua’ de’ muno’ mo’ bitabum so’ tilipang pungu’, kaang
donu yohmo’ kobos longod. Oyua’ de’ kobos inoh kulang lobih ogi’ duwoh
libu polong.

pairs.source: And they that fed the swine fled, and told [it] in the city, and in the country. And they went out to see what it was that was done.
pairs.target:
Ayua de’ jaga oyua’ de’ muno’ mo’ bikoduh buu ke’ kota, ke’
kupua’-kupua’ de’ sinok ngan-e tanon gah inoh. Nya’a mo’ nog ninga’ oni’  de’ magah-a inoh.

pairs.source: And they come to Jesus, and see him that was possessed with the devil, and had the legion, sitting, and clothed, and in his right mind: and they were afraid.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ muno’ mo’ odi tudu’ Yesus yohmo’ ninga’
dali de’ obuah bikalui muat munua inoh gulu’, yoh mo’ pakai pimakai-e
daang-e di’-e tiya’ bako’. Sua’ nya’a de’ nog de’ muno’ mo’ tolu.

pairs.source: And they that saw [it] told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil, and [also] concerning the swine.
pairs.target:
Sua’
nya’a de’ ninga’ dali inoh duoh kaban oyua’ inoh, mo’ silita oni de’ mo’
ninga’-a.

pairs.source: And they began to pray him to depart out of their coasts.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ lo’o de’ Gerasa inoh mo’ ulih-ulih mitia’ oda’ Yesus buu so’
topat inoh.

pairs.source: And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus mo’ muat kaang olud, dali de’ mokua’ obuah bikalui
muat munua inoh mitia’ odop-e ya’ suwa’ nuna’ Yesus.

pairs.source: Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him, Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus jaman-e, yohmo’ in-e, “Pali’ negeh, tanon tudu’ madih
ayua mu’, oni de’ mo’ nai Topa’ tudu’ mu’u duoh tanon nang Topa’ masi’
tudu’ mu’u.”

pairs.source: And he departed, and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him: and all [men] did marvel.
pairs.target:
Dali inoh mo’ buu, yohmo’ odi magah ke’ topat de’ sobot nya’a nang,
“Simoong Kota”. Dano’ iyoh mo’ silita oni de’ mo’ nai Yesus tudu’ odop-e.
Sua’ nya’a ilan ngojit oni’ de’ silita-e.

pairs.source: And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side, much people gathered unto him: and he was nigh unto the sea.
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E pali’ motas Donu Galilea pakai olud.
Takal Yesus mo’ nog polad donu, nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ bitodod-todod odi
nguma’ Iyoh.

pairs.source: And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name; and when he saw him, he fell at his feet,
pairs.target:
Pimipin topat simayang agama Yahudi de’ adon Yairus
nog tudu’ Yesus. Takal yoh mo’ ninga’ Yesus, yohmo’ gulu’ bikunyug de’
sulung jowin-E.

pairs.source: And besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death: [I pray thee], come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed; and she shall live.
pairs.target:
Daang-e in-e, “Tok-tok ku’ mitia’ tulung tudu’ Ingan,
odi ke’ boli ku’ dio’, toma’ gonan onak dayung ku’ de’ bona’, sa’-e mokua’,
duoh di’-e kobos.”

pairs.source: And [Jesus] went with him; and much people followed him, and thronged him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ lasu’ odi duoh Yairus. Nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ odi siuah-siuah-e
bituna’ duoh Yesus daang-e bitodod-todod, so’ boit so’ to’uh-E.

pairs.source: And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,
pairs.target:
Daang uluk nya’a de’ muno’, ogi’ ni’ na’an dayung de’ obuah onam
bubu’, onam nog ko’is-e de’ lika yoh noman-e, mo’ simoong duwoh sowa’
tuui-e.

pairs.source: And had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse,
pairs.target:
Mo’ puas yoh ngubat-e sape nog obua’ halta benda-e, pak-e alua’
geh di’-e mokua’. Makin onu makin bitamah bona’.

pairs.source: When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment.
pairs.target:
Dayung inoh mo’
ngojit oni' de’ mo’ nai Yesus so’ nya’a de’ bogo’, yoh mo’ odi sinok Yesus
so’ dug-E.

pairs.source: For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole.
pairs.target:
Yohmo’ in-e daang otin-e, “Simo’ ku’ tapod toma’ jubah-E,
oku’ pasti mokua’.”

pairs.source: And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up; and she felt in [her] body that she was healed of that plague.
pairs.target: Takal inoh geh yoh toma’ jubah Yesus, onam ko’is-e lasu’ mokua’.

pairs.source: And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him, turned him about in the press, and said, Who touched my clothes?
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh Yesus ngoon ogi’ kuasa de’ luah so’ odop-E. Yesus mo’   
kumiat tudu’ nya’a de’ bogo’ Yoh mo’ sikian in-E, “Osi de’ toma’ jubah
Ku’?”

pairs.source: And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee, and sayest thou, Who touched me?
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ in-e, “Idoh keh Ingan ninga’ nya’a bogo’ de’
bitodod-todod? Oni nai Ingan sikian osi de’ toma’ odop Ingan.”

pairs.source: And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing.
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ ninga’ kati’-kanih osi de’ toma’ odop-E.

pairs.source: But the woman fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her, came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth.
pairs.target:
Dayung inoh
mo’ kimotol tolu takal-e mo’ pu’an nang odop-e mo’ mokua’, yoh mo’
gulu’ bikunyug daang jowin-e sium tana’ de’ sulung jowin Yesus, yoh mo’
ngaku’ nang odop-e de’ toma’ jubah Yesus.

pairs.source: And he said unto her, Daughter, thy faith hath made thee whole; go in peace, and be whole of thy plague.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ dayung
inoh, “Luban mu’u bisaya’ punua’ tudu’ Oku’ mu’u mo’ mokua’, pali’ leh
daang otin de’ bidanah. Mu’u mo’ tok-tok mokua’.”

pairs.source: While he yet spake, there came from the ruler of the synagogue’s [house certain] which said, Thy daughter is dead: why troublest thou the Master any further?
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus alua’ sina, kudu-kudu na’an nya’a so’ boli Yairus mo’ nog
tanon in-e, “Onak dayung ingan mo’ kobos, dusah tiya’ nye’ nyusah Gulu
neh!”

pairs.source: As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken, he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue, Be not afraid, only believe.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus di’-e piduli oni’ de’ nang odop-e de’ muno’, Yesus mo’
sina tudu’ Yairus, “Ma’ tolu, bisaya’ negeh!”

pairs.source: And he suffered no man to follow him, save Peter, and James, and John the brother of James.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ lasu’ ponu, Yoh
jaman nya’a ni’ na’an tuang di’ so’on geh nuna’ Odop-E, jok-e oda’ Petrus,
Yakobus duoh madih-e Yohanes.

pairs.source: And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue, and seeth the tumult, and them that wept and wailed greatly.
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ nog boli Yairus,
yoh mo’ ninga’ bogo’ nya’a de’ si’ian nang puas bogan-e.

pairs.source: And when he was come in, he saith unto them, Why make ye this ado, and weep? the damsel is not dead, but sleepeth.
pairs.target:
Yesus molot,
Yoh mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Oni nai ingan kiak kaung si’ian de’
in inoh neh? Onak opot itih idoh di’-e kobos, iyoh jok-e bo’os.”

pairs.source: And they laughed him to scorn. But when he had put them all out, he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel, and them that were with him, and entereth in where the damsel was lying.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ muno’ mo’ towoh Yesus. Yoh mo’ oda’ sua’ nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’
luah. Yesus mo’ toban sino’ sama’ onak opot inoh duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E
molot kaang bilit-e.

pairs.source: And he took the damsel by the hand, and said unto her, Talitha cumi; which is, being interpreted, Damsel, I say unto thee, arise.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ kagong tongan onak dayung Yairus inoh,
Yoh mo’ sina tudu’-e, “Talita kum,” loti-e “Oi onak dayung, Oku’ oda’ mu’u
mokat!”

pairs.source: And straightway the damsel arose, and walked; for she was [of the age] of twelve years. And they were astonished with a great astonishment.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh onak dayung inoh mo’ lasu’ mokat mujuag, yoh mo’
ponu. Takal inoh umul-e simoong duwoh sowa’. Sua’ nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’
mo’ sukup doon-e daang-e ilan-e.

pairs.source: And he charged them straitly that no man should know it; and commanded that something should be given her to eat.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ isin-isin jaman odop-e de’ muno’ tanon tudu’ osi sija’-e.
Yesus mo’ in-e, “Ngin oda’ onak opot inoh man.”

pairs.source: And he went out from thence, and came into his own country; and his disciples follow him.
pairs.target:
So’ boli Yairus, Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E pali’ ke’ kupua’-E Nazaret,
kupua’ asal-E.

pairs.source: And when the sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue: and many hearing [him] were astonished, saying, From whence hath this [man] these things? and what wisdom [is] this which is given unto him, that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?
pairs.target:
Takal Onu Sabat, Iyoh mo’ mulai ngajal nya’a de’ bogo’ de’ boli topat
simayang agama Yahudi. Sua’ nya’a de’ ngojit oni’ de’ ngajal-E mo’ sukup  ilan-e. Nya’a de’ muno’ mo’ in-e, “So’ ki so’-E so’on ilmu de’ masam-masam?
Kuasa de’ oni wat-e de’ ogi’ da’-A? Oni wat-e ngan-E ponai nai oni’ de’ ilan
nya’a?

pairs.source: Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Joses, and of Juda, and Simon? and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him.
pairs.target:
De’ pu’an oto’, Yoh itih onak tukang koyuh. Sino’-E Maria, duoh
kudu-kudu sudi’-E de’ dali, Yakobus, Yoses, Yudas duoh Simon. Sudi’-E
de’ dayung tuang ogi’ geh dati’.” Noh leh ngan odop-e de’ muno’ dolia’-e
tilima’ Iyoh dano’.

pairs.source: But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honour, but in his own country, and among his own kin, and in his own house.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Daki-daki sija’-e nya’a pimodo
tudu’ nabi, pak-e jok-e nya’a de’ kupua’-e duoh madih ayua duoh sikia’
sudi’-e de’ di’-e pimodo tudu’-e.”

pairs.source: And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk, and healed [them].
pairs.target:
Dano’, Iyoh di’-e dapod nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a, jok-e kudu-kudu na’an
nya’a de’ toma’-E de’ oda’-E mokua’ so’ onam-e.

pairs.source:
And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went round about the villages, teaching.
  7	And he called [unto him] the twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two; and gave them power over unclean spirits;
pairs.target:
Yesus sukup ilan-e, oni
nai nya’a de’ kupua’-E di’-e bisaya’ tudu’ odop-E. Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ ponu ngajal nya’a ke’ kupua’-kupua’ de’
bokon.
mo’ mogan simoong duwoh na’an rasul-E. Iyoh mo’ ngin
kuasa tudu’-e sa’-e ponai kasig muat munua, yohmo’ oda’ odop-e de’ muno’
odi nga’ duwoh-duwoh.

pairs.source: And commanded them that they should take nothing for [their] journey, save a staff only; no scrip, no bread, no money in [their] purse:
pairs.target:
Iyoh sibaya tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’ jaman toban
balang-balang de’ ya’ pakai-e koda’ onyad, duit, duoh bek. Jok nye’ so’on
toban sikuud.

pairs.source: But [be] shod with sandals; and not put on two coats.
pairs.target: Jok nye’ pakai silipal duoh bojuh de’ polong nye’ sija’-e.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into an house, there abide till ye depart from that place.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’ in-e lagi’, “Simo’ ingan nog de’ kota, ogi’ nya’a tilima’ ingan
lo’o de’ boli-e, nye’ mo’ ngilumon dano’ nog ingan buu pali’ so’ kota inoh.

pairs.source: And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet for a testimony against them. Verily I say unto you, It shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrha in the day of judgment, than for that city.
pairs.target:
Simo’-e ogi’ nya’a de’ topat so’ ingan odi, di’-e tilima’ ingan duoh dolia’-e
ngojit oni’ de’ nang ingan, nye’ mo’ buu daang nye’ nguguah lopu tana' so’
lupa’ po’on ingan, sa’-e jadin tanda Topa’ ya’ ngukum odop-e de’ muno’.”

pairs.source: And they went out, and preached that men should repent.
pairs.target:
Takal-e mokua’ ngojit sibaya Yesus, ke’ simoong duwoh na’an rasul-E
mo’ bilakat ponu, tanon tudu’ sua’ nya’a de’ tapod-e, oda’ togan olan de’
ja’at duoh pali’ ke’ olan Topa’, nye’ mo’ nuna’ oni’ de’ nang-E.

pairs.source: And they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick, and healed [them].
pairs.target:
Bogo’
basa muat munua de’ kasig rasul-rasul Yesus, yoh gasak inyua’ zaitun de’
gonan nya’a de’ monam oda’ mokua’.

pairs.source: And king Herod heard [of him]; (for his name was spread abroad:) and he said, That John the Baptist was risen from the dead, and therefore mighty works do shew forth themselves in him.
pairs.target:
Laja Herodes mo’ ngojit gah tentang Yesus, dop-e adon-E mo’ timogah kati’-kanih. Ogi’ nya’a de’ nang, “Yohanes Pembaptis pali’ idip ba’uh, iyoh
ngan-e ogi’ kuasa-e nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a.”

pairs.source: Others said, That it is Elias. And others said, That it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets.
pairs.target:
Pak-e  
ogi’ geh nya’a de’ nang, “Iyoh itih nabi Elia de’ no’uh-e!” Ogi’
geh nya’a de’ nang “Iyoh itih nabi de’ samah koda’ nabi-nabi so’ joman
de’ no’uh-e.”

pairs.source: But when Herod heard [thereof], he said, It is John, whom I beheaded: he is risen from the dead.
pairs.target:
Takal Laja Herodes mo’ ngojit gah inoh iyoh mo’ in-e, “Iyoh pasti
Yohanes Pembaptis de’ no’uh-e, de’ mo’ mokua’ ku’ oda’ nya’a notok
tungua’-e de’ mo’ pali’ idip ba’uh.”

pairs.source: For Herod himself had sent forth and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias’ sake, his brother Philip’s wife: for he had married her.
pairs.target:
Dop-e de’ dio’ so’ kano’ Laja Herodes itih leh de’ oda’ nya’a takap
duoh pasung-e yohmo’ na’ kaang jel. Herodes nai wat inoh, dop-e Yohanes
Pembaptis ngalah nang Herodes mit Herodias oda’ jadin sowon-e. De’
dio’, Herodias itih iyohleh sowon Filipus, Filipus itih madih odop Herodes.

pairs.source: For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother’s wife.
pairs.target:
Yohanes mo’ silalu ngalah Herodes nang polih nye’ mit sowon madih
nye’ oda’ jadin sowon nye’.

pairs.source: Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have killed him; but she could not:
pairs.target:
Iyoh ngan Herodias bu’ui tudu’ Yohanes,
yoh mo’ ya’ ngabos-e. Pak-e yoh di’-e ponai nai wat inoh,

pairs.source: For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man and an holy, and observed him; and when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly.
pairs.target:
dop-e Herodes
pimodo tudu’ Yohanes. Iyoh pu’an-e geh nang Yohanes Pembaptis ulang
de’ bonal, doi’ salah-e. Yoh ngan-e oda’ nya’a jaga Yohanes sa’ nya’a di’-e
ngabos-e. Pak-e bilang-e ngojit pingunang Yohanes, yoh mo’ jadin bigaduh
kila-e, pak-e yoh sonang geh ngojit-e.

pairs.source: And when a convenient day was come, that Herod on his birthday made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief [estates] of Galilee;
pairs.target:
Nyuang-nyuang-e Herodias mo’ so’on olan ngan-e ya’ ngabos Yohanes
Pembaptis. Takal onu Herodes biluman onu limokah-e, yoh mo’ ngunang
sua’ piayuh-piayuh, pimipin-pimipin sidadu, duoh ulang-ulang de’ timogah
de’ propinsi Galilea.

pairs.source: And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel, Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give [it] thee.
pairs.target:
Takal-e biluman inoh, onak dayung Herodias bitana’. Herodes duoh
sua’ nya’a de’ ogi’ daang lami inoh sukup doon-e ninga’ iyoh bitana’. Yoh
ngan Herodes in-e, “Oni de’ ya’ mitia’ mu’ tudu’ oku’, tanon negeh tia’ ku’
ngin da’ nye’.”

pairs.source: And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shalt ask of me, I will give [it] thee, unto the half of my kingdom.
pairs.target:
Herodes mo’ bisupah tudu’ onak Herodias yoh mo’ in-e, “Oni sija’-e
de’ mitia’ mu’ ku’ ngin da’ nye’, bial-e sitengah so’ negeli de’ kagong ku’.”

pairs.source: And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist.
pairs.target:
Onak dayung inoh mo’ odi sikian tudu’ sino’-e “Oni de’ patut oku’
mitia’-e?” In-e.
Sino’-e mo’ nyawot-e, “Mitia’ bak Yohanes Pembaptis.”

pairs.source: And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me by and by in a charger the head of John the Baptist.
pairs.target:
Onak dayung inoh mo’ pali’ ngaduap Herodes yohmo’ in-e, “Oku’
mitia’ bak Yohanes Pembaptis tudu’ ingan, katod tudu’ oku’ na’ daang
talam!”

pairs.source: And the king was exceeding sorry; [yet] for his oath’s sake, and for their sakes which sat with him, he would not reject her.
pairs.target:
Takal Herodes ngojit oni’ de’ mitia’-e inoh bak Yohanes Pembaptis,
otin Herodes mo’ sukup ngilobu’, pak-e yoh mo’ di’-e ponai nalik sina-e,
dop-e mo’ tilanyul bisupah de’ jowin nya’a de’ ngunang-e.

pairs.source: And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought: and he went and beheaded him in the prison,
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’
lasu’ oda’ sidadu-e notok tungua’ Yohanes Pembaptis toban tudu’ odop-e.  Sidadu-e mo’ lasu’ odi ke’ jel yoh mo’ notok tungua’ Yohanes.

pairs.source: And brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel: and the damsel gave it to her mother.
pairs.target:
Mokua’
inoh yoh mo’ toban bak Yohanes de’ na’-e daang talam, yohmo’ ngin tudu’
onak dayung Herodias. Onak dayung inoh mo’ ngin tudu’ sino’-e lagi’.

pairs.source: And when his disciples heard [of it], they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.
pairs.target:
Takal pinuna’-pinuna’ Yohanes mo’ ngojit nang Yohanes mo’ obuah
ngabos, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ odi mit todang-e yohmo’ ngubul-e.

pairs.source: And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.
pairs.target:
Ke’ simoong duwoh na’an rasul Yesus de’ pait-e inoh pali’ tikuluk
duoh Yesus. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ tanon sua’ oni’ de’ mo’ nai-e duoh
oni’ de’ ngajal-e.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest a while: for there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ rasul-rasul-E de’ muno’, “Ja’ oto’
odi ke’ topat de’ motug, de’ doi’ nya’a da’-e sa’ oto’ tapod nosa’ lo’o ni’
tilia’.” Yesus in inoh, saai nya’a sikiya bogo’ de’ nog, de’ buu. Yesus duoh
pinuna’-pinuna’-E di’-e supot man.

pairs.source: And they departed into a desert place by ship privately.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ buu pakai
olud, ngan-e odi ke’ topat de’ doi’ nya’a da’-e.

pairs.source: And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and outwent them, and came together unto him.
pairs.target:
Pak-e bogo’ nya’a de’ kilin odop-e de’ muno’ buu, duoh pu’an kaki
so’-e ya’ odi. Nya’a mo’ obua’ bikoduh so’ kota-kota odi ke’ topat de’ so’
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E odi. Nya’a de’ muno’ mo’ dio’ nog.

pairs.source: And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep not having a shepherd: and he began to teach them many things.
pairs.target:
Takal
Yesus mo’ ma’ad so’ olud ke’ doyoh, Yoh mo’ ninga’ nya’a mo’ bogo’. Iyoh
masi’ tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, dop-e Yoh ninga’ nya’a de’ muno’ samah
koda’ domba de’ doi’ nya’a piala-e. Noh leh ngan Yesus mo’ mulai tanon
bogo’ pingajal tudu’ nya’a de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time [is] far passed:
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ngumi, pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ Yesus,
“Onu mo’ ya’ ngalom, topat itih juua’ so’ nya’a.

pairs.source: Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread: for they have nothing to eat.
pairs.target:
Lobih paguh Ingan
oda’ nya’a de’ muti’ buu so’ topat itih, sa’-a tapod milih pinguman-e de’
kupua’-kupua’ de’ ogi’ sinok itih.”

pairs.source: He answered and said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred pennyworth of bread, and give them to eat?
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Ingan negeh de’ ngin man tudu’ nya’a
de’ muti’!”
In odop-e de’ muno’ nyawot-e, “Doi’ ko’ih taan milih pinguman de’
loga-e duwoh latus kiping duit pilak, ngan ko’ih ya’ ma’an odop-e de’
kiang-kiang itih?”

pairs.source: He saith unto them, How many loaves have ye? go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five, and two fishes.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ bisikian tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Suba ninga’ dio’,
duam kudu kueh ingan de’ ogi’!” 
Takal-e mokua’ ninga’-e yoh mo’ in-e, “Ogi’ limoh kueh, ogi’ duwoh
polong ikian.”

pairs.source: And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass.
pairs.target: Iyoh mo’ oda’ nya’a de’ bogo’ gulu’ bikuluk de’ tun duh.

pairs.source: And they sat down in ranks, by hundreds, and by fifties.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ gulu’ bikuluk ogi’ de’ nga’ silatus, ogi’ de’
nga’ limoh pulu’ daang ni’ uluk.

pairs.source: And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fishes, he looked up to heaven, and blessed, and brake the loaves, and gave [them] to his disciples to set before them; and the two fishes divided he among them all.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mit limoh kueh baya duwoh
polong ikian inoh, Iyoh mo’ bigalong ke’ longit, yohmo’ bisukul tudu’
Topa’. Mokua’ inoh Iyoh mo’ nyipiak-nyipiak kueh-e, yohmo’ ngin tudu’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E sa’-e kutung tudu’ sua’ nya’a. Watnoh geh wat-e duoh
ikian de’ duwoh polong inoh, Iyoh bikutung tudu’ sua’ nya’a.

pairs.source: And they did all eat, and were filled.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a
de’ muno’ man nog busuah-e.

pairs.source: And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments, and of the fishes.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh, nya’a de’ muno’ mo’ nguluk
kuban-e. Takal-e mo’ tikuluk, alua’ ogi’ simoong duwoh bakul.

pairs.source: And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men.
pairs.target:
Nya’a
de’ suwa’ man inoh ogi’ kila-kila limoh libu na’an dali.

pairs.source: And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship, and to go to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while he sent away the people.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus lasu’ oda’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E muat de’ olud dio’ odi ke’ kota Betsaida de’ polad Donu Galilea. Iyoh mo’ oda’ nya’a de’ bogo’ buu
pali’.

pairs.source: And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray.
pairs.target:
Takal nya’a de’ bogo’ buu, Yesus mo’ ma’ad ke’ tun pungu’, ngan-e
ya’ bidoa.

pairs.source: And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land.
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ngalom, olud de’ pakai pinuna’-pinuna’-E
inoh mo’ nog uun donu, pak-e Yesus alua’ de’ doyoh.

pairs.source: And he saw them toiling in rowing; for the wind was contrary unto them: and about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them.
pairs.target:
Yesus ninga’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E lolah posah bikayuh olud-e dop-e sobak nog so’ jowin
olud-e. Takal onu alua’ bosow, Yesus odi tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, simadi-E
ponu tun pi’in. Iyoh ponu mun de’ ya’ kawan odop-e de’ muno’ ja’-a.

pairs.source: But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out:
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ ninga’ Iyoh ponu de’ tun pi’in, odop-e de’ muno’
mo’ saka’ nang inoh munua. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nang bogan-e.

pairs.source: For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and saith unto them, Be of good cheer: it is I; be not afraid.
pairs.target:
Sua’
odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ gogoh duoh tolu takal-e ninga’ nang inoh Yesus.
Pak-e Yesus lasu’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ma’ tolu! Oku’ itih Yesus.”

pairs.source: And he went up unto them into the ship; and the wind ceased: and they were sore amazed in themselves beyond measure, and wondered.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ma’ad kaang olud duoh odop-e de’ muno’, sobak mo’ lasu’
lo’o, pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ sukup ilan-e.

pairs.source: For they considered not [the miracle] of the loaves: for their heart was hardened.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ alua’ geh
di’-e ngiloti-e, takal-e ninga’ Yesus ma’an nya’a limoh libu na’an pakai
limoh kiping kueh, duoh pakai duwoh polong ikian, sobab otin odop-e de’
muno’ madod.

pairs.source: And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Gennesaret, and drew to the shore.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ nog polad donu, Iyoh mo’
ma’ad ke’ doyoh ke’ topat de’ adon Genesaret.

pairs.source: And when they were come out of the ship, straightway they knew him,
pairs.target: Takal Yesus mo’ ma’ad  so’ aang olud, nya’a mo’ lasu’ piluh nang Yoh Yesus.

pairs.source: And ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in beds those that were sick, where they heard he was.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ muno’
mo’ bikoduh ke’ boli-boli nya’a de’ ogi’ de’ topat inoh. Odop-e de’ muno’
mo’ bitawiak toban nya’a de’ monam de’ tun tilam yohmo’ toban tudu’
Yesus. Daki sija’-e so’ Yesus odi takal odop-e de’ muno’ pu’an-e, yoh lasu’
toban nya’a de’ monam tudu’-E.

pairs.source: And whithersoever he entered, into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him that they might touch if it were but the border of his garment: and as many as touched him were made whole.
pairs.target:
Daki sija’-e Yesus odi, bait de’ kota, de’
kupua’-kupua’ de’ ayuh, duoh kupua’-kupua’ de’ isit. Nya’a silalu toban
ulang de’ monam piguling de’ topat nya’a bijua, mitia’ masi’ tudu’ Yesus
kadu-e toma’ tubon jubah-E sija’-e. Yohmo’ sua’ odop-e de’ monam de’
toma’ tubon jubah Yesus mokua’.

pairs.source: Then came together unto him the Pharisees, and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ onu, takal kudu-kudu na’an ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi
duoh kudu-kudu na’an gulu agama Yahudi so’ Yerusalem odi bitapod
duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread with defiled, that is to say, with unwashen, hands, they found fault.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ ninga’ pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus man
pakai tongan-e de’ ko’is, di’-e mamia’-e.

pairs.source: For the Pharisees, and all the Jews, except they wash [their] hands oft, eat not, holding the tradition of the elders.
pairs.target:
Dop-e sua’ ulang Yahudi ya’ di’-e
man, mo’-e di’-e mamia’ tongan-e nuna’ adat sumuk babai-e. Amot-e ulang
Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi.

pairs.source: And [when they come] from the market, except they wash, they eat not. And many other things there be, which they have received to hold, [as] the washing of cups, and pots, brasen vessels, and of tables.
pairs.target:
Yoh di’-e so’on man oni’ de’ milih-e so’
pasal, mo’-e alua’ di’-e mamuh. Bogo’ lagi’ adat sumuk babai-e de’ halus
yoh nuna’-e, koda’ mamia’ sakil makup duoh balang-balang de’ so’ tibaga.

pairs.source: Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him, Why walk not thy disciples according to the tradition of the elders, but eat bread with unwashen hands?
pairs.target:
Noh leh ngan uluk ulang Farisi duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi sikian tudu’
Yesus, “Oni nai pinuna’-pinuna’ Mu’ man di’-e mamia’ tongan-e? Oni nai-e
di’-e nuna’ atulan adat sumuk babai oto’?”

pairs.source: He answered and said unto them, Well hath Esaias prophesied of you hypocrites, as it is written, This people honoureth me with [their] lips, but their heart is far from me.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Oi ulang de’ suka pula’-pula’! Tutuas koda’ de’
nang Topa’ pakai nabi Yesaya no’uh-e de’ in-e,
‘Nya’a de’ muno’ jok-e nyomah Oku’ de’ boba’-e,
pak-e daang otin-e idoh.

pairs.source: Howbeit in vain do they worship me, teaching [for] doctrines the commandments of men.
pairs.target:
Doi’ guna-e yoh nyomah Oku’,
dop-e yoh jok-e ngajal atulan adat de’ nai manusia.’
Inoh leh de’ mo’ tanon-e.

pairs.source: For laying aside the commandment of God, ye hold the tradition of men, [as] the washing of pots and cups: and many other such like things ye do.
pairs.target:
Pilitah-pilitah de’ so’ Topa’ ingan togan-e, ingan
mo’ ulih-ulih nuna’ atulan adat de’ nai manusia.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Full well ye reject the commandment of God, that ye may keep your own tradition.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e lagi’ tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ponai manah geh ingan
nulak pilitah Topa’, ngan ingan ya’ nuna’ atulan adat de’ nai manusia.

pairs.source: For Moses said, Honour thy father and thy mother; and, Whoso curseth father or mother, let him die the death:
pairs.target:
Nabi Musa mo’ ngin atulan wat tih, ‘Pimodo leh tudu’ sama’ sino’ mu’,’
duoh ‘Osi de’ di’-e pimodo duoh sama’ sino’-e, halus obuah ukum ngabos.’

pairs.source: But ye say, If a man shall say to his father or mother, [It is] Corban, that is to say, a gift, by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me; [he shall be free].
pairs.target:
Pak-e ingan ngajal nang doi’ salah-e mo’ ingan sina tudu’ pingoma ingan, ‘Doi’ ku’ tapod tulung ingan, dop-e sua’ oni’ de’ ya’ ngin ku’ tudu’ ingan
mo’ ngin ku’ tudu’ Topa’.’

pairs.source: And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;
pairs.target:
Oni’ de’ ngajal ingan inoh mo’ oda’ nya’a di’-e
piduli pingoma-e.

pairs.source: Making the word of God of none effect through your tradition, which ye have delivered: and many such like things do ye.
pairs.target:
Jadin ingan nang pilitah Topa’ di’-e tiya’ toga, pak-e
ingan mo’ nuna’ atulan adat de’ nai manusia. Alua’ bogo’ oni’ de’ koda’
itih de’ nai ingan.”

pairs.source: And when he had called all the people [unto him], he said unto them, Hearken unto me every one [of you], and understand:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mogan nya’a de’ bogo’, Iyoh mo’ sina tudu’-e, “Ngojit dio’
sa’ ingan ngiloti-e!

pairs.source: There is nothing from without a man, that entering into him can defile him: but the things which come out of him, those are they that defile the man.
pairs.target:
Sua’ oni’ de’ molot kaang polong nya’a, doi’ de’ oda’
nya’a ko’is, pak-e sua’ oni’ de’ luah so’ polong nya’a inoh leh de’ oda’ nya’a
ko’is.

pairs.source: If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.
pairs.target: Osi de’ ogi’ kojit-e, iyoh ngojit-e!”

pairs.source: And when he was entered into the house from the people, his disciples asked him concerning the parable.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ buu togan nya’a de’ bogo’ yohmo’ molot kaang boli,
pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ sikian oni loti silita inoh.

pairs.source: And he saith unto them, Are ye so without understanding also? Do ye not perceive, that whatsoever thing from without entereth into the man, [it] cannot defile him;
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sina in-e tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, “Idoh keh di’ ingan
pu’an-e, sua’ oni’ de’ molot kaang polong nya’a, doi’ de’ oda’ nya’a ko’is?

pairs.source: Because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly, and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats?
pairs.target:
Dop-e oni’ de’ man nya’a di’-e molot kaang otin nya’a, pak-e molot kaang
to’in nya’a, mokua’ inoh nya’a odi sa’at ke’ jaman.”
Yesus in inoh ngan-e tanon nang sua’ pinguman bisig, doi’ de’ polih
nye’ man-e.

pairs.source: And he said, That which cometh out of the man, that defileth the man.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e lagi’, “Sua’ oni’ de’ luah so’ polong nya’a inoh leh de’
oda’ nya’a ko’is.

pairs.source: For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, fornications, murders,
pairs.target:
Dop-e so’ aang otin nya’a timul pikil de’ ja’at, idip koda’
sowon duoh bonon pak-e alua’ di’-e kawin, noku, ngabos,

pairs.source: Thefts, covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness:
pairs.target:
biamai, sua’
oni’ yoh ya’ kaku’-e, suka nai oni’ de’ ja’at, nipu, idip nuna’ kila odop-e
de’ ja’at, sinia’, suka pija’at nya’a, samuh, li’iang bak-e.

pairs.source: All these evil things come from within, and defile the man.
pairs.target: Sua’ oni’ de’ ja’at inoh luah so’ aang otin nya’a duoh ka’is odop-e.”

pairs.source: And from thence he arose, and went into the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and entered into an house, and would have no man know [it]: but he could not be hid.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ buu so’ topat inoh yohmo’ odi ke’ topat de’
sinok kota Tirus. Iyoh molot kaang boli sa’-e doi’ nya’a pu’an-E. Pak-e Yoh
di’-e ponai ya’ suan odop-E.

pairs.source: For a [certain] woman, whose young daughter had an unclean spirit, heard of him, and came and fell at his feet:
pairs.target:
Ogi’ sino’ nya’a de’ onak dayung-e obuah
bikalui muat munua. Takal yoh mo’ ngojit tentang Yesus, yoh mo’ lasu’
nog tudu’-E yoh mo’ bonal-bonal mitia’ masi’ tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: The woman was a Greek, a Syrophenician by nation; and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil out of her daughter.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mitia’
tulung tudu’ Yesus oda’ kasig muat munua so’ gonan onak-e. Dayung inoh
di’-e ulang Yahudi. Iyoh so’ Fenisia de’ propinsi Siria.

pairs.source: But Jesus said unto her, Let the children first be filled: for it is not meet to take the children’s bread, and to cast [it] unto the dogs.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Onak opot leh de’ dio’ nye’ ma’an-e, dop-e di’-e
patut pinguman de’ ya’ ngin nye’ tudu’ onak opot, nye’ ngin de’ kosuang.”

pairs.source: And she answered and said unto him, Yes, Lord: yet the dogs under the table eat of the children’s crumbs.
pairs.target:
Pak-e dayung inoh mo’ nyawot-E, “Tok bonal oni’ de’ nang Ingan, pak-e
kosuang man-e geh puluh pinguman de’ luluh so’ tun mija.”

pairs.source: And he said unto her, For this saying go thy way; the devil is gone out of thy daughter.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot dayung inoh, “Dop-e mu’u mo’ nyawot in inoh,
pali’ negeh. Onak mu’ moh mo’ buu muat munua so’ gonan-e.”

pairs.source: And when she was come to her house, she found the devil gone out, and her daughter laid upon the bed.
pairs.target:
Dayung inoh mo’ buu. Nog boli-e, yoh mo’ ninga’ onak-e guling de’
topat bo’os, dop-e muat munua mo’ buu so’ gonan-e.

pairs.source: And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ buu so’ topat de’
sinok kota Tirus, odi ke’ donu Galilea ngilusu’ kota Sidon. Odop-e de’
