muno’ mo’ ponu ke’ topat de’ nang nya’a geh Simoong Kota.

pairs.source: And they bring unto him one that was deaf, and had an impediment in his speech; and they beseech him to put his hand upon him.
pairs.target:
Takal-e
dano’, kudu-kudu na’an nya’a toban tudu’ Yesus ni’ na’an nya’a de’ bongam
daang-e bebe’. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ bonal-bonal mitia’ oda’ Yesus toma’-e
sa’ iyoh mokua’.

pairs.source: And he took him aside from the multitude, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spit, and touched his tongue;
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ toban nya’a inoh buu so’ uluk nya’a de’ bogo’,
duam odop-e duwoh ja’-e. Yesus mo’ tiluak pakai tilinyu’-E so’ duwoh
lubang kojit nya’a inoh. Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ nguja’ de’ lupa’ tongan
odop-E duoh gasak loyang-E de’ jola’ nya’a de’ bebe’ inoh.

pairs.source: And looking up to heaven, he sighed, and saith unto him, Ephphatha, that is, Be opened.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh
Yesus mo’ bigalong ke’ longit daang-e nalik asong-E, yohmo’ sina tudu’
nya’a inoh, “Efata,” loti-e, “Tibuka’ mey!”

pairs.source: And straightway his ears were opened, and the string of his tongue was loosed, and he spake plain.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh yoh mo’ lasu’
ponai ngojit, jola’-e mo’ lasu’ dodot yoh mo’ lasu’ ponai sina.

pairs.source: And he charged them that they should tell no man: but the more he charged them, so much the more a great deal they published [it];
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sibaya tudu’ sua’ nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’ jaman kilakal tudu’
nya’a de’ bokon. Pak-e makin Yesus jaman-e, makin nya’a de’ muno’ silita
kati’ kanih.

pairs.source: And were beyond measure astonished, saying, He hath done all things well: he maketh both the deaf to hear, and the dumb to speak.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a de’ ngojit gah inoh mo’ ilan-e. Odop-e de’ muno’
mo’ in-e, “Paguh manah sua’ oni’ de’ nai-E. Nya’a de’ bongam ponai ngojit,
duoh nya’a de’ bebe’ ponai sina.”

pairs.source: In those days the multitude being very great, and having nothing to eat, Jesus called his disciples [unto him], and saith unto them,
pairs.target:
Kudu-kudu onu mokua’ inoh, ogi’ bilibu nya’a nog ba’uh tudu’
Yesus. Nya’a de’ muno’ doi’ oni’ de’ ya’ man-e. Yesus mo’ mogan
pinuna’-pinuna’-E yohmo’ in-e,

pairs.source: I have compassion on the multitude, because they have now been with me three days, and have nothing to eat:
pairs.target:
“Masi’ nyam Ku’ tudu’ nya’a de’ bogo’
itih neh. Mo’ taluh onu yoh bituna’ duoh Oku’, mo’ doi’ oni-oni de’ ya’
man-e tiya’.

pairs.source: And if I send them away fasting to their own houses, they will faint by the way: for divers of them came from far.
pairs.target:
Simo’ Ku’ oda’ nya’a de’ muti’ pali’ toban to’in-e de’ pilai,
jak-e ogi’ de’ pisan de’ olan, dop-e ogi’ odop-e de’ muti’ de’ nog so’ juua’.”

pairs.source: And his disciples answered him, From whence can a man satisfy these [men] with bread here in the wilderness?
pairs.target:
Pak-e pinuna’-pinuna’-e mo’ nyawot-e, “Daki so’ to’ ya’ kalik pinguman
de’ sukup sa’an nya’a de’ kiang-kiang itih? Topat itih juua’ so’ kupua’ so’
nye’ ya’ milih pinguman.”

pairs.source: And he asked them, How many loaves have ye? And they said, Seven.
pairs.target:
In Yesus sikian tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Oni kiang kueh de’ ogi’ de’
ingan?” Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-e, “Ogi’ ju’ kiping kueh.”

pairs.source: And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground: and he took the seven loaves, and gave thanks, and brake, and gave to his disciples to set before [them]; and they did set [them] before the people.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ oda’ sua’ nya’a de’ bogo’ gulu’ de’ tana’. Yesus mo’ mit kueh
de’ ju’ kiping inoh, yohmo’ bisukul tudu’ Topa’. Yoh mo’ nyipiak-nyipiak
kueh inoh, yohmo’ ngin tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E oda’ bikutung tudu’ sua’
nya’a.

pairs.source: And they had a few small fishes: and he blessed, and commanded to set them also before [them].
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh kudu-kudu polong ikian de’ toban odop-e de’ muno’.
Yesus mo’ mit ikian yohmo’ bisukul tudu’ Topa’, Yoh mo’ ngin tudu’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E oda’ bikutung tudu’ sua’ nya’a.

pairs.source: So they did eat, and were filled: and they took up of the broken [meat] that was left seven baskets.
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a man nog
busuah-e. Mokua’ inoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ nguluk kuban nya’a man-e,
alua’ ogi’ duam ju’ bakul.

pairs.source: And they that had eaten were about four thousand: and he sent them away.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ man inoh ogi’ kulang lobih pat libu
na’an. Mokua’ man, Yesus mo’ oda’ buu pali’.

pairs.source: And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples, and came into the parts of Dalmanutha.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh
pinuna’-pinuna’-E lasu’ muat daang olud, yohmo’ odi ke’ Dalmanuta.

pairs.source: And the Pharisees came forth, and began to question with him, seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him.
pairs.target:
Kudu-kudu ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi nog bikalah duoh Yesus, oda’ Yesus bitanga kuasa-E nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a, de’ jadin tanda nang
Iyoh tok obuah pait so’ Topa’, sa’ odop-e de’ muno’ dapod kalik wat olan
ngan-e nyalah Yesus.

pairs.source: And he sighed deeply in his spirit, and saith, Why doth this generation seek after a sign? verily I say unto you, There shall no sign be given unto this generation.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nalik asong-E omu-omu-e daang in-e,
“Aah, oni nai nya’a joman de’ adin biga’an mitia’ tanda? Oku’ tanon tudu’
ingan: Idoh di’ Ku’ bitanga kuasa nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a tudu’ ingan neh!”

pairs.source: And he left them, and entering into the ship again departed to the other side.
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ buu togan odop-e de’ muno’ odi ke’ polad donu inoh.

pairs.source: Now [the disciples] had forgotten to take bread, neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus komut toban kueh, jok-e ogi’ ni’ kiping kueh
daang olud, Yesus sibaya tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E,
daang olud.
in-E, “Ma’ tau’-tau’ duoh ragi ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi duoh ragi
Laja Herodes.”

pairs.source: And he charged them, saying, Take heed, beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, and [of] the leaven of Herod.
pairs.target: Takal-e

pairs.source: And they reasoned among themselves, saying, [It is] because we have no bread.
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus mo’ bolipotak si odop-e in-e, “Yoh sina in inoh
saai oto’ di’ to’ toban kueh, yoh ngan-e in inoh.”

pairs.source: And when Jesus knew [it], he saith unto them, Why reason ye, because ye have no bread? perceive ye not yet, neither understand? have ye your heart yet hardened?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ pu’an oni’ de’ sobot odop-e de’ muno’, Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Ma’
bigaduh nang doi’ kueh de’ toban to’! Idoh di’-e wat inoh wat-e oni’ de’
nang Ku’! Madod manah pikil ingan ngan di’ ingan dapod ngiloti!

pairs.source: Having eyes, see ye not? and having ears, hear ye not? and do ye not remember?
pairs.target:
Boton
ingan ogi’, pak-e ingan koda’ nya’a de’ buta’. Kojit ingan ogi’ geh, pak-e
ingan koda’ nya’a de’ bongam. Podo idoh di’ ingan natong-e,

pairs.source: When I brake the five loaves among five thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? They say unto him, Twelve.
pairs.target:
takal Oku’
nyipiak limoh kiping kueh sa’an limoh libu na’an nya’a de’ man, duam
kudu kuban-e?”
Odop-e de’ muno’ nyawot-e, “Duam simoong duwoh bakul.”

pairs.source: And when the seven among four thousand, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up? And they said, Seven.
pairs.target:
“Takal ju’ kiping kueh sa’an pat libu na’an nya’a, duam kudu kuban-e?”
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-e, “Duam ju’ bakul punua’.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, How is it that ye do not understand?
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ in-e lagi tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Podo alua’ geh di’ ingan
ngiloti-e?”

pairs.source: And he cometh to Bethsaida; and they bring a blind man unto him, and besought him to touch him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E nog ke’ kota Betsaida,
kudu-kudu na’an nya’a toban ulang de’ buta’ tudu’ Yesus. Yohmo’ mitia’
masi’ oda’ Yesus toma’ ulang de’ buta’ inoh sa’-e tapod ninga’.

pairs.source: And he took the blind man by the hand, and led him out of the town; and when he had spit on his eyes, and put his hands upon him, he asked him if he saw ought.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’
kagong tongan-e, yohmo’ kayak toban luah so’ kota inoh. Yesus mo’ nguja’
duoh toma’ so’ duwoh boton nya’a de’ buta’ inoh. Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’
sikian tudu’-e, “Podo mu’u mo’ ponai kilin oni’?”

pairs.source: And he looked up, and said, I see men as trees, walking.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ buta’ inoh mo’ ninga’ ke’ jowin, yohmo’ in-e, “Oku’ mo’
ponai ninga’ nya’a ponu, pak-e mun sibamia tongon koyuh mun-e.”

pairs.source: After that he put [his] hands again upon his eyes, and made him look up: and he was restored, and saw every man clearly.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ toma’ ba’uh boton nya’a de’ buta’ inoh. Mokua’ inoh ke yoh
mo’ tapod ninga’ sukup telang-e, dop-e boton-e mo’ paguh.

pairs.source: And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell [it] to any in the town.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’
oda’ iyoh pali’ ke’ boli-e, Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Ma’ ya’ nosa’ ke’ kota Betsaida.”

pairs.source: And Jesus went out, and his disciples, into the towns of Caesarea Philippi: and by the way he asked his disciples, saying unto them, Whom do men say that I am?
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E odi ke’ kupua’-kupua’ de’
ogi’ de’ sinok kota Kaisarea Filipi. Takal-e alua’ daang pimonu-e Yesus
sikian tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, in-E, “Mo’-e nuna’ de’ sobot nya’a, osi Oku’
tih?”

pairs.source: And they answered, John the Baptist: but some [say], Elias; and others, One of the prophets.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-e, “Ogi’ nya’a nang Yohanes Pembaptis,
ogi’ geh nya’a nang nabi Elia, ogi’ geh nya’a de’ nang Ingan nabi de’ bokon.”

pairs.source: And he saith unto them, But whom say ye that I am? And Peter answereth and saith unto him, Thou art the Christ.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus sikian tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’ lagi’, “Mo’-e nuna’ pikil
ingan osi odop-e Oku’ itih?”
Petrus mo’ nyawot-e, “Ingan leh Laja Pinyilamat de’ pait Topa’.”

pairs.source: And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sibaya tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E jaman tanon tudu’ osi sija’-e,
nang odop-E inoh leh Laja Pinyilamat.

pairs.source: And he began to teach them, that the Son of man must suffer many things, and be rejected of the elders, and [of] the chief priests, and scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ tanon tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E nang odop-E
Onak Manusia de’ halus idip susah jola’. Iyoh obuah netang oda’
pimipin-pimipin ulang Yahudi, pimipin-pimipin agama de’ ayuh, duoh
gulu-gulu agama. Odop-e de’ muti’ leh de’ oda’ nya’a ngabos Onak Manusia
inoh, pak-e takal mokua’ taluh onu Onak manusia pali’ mokat idip.

pairs.source: And he spake that saying openly. And Peter took him, and began to rebuke him.
pairs.target:
Yesus
mo’ telang-telang tanon sua’ oni’ de’ muno’ ya’ obuah odop-E. Pak-e Petrus
mo’ toban Yesus ke’ tuak tana’ yoh mo’ jaman nang sina de’ in inoh.

pairs.source: But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples, he rebuked Peter, saying, Get thee behind me, Satan: for thou savourest not the things that be of God, but the things that be of men.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ kos odop-e ninga’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E de’ bokon. Iyoh
mo’ ngalah Petrus daang-e in-e, “Buu mu’u Laja Muat munua! Mu’u di’ mu’
piduli oni’ de’ la’an Topa’, mu’u jok mu’ piduli oni’ de’ la’an manusia.”

pairs.source: And when he had called the people [unto him] with his disciples also, he said unto them, Whosoever will come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mogan pinuna’-pinuna’-E duoh nya’a de’ bogo’ de’ ogi’
dano’. Yoh mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Osi sija’-e de’ ya’ nuna’ Oku’,
iyoh halus lawan kila-e, siap idip jola’ koda’ Oku’, yohmo’ nah-nah nuna’
Oku’.

pairs.source: For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel’s, the same shall save it.
pairs.target:
Dop-e osi de’ ngibala’ asong-e iyoh di’-e so’on idip so’ Topa’. Pak-e
osi de’ tumut asong-e ngan-e nuna’ Oku’ duoh magah Gah de’ Paguh, iyoh
de’ so’on idip de’ so’ Topa’.

pairs.source: For what shall it profit a man, if he shall gain the whole world, and lose his own soul?
pairs.target:
Nai oni ingan kaku’ sua’ oni’ de’ ogi’ daang
dunia, pak-e di’ ingan so’on idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’.

pairs.source: Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?
pairs.target:
Dop-e doi’ oni’
de’ dunia itih de’ tapod ngan ingan ya’ milih idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’.

pairs.source: Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation; of him also shall the Son of man be ashamed, when he cometh in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
pairs.target:
Dop-e osi de’ dasa’ ngaku’ Oku’ duoh oni’ de’ ngajal ku’ de’ uun
manusia de’ suka nai dosa duoh di’-e taat tudu’ Topa’, Oku’, Onak Manusia
tuang dasa’ geh ngaku’ iyoh, takal Ku’ nog daang kuasa Sama’ Ku’ baya
ayua malaikat so’ Topa’.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Verily I say unto you, That there be some of them that stand here, which shall not taste of death, till they have seen the kingdom of God come with power.
pairs.target:
Yesus tanon lagi’ tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Oku’ tanon tudu’ ingan:
Ogi’ so’ ingan de’ muti’ de’ alua’ totap idip nog Topa’ bitanga odop-E
jadin Laja de’ punua’ kuasa-E.”

pairs.source: And after six days Jesus taketh [with him] Peter, and James, and John, and leadeth them up into an high mountain apart by themselves: and he was transfigured before them.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ nuam onu, Yesus toban Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes ma’ad
ke’ tun dolod de’ bigatung sa’-e juua’ so’ nya’a. Takal-e mo’ de’ tun dolod
Yesus mo’ bilubah jawa’ jowin-E.

pairs.source: And his raiment became shining, exceeding white as snow; so as no fuller on earth can white them.
pairs.target:
Pimakai-E mo’ jadin mopu’ bikilap. Doi’
nya’a de’ daang dunia itih de’ tapod mamia’ pimakai-e oda’ mopu’ mun
inoh.

pairs.source: And there appeared unto them Elias with Moses: and they were talking with Jesus.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ taluh mo’ ninga’ nabi Elia duoh nabi Musa sina duoh
Yesus.

pairs.source: And Peter answered and said to Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here: and let us make three tabernacles; one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias.
pairs.target:
Petrus mo’ sina tudu’ Yesus, “Gulu, tok-tok nyam doon-e ko’ih de’
topat itih neh. Oni wat-e mo’ ko’ih nai taluh galang, ni’ sa’an Ingan, ni’
sa’an Musa, ni’ sa’an Elia.”

pairs.source: For he wist not what to say; for they were sore afraid.
pairs.target:
Petrus nang sina de’ in inoh, iyoh di’-e pu’an
oni de’ ya’ nang-e, dop-e yoh sukup tolu-e.

pairs.source: And there was a cloud that overshadowed them: and a voice came out of the cloud, saying, This is my beloved Son: hear him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh abun mo’ muun de’ tun odop-e de’ muno’. Yoh mo’ ngojit
sina so’ aang abun inoh de’ in-e, “Itihleh Onak Ku’ de’ sukup Ku’ ngibala’,
ngojit leh oni’ de’ tanon-E.”

pairs.source: And suddenly, when they had looked round about, they saw no man any more, save Jesus only with themselves.
pairs.target:
Tang-tang takal odop-e de’ taluh kumiat kati’
kanih, doi’-e nak ogi’ osi-osi dano’, jok-e ogi’ Yesus sija’-e.

pairs.source: And as they came down from the mountain, he charged them that they should tell no man what things they had seen, till the Son of man were risen from the dead.
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ muun so’ tun dolod, Yesus sibaya tudu’ odop-e
de’ muno’ sa’-e di’-e silita duoh osi-osi-e oni’ de’ ninga’-e, nog Onak Manusia
pali’ idip lagi’.

pairs.source: And they kept that saying with themselves, questioning one with another what the rising from the dead should mean.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ taluh inoh mo’ nyikon sibaya inoh daang otin-e, pak-e
odop-e de’ taluh mulai kilakal oni loti oni’ de’ nang-E, “Pali’ idip lagi’.”

pairs.source: And they asked him, saying, Why say the scribes that Elias must first come?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ sikian tudu’ Yesus, “Oni nai gulu-gulu agama Yahudi
nang Elia ya’ dio’ nog?”

pairs.source: And he answered and told them, Elias verily cometh first, and restoreth all things; and how it is written of the Son of man, that he must suffer many things, and be set at nought.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Elia tok dio’ nog, nai sua’ oni’ oda’ pali’ paguh.
Pak-e oni nai-e ogi’ sina daang Kitab de’ nang Onak Manusia ya’ susah
jola’ duoh obuah nulak?

pairs.source: But I say unto you, That Elias is indeed come, and they have done unto him whatsoever they listed, as it is written of him.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Oku’ tanon tudu’ ingan: Elia mo’ bilasa
nog, nya’a mo’ adoh-adoh wat-e duoh-e samah koda’ daang Kitab.”

pairs.source: And when he came to [his] disciples, he saw a great multitude about them, and the scribes questioning with them.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus, Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes muun so’ dolod, odop-e
de’ muno’ mo’ ninga’ bogo’ nya’a ngubun pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus de’ bokon.
Ogi’ geh kudu-kudu na’an gulu agama Yahudi de’ bikalah duoh odop-e de’
muno’.

pairs.source: And straightway all the people, when they beheld him, were greatly amazed, and running to [him] saluted him.
pairs.target:
Takal nya’a de’ bogo’ inoh ninga’ Yesus yoh mo’ sukup nyam-e
ilan-e, yoh mo’ bikoduh odi nguma’-E.

pairs.source: And he asked the scribes, What question ye with them?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ bisikian tudu’ odop-e
de’ muno’, “Oni de’ bikalah ingan duoh odop-e de’ muno’?”

pairs.source: And one of the multitude answered and said, Master, I have brought unto thee my son, which hath a dumb spirit;
pairs.target:
Ogi’ ni’ na’an so’ uluk odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-E, “Gulu, oku’
toban onak ku’ tudu’ Ingan. Iyoh obuah nguasa muat munua de’ oda’ yoh   
bebe’.

pairs.source: And wheresoever he taketh him, he teareth him: and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away: and I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out; and they could not.
pairs.target:
Asal muat munua nyelang gonan-e, yoh mo’ paan-paan gonan-e
ke’ tana’, loyang-e bijulak luah so’ boba’-e, daang jipon-e obua’ bitatuak,
gonan-e mo’ nisuk. Oku’ mitia’ pinuna’-pinuna’ Ingan oda’ kasig muat
munua inoh, pak-e di’-e taan kasig-e.”

pairs.source: He answereth him, and saith, O faithless generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him unto me.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ingan de’ muti’ tok-tok di’
ingan bisaya’ tudu’ Topa’! Oni tian Ku’ ya’ lo’o duoh sabal tudu’ ingan?
Toban onak dali inoh kati’!”

pairs.source: And they brought him unto him: and when he saw him, straightway the spirit tare him; and he fell on the ground, and wallowed foaming.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ toban onak dali inoh
tudu’ Yesus. Takal muat munua inoh mo’ ninga’ Yesus, yoh mo’ lasu’ oda’
gonan onak dali inoh nisuk. Onak dali inoh mo’ lasu’ tumang bigulai-gulai
de’ tana’ daang loyang-e bijulak luah so’ boba’-e.

pairs.source: And he asked his father, How long is it ago since this came unto him? And he said, Of a child.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sikian tudu’
sama’ onak dali inoh, “Mo’ oni tian-e yoh obuah oni’ de’ wat itih?”
Sama’-e mo’ nyawot-e, “So’ iso’-e geh.

pairs.source: And ofttimes it hath cast him into the fire, and into the waters, to destroy him: but if thou canst do any thing, have compassion on us, and help us.
pairs.target:
Mo’ bogo’ sidoh-e muat munua
ya’ ngabos-e, oda’ tolan odop-e kaang opui, duoh oda’ tolan odop-e kaang
pi’in. Simo’ Ingan tapod oda’ onak dali itih mokua’, Ingan masi’ leh, duoh
Ingan tulung leh ko’ih.”

pairs.source: Jesus said unto him, If thou canst believe, all things [are] possible to him that believeth.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’-e, “Oni nai mu’ sina: ‘Simo’ Ingan tapod?’ Doi’
oni’ de’ di’-e tapod sa’an nya’a de’ bisaya’.”

pairs.source: And straightway the father of the child cried out, and said with tears, Lord, I believe; help thou mine unbelief.
pairs.target:
Sama’ onak dali inoh mo’ lasu’ nang sina-e dolas-dolas, “Oku’ bisaya’!
Pak-e alua’ kulang. Tulung leh oda’ oku’ bisaya’ lobih lagi’!”

pairs.source: When Jesus saw that the people came running together, he rebuked the foul spirit, saying unto him, [Thou] dumb and deaf spirit, I charge thee, come out of him, and enter no more into him.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ninga’ makin bogo’ nya’a de’ nog bikubun, Yesus mo’
nyingak muat munua inoh daang-E sina duoh-e, “Buu! Muat de’ oda’ nya’a
itih bongam duoh bebe’! Oku’ oda’ mu’u luah so’ onak dali itih duoh ma’
tiya’ pali’ nguasa onak dali itih!”

pairs.source: And [the spirit] cried, and rent him sore, and came out of him: and he was as one dead; insomuch that many said, He is dead.
pairs.target:
Muat munua inoh mo’ nang bogan-e, yoh mo’ oda’ sua’ gonan onak
dali inoh nisuk. Mokua’ inoh muat munua mo’ lasu’ buu luah so’ gonan
onak dali inoh. Onak dali inoh mo’ mun nya’a de’ mo’ kobos mun-e, iyoh
leh ngan nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ in-e, “Iyoh mo’ kobos.”

pairs.source: But Jesus took him by the hand, and lifted him up; and he arose.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’
kagian tongan-e, Yoh mo’ tulung oda’ mokat. Onak dali inoh mo’ lasu’
mokat.

pairs.source: And when he was come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, Why could not we cast him out?
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus mo’ daang boli, duam Yoh duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E, odop-e
de’ muno’ mo’ sikian, in-e, “Oni nai ko’ih di’ taan oda’ muat munua inoh
buu so’ onak dali inoh?”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, This kind can come forth by nothing, but by prayer and fasting.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Muat munua de’ basa inoh jok to’ tapod kasig
pakai bidoa.”

pairs.source: And they departed thence, and passed through Galilee; and he would not that any man should know [it].
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ buu togan topat inoh ngilusu’
Galilea. Yoh dolia’-e oda’ nya’a pu’an so’-e lo’o,

pairs.source: For he taught his disciples, and said unto them, The Son of man is delivered into the hands of men, and they shall kill him; and after that he is killed, he shall rise the third day.
pairs.target:
dop-e Yoh ya’ ngajal
pinuna’-pinuna’-E ja’-e. Yoh mo’ in-e, “Onak Manusia ya’ obuah nyelah
tudu’ ulang-ulang de’ ja’at, yoh mo’ ngabos-e, pak-e mokua’ taluh onu Yoh
pali’ mokat idip.”

pairs.source: But they understood not that saying, and were afraid to ask him.
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E di’-e ngiloti oni loti sina de’ nang Yesus inoh, pak-e
odop-e de’ muno’ tolu ya’ sikian-e.

pairs.source: And he came to Capernaum: and being in the house he asked them, What was it that ye disputed among yourselves by the way?
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ nog ke’ Kapernaum. Takal-e mo’
nog kaang boli, Yesus mo’ sikian tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, “Oni de’ kilakal
ingan daang olan ti’-e?”

pairs.source: But they held their peace: for by the way they had disputed among themselves, who [should be] the greatest.
pairs.target:
Pak-e sua’ odop-e de’ muno’ doi’ de’ nyawot, dop-e daang olan odop-e
de’ muno’ bikalah osi de’ paling ayuh so’ odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And he sat down, and called the twelve, and saith unto them, If any man desire to be first, [the same] shall be last of all, and servant of all.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’
gulu’, yohmo’ mogan so’ simoong duwoh pinuna’-E de’ sobot-E nang rasul.
Yoh mo’ in-e, “Nya’a de’ la’an jadin nomol ni’, yoh mesti jadin de’ paling
piobua’-e duoh jadin kuli nya’a de’ bogo’.”

pairs.source: And he took a child, and set him in the midst of them: and when he had taken him in his arms, he said unto them,
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ mit
onak opot de’ alua’ iso’, yohmo’ posan de’ uun odop-e de’ muno’, simadi-e
pakua’ onak opot inoh Yesus mo’ in-e,

pairs.source: Whosoever shall receive one of such children in my name, receiveth me: and whosoever shall receive me, receiveth not me, but him that sent me.
pairs.target:
“Osi sija’-e de’ nyamut onak opot
koda’ itih, ngan yoh bisaya’ tudu’ Oku’, samah geh iyoh tilima’ Oku’. Osi
de’ tilima’ Oku’, yoh tilima’ geh Topa’ de’ pait Oku’.”

pairs.source: And John answered him, saying, Master, we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and he followeth not us: and we forbad him, because he followeth not us.
pairs.target:
Yohanes mo’ in-e tudu’ Yesus, “Gulu, ko’ih ninga’ nya’a de’ di’-e nuna’ oto’ kasig muat munua pakai adon Ingan. Ko’ih mo’ jaman-e, dop-e yoh
di’-e nuna’ oto’.”

pairs.source: But Jesus said, Forbid him not: for there is no man which shall do a miracle in my name, that can lightly speak evil of me.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ in-e, “Ma’ ya’ jaman-e, dop-e ni’ na’an
tuang doi’ geh de’ tapod nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a pakai adon Oku’, mokua’
inoh yoh lasu’ pija’at adon Oku’.

pairs.source: For he that is not against us is on our part.
pairs.target: Osi de’ di’-e netang oto’, iyoh nua’ oto’.

pairs.source: For whosoever shall give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because ye belong to Christ, verily I say unto you, he shall not lose his reward.
pairs.target:
Oku’ tanon tudu’ ingan: Osi sija’-e de’ ngin nuak ni’ sakil pi’in tudu’
ingan, ngan ingan jadin pinuna’ Laja Pinyilamat, yoh totap so’on upah-e.”

pairs.source: And whosoever shall offend one of [these] little ones that believe in me, it is better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he were cast into the sea.
pairs.target:
Yesus lanyut sina-e, “Osi sija’-e de’ oda’ ni’ na’an onak opot di’-e tiya’
bisaya’ tudu’ Oku’, lobih paguh nye’ gutan batuh de’ ayuh de’ baat de’
tungua’-e, nye’ mo’ tolan kaang laut.

pairs.source: And if thy hand offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter into life maimed, than having two hands to go into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
pairs.target:
Simo’ tongan mu’ de’ oda’ mu’u
nai oni’ de’ ja’at, lobih paguh mu’ kopog-e! Dop-e lobih paguh doi’ tongan
mu’ ni’ kawa, pak-e idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’ de’ siluga. Nai oni ogi’ so’
duwoh tongan mu’, pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka de’ opui-e di’-e ponai
pula’?

pairs.source: Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target: De’ neraka olod-e di’-e ponai kobos, opui-e di’-e ponai pula’.

pairs.source: And if thy foot offend thee, cut it off: it is better for thee to enter halt into life, than having two feet to be cast into hell, into the fire that never shall be quenched:
pairs.target:
Simo’ po’on mu’ de’ oda’ mu’u nai oni’ de’ ja’at, lobih paguh mu’
kopog-e, dop-e lobih paguh mu’ bojang pak-e idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’.
Nai oni ogi’ so’ duwoh po’on mu’ pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka?

pairs.source: Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target:
De’
neraka olod-e di’-e ponai kobos, opui-e di’-e ponai pula’.

pairs.source: And if thine eye offend thee, pluck it out: it is better for thee to enter into the kingdom of God with one eye, than having two eyes to be cast into hell fire:
pairs.target:
Simo’ boton mu’ de’ oda’ mu’u nai oni’ de’ ja’at, tukiat kadi-e. Lobih
paguh mu’u molot ke’ siluga pakai boton ni’. Nai oni ogi’ so’ duwoh boton
mu’, pak-e obuah tolan kaang neraka?

pairs.source: Where their worm dieth not, and the fire is not quenched.
pairs.target:
De’ neraka olod-e di’-e ponai
kobos, opui-e di’-e ponai pula’.

pairs.source: For every one shall be salted with fire, and every sacrifice shall be salted with salt.
pairs.target:
Dop-e sua’ nya’a de’ nuna’ Topa’ ya’ obuah nguji pakai idip de’ susah
jola’, samah koda’ nya’a ngoon bongoh opui, samah geh koda’ dagin de’
modia’ nya’a pakai galua’.

pairs.source: Salt [is] good: but if the salt have lost his saltness, wherewith will ye season it? Have salt in yourselves, and have peace one with another.
pairs.target:
Galua’ inoh paguh, pak-e simo’-e doi’ sap
pidia’-e, oni wat nye’ oda’ pidia’ ba’uh? Oda’ leh idip ingan biguna sa’an
nya’a, duoh silalu idip bidamai duoh nya’a de’ bokon.”

pairs.source: And he arose from thence, and cometh into the coasts of Judaea by the farther side of Jordan: and the people resort unto him again; and, as he was wont, he taught them again.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ buu so’ kota Kapernaum, Iyoh mo’ odi
ke’ propinsi Yudea duoh motas polad sungi Yordan. Nya’a mo’
siuah-siuah nog tudu’-E. Iyoh mo’ ngajal nya’a de’ muno’ koda’ de’ silalu
Iyoh nai-e.

pairs.source: And the Pharisees came to him, and asked him, Is it lawful for a man to put away [his] wife? tempting him.
pairs.target:
Kudu-kudu na’an ulang Yahudi so’ uluk ulang Farisi nog ya’ suba
Yesus. Yoh mo’ sikian tudu’ Yesus in-e, “So’on yeh dali de’ mo’ kawin
posan sowon-e?”

pairs.source: And he answered and said unto them, What did Moses command you?
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus mo’ nyawot odop-e de’ muno’, “Oni in sibaya nabi Musa
no’uh-e tudu’ ingan?”

pairs.source: And they said, Moses suffered to write a bill of divorcement, and to put [her] away.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-e, “Musa nang so’on nya’a biposan,
asal-e nai sulat biposan-e tudu’ sowon-e.”

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said unto them, For the hardness of your heart he wrote you this precept.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Musa nai sibaya de’ in inoh dop-e ingan sikiya
kolas ya’ nai oni’ de’ la’an odop ingan.

pairs.source: But from the beginning of the creation God made them male and female.
pairs.target:
Pak-e sibungas-e Topa’ nai dunia
itih, ‘Iyoh mo’ nai ni’ dali duoh ni’ dayung.’

pairs.source: For this cause shall a man leave his father and mother, and cleave to his wife;
pairs.target:
‘Iyoh leh ngan-e dali de’
kawin togan sama’ sino’-e, iyoh mo’ tikuluk duoh sowon-e,

pairs.source: And they twain shall be one flesh: so then they are no more twain, but one flesh.
pairs.target:
odop-e de’
duwoh mo’ jadin ni’.’ Jadin, yoh di’-e tiya’ duwoh, pak-e ni’.

pairs.source: What therefore God hath joined together, let not man put asunder.
pairs.target:
Iyoh leh
ngan-e nya’a de’ mo’ nguluk Topa’, di’ so’on ya’ biposan.”

pairs.source: And in the house his disciples asked him again of the same [matter].
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ daang boli, pinuna’-pinuna’-E pali’ sikian
tentang nya’a de’ biposan.

pairs.source: And he saith unto them, Whosoever shall put away his wife, and marry another, committeth adultery against her.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Osi
sija’-e de’ posan sowon-e, yohmo’ kawin ba’uh duoh dayung de’ bokon,
iyoh biamai.

pairs.source: And if a woman shall put away her husband, and be married to another, she committeth adultery.
pairs.target:
Wat noh geh dayung de’ posan bonon-e, iyoh mo’ kawin
duoh dali de’ bokon, iyoh tuang biamai geh.”

pairs.source: And they brought young children to him, that he should touch them: and [his] disciples rebuked those that brought [them].
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh ogi’ kudu-kudu na’an nya’a toban onak opot-e tudu’
Yesus, sa’ Yesus toma’-e duoh blokat-e, pak-e pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus mo’
malah tudu’ nya’a de’ muno’.

pairs.source: But when Jesus saw [it], he was much displeased, and said unto them, Suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus ninga’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E malah
tudu’ nya’a de’ muno’, Yesus mo’ malah tudu’-e. Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Tanah sa’
onak opot de’ muno’ odi tudu’ Oku’. Dop-e nya’a de’ koda’ onak opot de’
muti’ leh de’ tilima’ Topa’ militah daang idip-e.

pairs.source: Verily I say unto you, Whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child, he shall not enter therein.
pairs.target:
Oku’ tanon tudu’ ingan:
Osi sija’-e de’ di’-e tilima’ pilitah Topa’ koda’ onak opot, iyoh di’-e tapod
jadin ayua umat Topa’.”

pairs.source: And he took them up in his arms, put [his] hands upon them, and blessed them.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ sina in inoh, Yesus mo’ pakua’ onak
opot de’ muno’ yohmo’ toma’ bak-e, daang-e blokat-e.

pairs.source: And when he was gone forth into the way, there came one running, and kneeled to him, and asked him, Good Master, what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus lanyut pimonu-E, ogi’ ni’ na’an dali odi tudu’ Yesus. Iyoh
gulu’ bikunyug yohmo’ in-e sikian tudu’ Yesus, “Gulu de’ paguh, oni de’
halus ku’ nai-e sa’ ku’ so’on idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’ takal ku’ mo’ kobos?”

pairs.source: And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? [there is] none good but one, [that is], God.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Oni nai mu’ nang Oku’ de’ paguh? Doi’ nya’a
de’ paguh, jok-e Topa’.

pairs.source: Thou knowest the commandments, Do not commit adultery, Do not kill, Do not steal, Do not bear false witness, Defraud not, Honour thy father and mother.
pairs.target:
Mu’u mo’ pu’an pilitah-pilitah Topa’: Ma’ ngabos nya’a, ma’ biamai,
ma’ noku, ma’ jadin tukang tanon de’ pibula’, ma’ ngakal-nipu nya’a,
pimodo leh duoh sama’ sino’ mu’.”

pairs.source: And he answered and said unto him, Master, all these have I observed from my youth.
pairs.target:
Dali inoh mo’ in-e, “Gulu, sua’ pilitah de’ muno’ mo’ nai ku’ so’ iso’
ku’ geh.”

pairs.source: Then Jesus beholding him loved him, and said unto him, One thing thou lackest: go thy way, sell whatsoever thou hast, and give to the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in heaven: and come, take up the cross, and follow me.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ninga’ nya’a inoh daang kila-E masi’ yohmo’ in-e, “Duam
ni’ de’ kulang de’ alua’ di’ mu’ nai-e. Odi jua sua’ halta mu’ nye’ mo’
bikutung duit-e duoh nya’a de’ botak. Mokua’ inoh mu’u mo’ ya’ so’on
halta de’ siluga. Mokua’ inoh pali’ kati’ nuna’ Oku’.”

pairs.source: And he was sad at that saying, and went away grieved: for he had great possessions.
pairs.target:
Takal-e ngojit sina
Yesus de’ in inoh, yoh mo’ nesal-e yohmo’ buu, dop-e iyoh bogo’ halta-e.

pairs.source: And Jesus looked round about, and saith unto his disciples, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ninga’ tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, Iyoh mo’ in-e tudu’-e,
“Susah manah nya’a de’ kaya ya’ jadin ayua umat Topa’.”

pairs.source: And the disciples were astonished at his words. But Jesus answereth again, and saith unto them, Children, how hard is it for them that trust in riches to enter into the kingdom of God!
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E ilan ngojit oni’ de’ nang-E. Pak-e Yesus mo’ in-e
lagi’, “Onak-onak Ku’, sukup susah-e nya’a ya’ jadin ayua umat Topa’.

pairs.source: It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
Sonang doo’ unta molot kaang lubang tuas so’ ulang de’ kaya ya’ jadin
ayua umat Topa’.”

pairs.source: And they were astonished out of measure, saying among themselves, Who then can be saved?
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E makin ilan-e, daang-e bisikian si odop-e, “Simo’-e
wat inoh osi de’ tapod silamat?”

pairs.source: And Jesus looking upon them saith, With men [it is] impossible, but not with God: for with God all things are possible.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ninga’ odop-e de’ muno’ daang-e in-e, “Manusia di’-e tapod
nyilamat odop-e, pak-e Topa’ tapod nyilamat manusia. Doi’ de’ di’ Topa’
tapod nai-e.”

pairs.source: Then Peter began to say unto him, Lo, we have left all, and have followed thee.
pairs.target:
Petrus mo’ in-e tudu’ Yesus, “Ko’ih mo’ togan sua’ oni’ ngan ko’ih
nuna’ Ingan.”

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said, Verily I say unto you, There is no man that hath left house, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my sake, and the gospel’s,
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Oku’ tanon tudu’ mu’u: Osi sija’-e de’ togan
boli-e, atou madih ayua-e, atou pingoma-e, atou onak-e, atou umoh-e
ngan-e nuna’ oku’ duoh magah Gah de’ Paguh,

pairs.source: But he shall receive an hundredfold now in this time, houses, and brethren, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and lands, with persecutions; and in the world to come eternal life.
pairs.target:
daang idip-e de’ dunia
itih geh yoh ya’ so’on silatus sidoh bogo’ boli-e, madih ayua-e, pingoma-e,
onak-e duoh umoh-e, duoh susah jola’ tuang ogi’ geh. Pak-e tia’ ijo’ de’
Dunia de’ Ba’uh, iyoh ya’ so’on idip de’ ba’uh duoh Topa’.

pairs.source: But many [that are] first shall be last; and the last first.
pairs.target:
Pak-e bogo’
nya’a de’ dio’ adin ya’ ponai sunih, nya’a de’ sunih adin ya’ ponai dio’.”

pairs.source: And they were in the way going up to Jerusalem; and Jesus went before them: and they were amazed; and as they followed, they were afraid. And he took again the twelve, and began to tell them what things should happen unto him,
pairs.target:
Daang pimonu Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E nuju Yerusalem, Yesus
ponu dio’ nua’ jowin. Sua’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E bigaduh duoh nya’a de’ bokon
de’ suwa’ de’ nuna’ dug-e tuang tolu geh. Mokua’ inoh, Yesus ngija’ lagi’
so’ simoong duwoh na’an pinuna’-E oda’ odi okon so’-o, sa’-e di’-e sinok  nya’a de’ bokon. Yesus mo’ tanon tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’ oni wat nya’a
ya’ duoh odop-E.

pairs.source: [Saying], Behold, we go up to Jerusalem; and the Son of man shall be delivered unto the chief priests, and unto the scribes; and they shall condemn him to death, and shall deliver him to the Gentiles:
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ in-e, “Oto’ ya’ odi ke’ Yerusalem, danih nya’a ya’ nyelah
Oku’ Onak Manusia tudu’ pimipin-pimipin agama de’ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu
agama Yahudi. Yoh mo’ ya’ ngukum ngabos Oku’. Odop-e de’ muno’ ya’
ngin tudu’ ulang de’ di’-e ulang Yahudi.

pairs.source: And they shall mock him, and shall scourge him, and shall spit upon him, and shall kill him: and the third day he shall rise again.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ muno’ ya’ ngine Oku’,
yoh ya’ nguja’, pijola’, duoh ngabos Oku’. Pak-e mokua’ taluh onu Oku’
ya’ pali’ idip.”

pairs.source: And James and John, the sons of Zebedee, come unto him, saying, Master, we would that thou shouldest do for us whatsoever we shall desire.
pairs.target:
Yakobus duoh Yohanes, onak-onak Zebedeus mo’ odi sinok Yesus.
Yoh mo’ in-e, “Gulu, ogi’ oni’ de’ mitia’ ko’ih tudu’ Ingan, oda’ Ingan nai-e.”

pairs.source: And he said unto them, What would ye that I should do for you?
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Oni de’ mitia’ ingan oda’ Oku’ nai-e?”

pairs.source: They said unto him, Grant unto us that we may sit, one on thy right hand, and the other on thy left hand, in thy glory.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ nyawot-e, “Takal Ingan militah jadin Laja de’ ayuh oda’ leh
ko’ih gulu’, ni’ na’an nua’ to’uh, ni’ na’an nua’ boit Ingan.”

pairs.source: But Jesus said unto them, Ye know not what ye ask: can ye drink of the cup that I drink of? and be baptized with the baptism that I am baptized with?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Ingan di’ ingan ngiloti oni’ de’ mitia’ ingan.
Podo ingan mo’ siap tilima’ susah jola’ koda’ de’ ya’ obuah Oku’? Podo
ingan taan ya’ obuah pijola’ koda’ de’ ya’ obuah Oku’?”

pairs.source: And they said unto him, We can. And Jesus said unto them, Ye shall indeed drink of the cup that I drink of; and with the baptism that I am baptized withal shall ye be baptized:
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ duwoh mo’ nyawot lagi’, “Ko’ih taan.”
Yesus mo’ in-e lagi’, “Tok ingan ya’ ki’an susah jola’ duoh obuah pijola’
samah koda’ de’ ya’ obuah Oku’.

pairs.source: But to sit on my right hand and on my left hand is not mine to give; but [it shall be given to them] for whom it is prepared.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Oku’ doi’ hak Ku’, ya’ notap osi
de’ gulu’ nua’ to’uh duoh osi de’ nua’ boit Ku’. Inoh Topa’ sidia sa’an nya’a
de’ mo’ nyok-E.”

pairs.source: And when the ten heard [it], they began to be much displeased with James and John.
pairs.target:
Takal simoong pinuna’-E de’ bokon ngojit oni’ de’ mitia’ odop-e de’
duwoh, yoh mo’ malah tudu’-e.

pairs.source: But Jesus called them [to him], and saith unto them, Ye know that they which are accounted to rule over the Gentiles exercise lordship over them; and their great ones exercise authority upon them.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ mogan sua’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E yohmo’ in-e,
“Pimipin-pimipin dunia militah layat-e pakai paksa duoh pijola’.

pairs.source: But so shall it not be among you: but whosoever will be great among you, shall be your minister:
pairs.target:
Pak-e
ingan di’ so’on wat inoh! Osi de’ ya’ jadin pimipin de’ so’ ingan, iyoh halus
jadin pilayan.

pairs.source: And whosoever of you will be the chiefest, shall be servant of all.
pairs.target:
Duoh osi de’ ya’ jadin ulang timogah, iyoh sidia jadin kuli
sa’an nya’a de’ bokon.

pairs.source: For even the Son of man came not to be ministered unto, but to minister, and to give his life a ransom for many.
pairs.target:
Dop-e Onak Manusia nog idoh di’-e oda’ nya’a
layan odop-E, pak-e Yoh ya’ layan duoh ngin asong-E ngan-e nyilamat
nya’a de’ bogo’.”

pairs.source: And they came to Jericho: and as he went out of Jericho with his disciples and a great number of people, blind Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, sat by the highway side begging.
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh sua’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ nog ke’ Kota Yerikho. Takal
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E buu luah so’ Kota inoh, nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’
siuah-siuah nuna’-E. Ogi’ nya’a de’ buta’ de’ tukang mitia’-mitia’ de’ gulu’
de’ bingon olan de’ adon Bartimeus onak Timeus.

pairs.source: And when he heard that it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out, and say, Jesus, [thou] Son of David, have mercy on me.
pairs.target:
Takal Bartimeus mo’ ngojit nang Yesus de’ so’ Nazaret ponu ngilusu’
odop-e, iyoh mo’ nang bogan-e mitia’ masi’, “Yesus onak sukun Laja Daud!
Masi’ leh tudu’ oku’!”

pairs.source: And many charged him that he should hold his peace: but he cried the more a great deal, [Thou] Son of David, have mercy on me.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ bogo’ mo’ malah da’-a daang-e oda’ yoh lo’o, pak-e yoh
makin dolas nang bogan-e, “Yesus onak sukun Laja Daud! Masi’ leh tudu’
oku’!”

pairs.source: And Jesus stood still, and commanded him to be called. And they call the blind man, saying unto him, Be of good comfort, rise; he calleth thee.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ lo’o daang-e sina, “Mogan oda’ iyoh odi kati’!” Odop-e de’
muno’ mo’ mogan nya’a de’ buta’ inoh simadi-e sina tudu’-e, “Notod negeh
kila mu’, mokat likas-e, Yesus mogan mu’u!”

pairs.source: And he, casting away his garment, rose, and came to Jesus.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ buta’ inoh mo’ lasu’ buka’ jubah-e, iyoh mo’ lasu’ mujuag,
iyoh mo’ odi tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said unto him, What wilt thou that I should do unto thee? The blind man said unto him, Lord, that I might receive my sight.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sikian tudu’-e, “Oni de’ mitia’ ingan oda’ Oku’ nai-e?”
Nya’a de’ buta’ inoh mo’ nyawot-e, “Gulu, oku’ mitia’ oda’ boton ku’ ponai
ninga’!”

pairs.source: And Jesus said unto him, Go thy way; thy faith hath made thee whole. And immediately he received his sight, and followed Jesus in the way.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sina tudu’-e, “Dop-e mu’u bisaya’, mu’u mokua’.Pali’
leh.” Takal inoh geh yoh lasu’ ponai ninga’. Yoh mo’ nuna’ Yesus daang
pimonu’-E.

pairs.source: And when they came nigh to Jerusalem, unto Bethphage and Bethany, at the mount of Olives, he sendeth forth two of his disciples,
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ ya’ nog Yerusalem, odop-e
de’ muno’ nog ke’ kupua’ Betfage duoh kupua’ Betania. So’ duoh
kupua’ inoh ogi’ de’ tilipang Pungu’ Zaitun. Takal-e dano’, Yesus oda’
duwoh na’an pinuna’-E ponu dio’.

pairs.source: And saith unto them, Go your way into the village over against you: and as soon as ye be entered into it, ye shall find a colt tied, whereon never man sat; loose him, and bring [him].
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ sibaya tudu’-e in-E, “Odi leh
ke’ kupua’ de’ ogi’ de’ nua’ jowin to’ inoh. Takal mu’ molot kano’, mu’u
ninga’ ogi’ ni’ polong keledai de’ alua’ muda’ de’ obuah mokos, de’ alua’
doi’ nya’a muat da’-e. Nye’ mo’ nukas-e, nye’ mo’ toban kati’.

pairs.source: And if any man say unto you, Why do ye this? say ye that the Lord hath need of him; and straightway he will send him hither.
pairs.target:
Simo’-e
ogi’ nya’a sikian-e, oni nai mu’ mit keledai inoh? Nye’ tanon tudu’-e, ‘Gulu
pilelu keledai itih, mokua’ inoh Iyoh ya’ lasu’ pali’-e.’ ”

pairs.source: And they went their way, and found the colt tied by the door without in a place where two ways met; and they loose him.
pairs.target:
So’ duwoh pinuna’-e mo’ odi. Yoh mo’ tapod ogi’ ni’ polong onak
keledai de’ mokos nya’a de’ jowin boli-e sinok olan. Odop-e de’ duwoh  mo’ nukas tolin-e.

pairs.source: And certain of them that stood there said unto them, What do ye, loosing the colt?
pairs.target:
Kudu-kudu na’an nya’a de’ mujuag sinok topat inoh
mo’ sikian-e, “Oni nai ingan nukas keledai inoh neh?”

pairs.source: And they said unto them even as Jesus had commanded: and they let them go.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ duwoh mo’ nyawot nuna’ de’ tanon Yesus tudu’-e, yohmo’
nya’a dano’ mo’ tanah oda’ iyoh toban-e.

pairs.source: And they brought the colt to Jesus, and cast their garments on him; and he sat upon him.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’ toban keledai inoh
tudu’ Yesus. Iyoh mo’ nopas tun dug keledai inoh pakai jubah-e. Yesus mo’
nyikoh gulu’ de’ tun-e.

pairs.source: And many spread their garments in the way: and others cut down branches off the trees, and strawed [them] in the way.
pairs.target:
Bogo’ nya’a de’ nopas olan de’ ya’ ngilusu’ Yesus
pakai jubah-e. Ogi’ geh nya’a de’ nopas olan pakai dowon-dowon koyuh
de’ mit-e so’ kobon-e.

pairs.source: And they that went before, and they that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna; Blessed [is] he that cometh in the name of the Lord:
pairs.target:
Ayua de’ nuna’ Yesus de’ nua’ jowin duoh nya’a
de’ nuna’ nua’ dug-e mo’ nang boba’-e,
“Mudi Topa’ de’ siluga! Obuah bilokat Iyoh de’ nog daang adon Topa’!

pairs.source: Blessed [be] the kingdom of our father David, that cometh in the name of the Lord: Hosanna in the highest.
pairs.target:
Obuah bilokat leh Onak sukun Laja Daud itih, de’ ya’ militah oto’ oda’
paguh! Mudi leh Topa’ oto’ de’ siluga!”

pairs.source: And Jesus entered into Jerusalem, and into the temple: and when he had looked round about upon all things, and now the eventide was come, he went out unto Bethany with the twelve.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus nog ke’ Yerusalem, Iyoh mo’ molot ke’ awah Boli Topa’.
Iyoh ninga’ sua’ oni’ de’ ogi’ de’ awah Boli Topa’ inoh, dop-e onu mo’ ya’
ngalom Iyoh duoh pinuna’-E de’ simoong duwoh na’an mo’ odi ke’ kupua’
Betania.

pairs.source: And on the morrow, when they were come from Bethany, he was hungry:
pairs.target:
Onu tia’ pagi-e, takal Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E buu so’ Betania
odi ke’ Yerusalem, Yesus noman to’in-e pilai.

pairs.source: And seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came, if haply he might find any thing thereon: and when he came to it, he found nothing but leaves; for the time of figs was not [yet].
pairs.target:
So’ juua’ Iyoh mo’ ninga’
tongon ara de’ bidonom dowon-e. Iyoh mo’ odi ke’ pu’un-e, podo-podo-e ogi’
bua’-e. Pak-e takal Yesus mo’ nog libua’-e Iyoh mo’ ninga’ jok-e ogi’ dowon-e
sija’-e, dop-e alua’ di’-e musim tongon ara inoh bibua’.

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said unto it, No man eat fruit of thee hereafter for ever. And his disciples heard [it].
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E
mo’ ngojit Yesus sina in-e tudu’ tongon ara inoh, “Mulai so’ adin doi’ tiya’
nya’a ya’ man bua’ so’ tongon mu’!”

pairs.source: And they come to Jerusalem: and Jesus went into the temple, and began to cast out them that sold and bought in the temple, and overthrew the tables of the moneychangers, and the seats of them that sold doves;
pairs.target:
Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ nog ke’ Yerusalem. Iyoh mo’ molot
ke’ awah Boli Topa’, Iyoh mo’ kasig nya’a de’ bijua dano’. Yesus mo’
ngibolui mija topat nya’a nukal duit duoh mija topat nya’a jua manuk
asang.

pairs.source: And would not suffer that any man should carry [any] vessel through the temple.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ jaman osi sija’-e di’ so’on toban balang de’ ya’ jua-e
ngilusu’ awah boli Topa’.

pairs.source: And he taught, saying unto them, Is it not written, My house shall be called of all nations the house of prayer? but ye have made it a den of thieves.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ ngajal nya’a dano’
in-e, “Ogi’ de’ obuah nulis daang Kitab de’ in-e, ‘Boli ku’ nya’a sobot nang

pairs.source: And the scribes and chief priests heard [it], and sought how they might destroy him: for they feared him, because all the people was astonished at his doctrine.
pairs.target:
Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi
mo’ ngojit sina Yesus inoh, yoh mo’ kalik olan ngan-e ya’ ngabos Yesus.
Pak-e yoh tolu tudu’ Yesus dop-e bogo’ nya’a de’ sonang duoh oni’ de’
ngajal Yesus.

pairs.source: And when even was come, he went out of the city.
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ya’ ngalom Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E buu so’ kota
inoh.

pairs.source: And in the morning, as they passed by, they saw the fig tree dried up from the roots.
pairs.target:
Tia’ pagi-e takal Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E ponu ngilusu’ tongon
ara inoh, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ ninga’ tongon ara inoh mo’ kobos pisok
nog aat-e.

pairs.source: And Peter calling to remembrance saith unto him, Master, behold, the fig tree which thou cursedst is withered away.
pairs.target:
Petrus mo’ natong oni’ de’ nai Yesus sumia-e yoh mo’ in-e,
“Gulu, ninga’ mey tongon ara de’ obuah nyupah Ingan sumia-e mo’ pisok.”

pairs.source: And Jesus answering saith unto them, Have faith in God.
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Bisaya’ negeh tudu’ Topa’!

pairs.source: For verily I say unto you, That whosoever shall say unto this mountain, Be thou removed, and be thou cast into the sea; and shall not doubt in his heart, but shall believe that those things which he saith shall come to pass; he shall have whatsoever he saith.
pairs.target:
Oku’ tanon tudu’
ingan: Osi sija’-e de’ sina tudu’ dolod itih, ‘Bilalih leh duoh obuah tolan
kaang laut,’ sua’ oni’ de’ nang ingan inoh ya’ jadi, asal ingan di’ ingan
bigaduh duoh totap bisaya’ nang oni’ de’ muno’ bonal-bonal jadi.

pairs.source: Therefore I say unto you, What things soever ye desire, when ye pray, believe that ye receive [them], and ye shall have [them].
pairs.target:
Yoh
ngan Ku’ tanon tudu’ ingan: Oni sija’-e de’ mitia’ mu’ daang doa mu’,
bisaya’ negeh nang mu’u mo’ so’on-e, mu’u pasti ya’ so’on-e.

pairs.source: And when ye stand praying, forgive, if ye have ought against any: that your Father also which is in heaven may forgive you your trespasses.
pairs.target:
Sinia’ sija’-e
takal mu’u bidoa, simo’ mu’ natong mu’u ogi’ monam otin tudu’ nya’a de’
bokon, mu’u halus ngapun dio’ salah-e, sa’ Sama’ mu’ de’ siluga ngapun-E
geh mu’u.

pairs.source: But if ye do not forgive, neither will your Father which is in heaven forgive your trespasses.
pairs.target:
Pak-e simo’ mu’ di’ ngapun salah nya’a de’ bokon, Sama’ mu’
de’ siluga tuang dolia’-e geh ngapun dosa mu’.”

pairs.source: And they come again to Jerusalem: and as he was walking in the temple, there come to him the chief priests, and the scribes, and the elders,
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ odi lagi’ ke’ Yerusalem. Takal Yesus ponu-ponu de’ limang Boli Topa’, pimipin-pimipin agama duoh gulu-gulu agama ulang
Yahudi duoh pimipin-pimipin ulang Yahudi de’ bokon bitapod duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: And say unto him, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority to do these things?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sikian tudu’ Yesus, “Osi de’ oda’ Mu’u nai oni’
de’ muti’? Osi de’ ngin tugas tudu’ Mu’u nai sua’ oni’ de’ muti’?”

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said unto them, I will also ask of you one question, and answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.
pairs.target:
Yesus
mo’ nyawot-e, “Oku’ tuang ya’ sikian geh tudu’ ingan. Simo’ ingan tapod
nyawot, Oku’ tuang tanon Ku’ geh osi de’ oda’ Oku’ nai sua’ oni’ de’ muti’.

pairs.source: The baptism of John, was [it] from heaven, or of men? answer me.
pairs.target: Osi de’ oda’ Yohanes Pembaptis baptis nya’a? Manusia keh Topa’?”

pairs.source: And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say, From heaven; he will say, Why then did ye not believe him?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ biloneng si odop-e, “Mo’ to’ nang ‘Topa’ de’
oda’’, Iyoh pasti nang ‘Oni nai di’ mu’ bisaya’ tudu’ Yohanes?’

pairs.source: But if we shall say, Of men; they feared the people: for all [men] counted John, that he was a prophet indeed.
pairs.target:
Pak-e
idoh geh di’ oto’ ponai nang ‘Manusia de’ oda’.’ ” Odop-e de’ muno’ nang
in inoh saai yoh tolu de’ nya’a de’ bogo’ ya’ malah tudu’ odop-e, dop-e
sua’ nya’a bisaya’ nang Yohanes inoh nabi.

pairs.source: And they answered and said unto Jesus, We cannot tell. And Jesus answering saith unto them, Neither do I tell you by what authority I do these things.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-E, “Ko’ih di’ ko’ih pu’an-e.”
Yesus mo’ nyawot in-e, “Oku’ tuang idoh geh di’ ku’ tanon osi Nya’a
de’ oda’ Oku’ nai sua’ oni’ de’ muno’.”

pairs.source: And he began to speak unto them by parables. A [certain] man planted a vineyard, and set an hedge about [it], and digged [a place for] the winefat, and built a tower, and let it out to husbandmen, and went into a far country.
pairs.target:
Yesus mulai sina tudu’ pimipin-pimipin agama de’ ayuh, gulu-gulu
agama, duoh pimipin-pimipin Yahudi de’ bokon pakai nang silita,
in-e, “Ogi’ nya’a nai kobon anggul, yoh mo’ ngijuam-e, mokua’ inoh yoh
mo’ nai lubang topat nya’a misiat pi’in bua’ anggul. Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’
nai pangal topat nya’a jaga kobon, yoh mo’ oda’ nya’a nyewa kobon-e,
odop-e mo’ buu ke’ negeli de’ bokon.

pairs.source: And at the season he sent to the husbandmen a servant, that he might receive from the husbandmen of the fruit of the vineyard.
pairs.target:
Takal-e nog musim ngutuam bua’
anggul, nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh mo’ pait kuli-e oda’ odi mit duman
so’ nya’a de’ nyewa kobon-e.

pairs.source: And they caught [him], and beat him, and sent [him] away empty.
pairs.target:
Pak-e nya’a de’ nyewa kobon inoh mo’
takap kuli de’ pait nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon. Yoh mo’ bipupu’ duoh-e, yohmo’
oda’ pali’ boloh.

pairs.source: And again he sent unto them another servant; and at him they cast stones, and wounded [him] in the head, and sent [him] away shamefully handled.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh mo’ pait kuli-e de’ bokon,
pak-e odop-e de’ muno’ mupu’ bak-e yohmo’ kasig oda’ buu, daang-e
maki’-muta’-e.

pairs.source: And again he sent another; and him they killed, and many others; beating some, and killing some.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh mo’ pait kuli-e de’ bokon,
pak-e odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ ngabos-e. Watnoh geh yoh duoh kuli-e de’
bogo’ de’ pait-e de’ bokon. Ogi’ de’ mupu’-e, ogi’ geh de’ ngabos-e.

pairs.source: Having yet therefore one son, his wellbeloved, he sent him also last unto them, saying, They will reverence my son.
pairs.target:
Adin
mo’ doi’ tiya’ nya’a de’ bokon de’ ya’ pait nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh,
duam onak odop-e de’ ngibala’-e ja’-e. Yoh mo’ in-e daang pikil-e, ‘Paguh
oku’ oda’ onak odop ku’ de’ odi, sa’-e pimodo da’-e.’

pairs.source: But those husbandmen said among themselves, This is the heir; come, let us kill him, and the inheritance shall be ours.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal nya’a de’
nyewa kobon ninga’ onak nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh nog, yoh mo’ sina
tipan odop-e, in-e, ‘Ninga’ onak nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon itih! Iyoh leh de’
ya’ kaku’ sua’ kobon itih, takal sama’-e kobos. Ja’ to’ ngabos-e sa’ oto’ de’
kaku’ kobon itih.’

pairs.source: And they took him, and killed [him], and cast [him] out of the vineyard.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ takap duoh ngabos onak nya’a
de’ kaku’ kobon inoh, yoh mo’ tolan todang-e ke’ sopa’ kobon.”

pairs.source: What shall therefore the lord of the vineyard do? he will come and destroy the husbandmen, and will give the vineyard unto others.
pairs.target:
Yesus mokua’ silita, yohmo’ sikian tudu’ nya’a de’ muno’, “Oni wat
oni’ de’ ya’ nai nya’a de’ kaku’ kobon inoh? Pasti odop-e sadi’-e de’ ya’ nog   
ngabos nya’a de’ nyewa kobon-e inoh. Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ oda’ nya’a
de’ bokon de’ nyewa.

pairs.source: And have ye not read this scripture; The stone which the builders rejected is become the head of the corner:
pairs.target:
Pasti mo’ ogi’ ingan basa daang Kitab de’ in-e,
‘Batuh de’ tolan tukang boli,
mo’ jadin batuh de’ sukup biguna-e.

pairs.source: This was the Lord’s doing, and it is marvellous in our eyes?
pairs.target:
Itih leh oni’ de’ nai Topa’,
de’ sukup oto’ ilan-e.’ ”

pairs.source: And they sought to lay hold on him, but feared the people: for they knew that he had spoken the parable against them: and they left him, and went their way.
pairs.target:
Ayua pimipin Yahudi de’ ngojit silita inoh mo’ kaga’ odop-e ya’ takap
Yesus, dop-e silita de’ nang Yesus inoh nados odop-e de’ muno’. Pak-e
odop-e de’ muno’ tolu tudu’ nya’a' de’ bogo’, inoh leh ngan odop-e de’
muno’ mo’ buu togan Yesus.

pairs.source: And they send unto him certain of the Pharisees and of the Herodians, to catch him in [his] words.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh ayua pimipin Yahudi mo’ oda’ kudu-kudu na’an so’ uluk
ulang Farisi duoh nya’a de’ nua’ Laja Herodes odi tudu’ Yesus ngan-e oda’
Yesus ya’ nang sina de’ di’-e bonal, sa’ odop-e de’ muno’ dapod nyalah
Yesus.

pairs.source: And when they were come, they say unto him, Master, we know that thou art true, and carest for no man: for thou regardest not the person of men, but teachest the way of God in truth: Is it lawful to give tribute to Caesar, or not?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nog tudu’ Yesus, yohmo’ in-e, “Gulu, ko’ih
pu’an nang Ingan tanon oni’ de’ bonal duoh di’ Ingan piduli oni in sina
nya’a de’ bokon. Ingan di’ Ingan tolu, bait tudu’ nya’a de’ timogah, bait
tudu’ nya’a de’ di’-e timogah, pak-e Ingan suang-suang in Ingan ngajal wat
ki wat manusia idip nuna’ de’ la’an Topa’. Adin, suba tanon tudu’ ko’ih,
mo’-e nuna’ atulan agama oto’, so’on kedoh keh oto’ bayal suke tudu’ Laja
Roma de’ paling ayuh? Halus keh idoh oto’ bayal-e?”

pairs.source: Shall we give, or shall we not give? But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said unto them, Why tempt ye me? bring me a penny, that I may see [it].
pairs.target:
Yesus pu’an nang odop-e de’ muno’ pula’-pula’ paguh. Iyoh mo’
nyawot-e, “Oni nai ingan siaji ingan oda’ Oku’ ya’ nang sina de’ di’-e
bonal? Suba bitanga tudu’ Oku’ ni’ kiping duit pilak!”

pairs.source: And they brought [it]. And he saith unto them, Whose [is] this image and superscription? And they said unto him, Caesar’s.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ ngin tudu’-E. Yesus mo’ sikian in-E, “Gamal
duoh adon osi de’ ogi’ dati’?” Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ nyawot-e, “Gamal
duoh adon Laja Roma de’ paling ayuh.”

pairs.source: And Jesus answering said unto them, Render to Caesar the things that are Caesar’s, and to God the things that are God’s. And they marvelled at him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e, “Mo’-e wat inoh, oni de’ kaku’ laja, ngin tudu’ laja.
Oni de’ kaku’ Topa’, ngin tudu’ Topa’!” Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sukup ilan-e.

pairs.source: Then come unto him the Sadducees, which say there is no resurrection; and they asked him, saying,
pairs.target:
Uluk ulang Saduki iyoh leh uluk ulang de’ di’-e bisaya’ nang nya’a de’
kobos tapod pali’ idip. Ogi’ kudu-kudu na’an nya’a so’ odop-e de’ muno’  de’ nog tudu’ Yesus.Yoh bisikian tudu’ Yesus, in-e,

pairs.source: Master, Moses wrote unto us, If a man’s brother die, and leave [his] wife [behind him], and leave no children, that his brother should take his wife, and raise up seed unto his brother.
pairs.target:
“Gulu, Musa nulis
atulan itih sa’an oto’: ‘Simo’-e ogi’ dali de’ mo’ kawin, yoh mo’ kobos, pak-e
yoh doi’ onak-e, yohmo’ madih-e de’ dali de’ bokon mit bokas sowon-e,
oda’ jadin sowon odop-e, sa’-e ogi’ onak sa’an bonon-e de’ mo’ kobos.’

pairs.source: Now there were seven brethren: and the first took a wife, and dying left no seed.
pairs.target:
De’ dio’, ogi’ nya’a de’ sikia’-sudi’ ju’ madih odop-e de’ dali. Madih-e de’
pinuan kawin, yoh mo’ dio’ kobos ngan-e alua’ doi’ onak-e.

pairs.source: And the second took her, and died, neither left he any seed: and the third likewise.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh
madih-e de’ ke’ duwoh-e mit bokas sowon-e inoh oda’ jadin sowon-e, yoh
tuang dio’ kobos geh ngan-e alua’ doi’ onak-e. Wat noh geh, madih-e de’ ke’
taluh-e,

pairs.source: And the seven had her, and left no seed: last of all the woman died also.
pairs.target:
telus nog madih-e de’ ke' ju’-e, wat inoh geh yoh kobos ngan-e
alua’ doi’ onak-e. Mokua’ inoh dayung inoh tuang kobos geh.

pairs.source: In the resurrection therefore, when they shall rise, whose wife shall she be of them? for the seven had her to wife.
pairs.target:
Takal sua’
nya’a de’ mo’ kobos pali’ idip, dayung inoh jadin sowon osi? Dop-e so’ ju’
madih odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ kawin duoh-e.”

pairs.source: And Jesus answering said unto them, Do ye not therefore err, because ye know not the scriptures, neither the power of God?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot odop-e de’ muno’ in-e, “Pikil ingan mo’ salah.
Ingan di’ ingan pu’an Kitab duoh kuasa Topa’.

pairs.source: For when they shall rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage; but are as the angels which are in heaven.
pairs.target:
Dop-e takal nya’a de’ mo’
kobos mokat pali’ idip, doi’ tiya’ nya’a ya’ kawin, sua’ nya’a idip koda’
malaikat de’ siluga.

pairs.source: And as touching the dead, that they rise: have ye not read in the book of Moses, how in the bush God spake unto him, saying, I [am] the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob?
pairs.target:
Tentang nya’a de’ mo’ kobos mokat pali’ idip, podo
doi’ sidoh ingan basa daang buk de’ nulis nabi Musa, takal Topa’ bitanga
odop-E tudu’ Musa so’ tota’ loja’ de’ bidudu’ opui da’-e? Topa’ in-e, ‘Oku’
leh Topa’ de’ obuah nyomah oda’ Abraham, Ishak duoh Yakub,’

pairs.source: He is not the God of the dead, but the God of the living: ye therefore do greatly err.
pairs.target:
Iyoh
idoh di’-e Topa’ de’ obuah nyomah oda’ nya’a de’ kobos, pak-e Iyoh Topa’
de’ obuah nyomah oda’ nya’a de’ idip. Ingan di’ ingan ngiloti-e!”

pairs.source: And one of the scribes came, and having heard them reasoning together, and perceiving that he had answered them well, asked him, Which is the first commandment of all?
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus alua’ bikalah duoh uluk ulang Saduki, ogi’ ni’ na’an
gulu agama Yahudi suwa’ ngojit-e. Yoh ninga’ Yesus nyawot oni de’ sikian
odop-e de’ muno’ sukup bonal-e. Gulu agama Yahudi inoh mo’ sikian tudu’
Yesus in-e, “Ki pilitah de’ paling penting so’ susua’ pilitah so’ Topa’?”

pairs.source: And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments [is], Hear, O Israel; The Lord our God is one Lord:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Pilitah de’ paling penting ke’ ni’-e iyoh leh:
‘Ngojit leh ingan oi ulang Israel! Topa’ oto’ jok-e ni’.

pairs.source: And thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy heart, and with all thy soul, and with all thy mind, and with all thy strength: this [is] the first commandment.
pairs.target:
Ngibala’ leh Topa’
daang sua’ otin mu’, sua’ asong mu’, sua’ pikil-kila mu’, duoh sua’ tenaga
mu’.’

pairs.source: And the second [is] like, [namely] this, Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself. There is none other commandment greater than these.
pairs.target:
Pilitah de’ ke’ duwoh-e iyoh leh: ‘Ngibala’ leh siodop mu’ manusia,
samah koda’ mu’u ngibala’ odop mu’. Doi’ pilitah de’ bokon de’ paling
penting so’ pilitah de’ duwoh itih.’ ”

pairs.source: And the scribe said unto him, Well, Master, thou hast said the truth: for there is one God; and there is none other but he:
pairs.target:
Gulu agama Yahudi inoh mo’ sina tudu’ Yesus, “Bonal manah oni’ de’
nang Ingan, pak Gulu-e! Iyoh jok-e ni’, doi’ Topa’ de’ bokon.

pairs.source: And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love [his] neighbour as himself, is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.
pairs.target:
Manusia
halus ngibala’ Topa’ daang sua’ otin-e, pakai sua’ pikil kila-e, duoh sua’   
tenaga-e, duoh halus ngibala’ si odop-e manusia, samah koda’ iyoh ngibala’
odop-e sadi’-e. Itih lobih paguh so’ binatang de’ ngabos nye’ ngan nye’
nyomah Topa’, duoh de’ bokon-bokon-e de’ ngin nye’ tudu’ Topa’.”

pairs.source: And when Jesus saw that he answered discreetly, he said unto him, Thou art not far from the kingdom of God. And no man after that durst ask him [any question].
pairs.target:
Yesus ninga’ gulu agama ulang Yahudi inoh sikiya ponai nyawot
sina-E, Yesus mo’ sina lagi’ tudu’-e, “Mu’u mo’ siap ya’ tilima’ Topa’ militah
daang idip mu’.”
Mokua’ inoh sua’ odop-e de’ muno’ di’-e tiya’ puus sikian oni-oni-e tudu’
Yesus.

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said, while he taught in the temple, How say the scribes that Christ is the Son of David?
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus alua’ ngajal de’ awah Boli Topa’, Yesus mo’ in-E, “Oni
wat gulu-gulu agama ulang Yahudi tapod tanon nang Laja Pinyilamat so’
onak sukun Laja Daud?

pairs.source: For David himself said by the Holy Ghost, The LORD said to my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool.
pairs.target:
No’uh-e Laja Daud sibonal-e obuah nutuan Iyang
Topa’ yohmo’ in-e,
‘Topa’ sina tudu’ Tuan ku’:
gulu’ nua’ to’uh Ku’ sa’ Mu’ militah jadin Laja,
nog ku’ oda’ musuh-musuh Mu’ tunuak tudu’ Mu’u.’

pairs.source: David therefore himself calleth him Lord; and whence is he [then] his son? And the common people heard him gladly.
pairs.target:
Simo’-e Daud sobot nang Laja Pinyilamat inoh Tuan-e, jadin Iyoh
nak-e jok-e onak sukun Daud, Iyoh pasti lobih ayuh kuasa-E so’ Daud.”
Nya’a de’ bogo’ dano’ sukup sonang-e ngojit pingajal Yesus.

pairs.source: And he said unto them in his doctrine, Beware of the scribes, which love to go in long clothing, and [love] salutations in the marketplaces,
pairs.target:
Yesus tanon geh tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ma’ tau’-tau’ ya’ nuna’
gaya gulu-gulu agama de’ muno’. Iyoh suka ponu pakai jubah de’ omu, yoh
magah nang odop-e ulang timogah, duoh suka oda’ nya’a mudi odop-e de’
pasal.

pairs.source: And the chief seats in the synagogues, and the uppermost rooms at feasts:
pairs.target:
Iyoh suka gulu’ de’ topat-topat nua’ jowin daang topat simayang
agama Yahudi, duoh de’ topat-topat nya’a man ayuh.

pairs.source: Which devour widows’ houses, and for a pretence make long prayers: these shall receive greater damnation.
pairs.target:
Iyoh suka nipu
sino’ nya’a de’ mo’ janda duoh mit lomin boli-e. Iyoh suka bidoa tuui-tuui
de’ jowin nya’a ngan-e magah nang odop-e paguh . Tia’ ijo’ odop-e de’
muno’ lobih baat ukum de’ ya’ tilima’-e.”

pairs.source: And Jesus sat over against the treasury, and beheld how the people cast money into the treasury: and many that were rich cast in much.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus gulu’ ngaduap topat nya’a ngin duit tudu’ Topa’ de’ Boli
Topa’, Yesus ninga’ sua’ nya’a de’ kibalot duit-e daang kutak inoh. Bogo’
nya’a de’ kaya kibalot duit-e lobih bogo’.

pairs.source: And there came a certain poor widow, and she threw in two mites, which make a farthing.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh sino’ janda de’ botak suwa’ odi, iyoh kibalot duwoh kiping
duit tibaga de’ mulah loga-e.

pairs.source: And he called [unto him] his disciples, and saith unto them, Verily I say unto you, That this poor widow hath cast more in, than all they which have cast into the treasury:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ mogan pinuna’-pinuna’-E, Iyoh mo’ sina, “Oku’ tanon tudu’
ingan: Duit de’ kibalot sino’ janda inoh lobih ayuh loga-e so’ nya’a de’
bokon.

pairs.source: For all [they] did cast in of their abundance; but she of her want did cast in all that she had, [even] all her living.
pairs.target:
Dop-e nya’a de’ bokon ngin so’ lobih-e. Pak-e sino’ janda inoh
bial yoh botak, iyoh ngin sua’ duit-e de’ ogi’. Dop-e duam inoh ja’-e duit-e
de’ ogi’.”

pairs.source: And as he went out of the temple, one of his disciples saith unto him, Master, see what manner of stones and what buildings [are here]!
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus luah so’ awah Boli Topa’, ogi’ ni’ na’an so’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E sina tudu’ Yesus, “Gulu, suba ninga’! Batuh-batuh
Boli Topa’ inoh sangon manah! Wat inoh geh duoh sinung-sinung-e!”

pairs.source: And Jesus answering said unto him, Seest thou these great buildings? there shall not be left one stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Suba ingan ninga’ batuh-batuh duoh
sinung-sinung de’ sangon inoh. Ogi’ onu takal-e sua’ oni’ de’ ninga’
ingan itih ya’ asul. Ni’ tuang doi’ geh de’ so’ sua’ Boli Topa’ inoh de’ ya’
wat-wat-e geh, sua’-e ya’ obuah pilubuh.”

pairs.source: And as he sat upon the mount of Olives over against the temple, Peter and James and John and Andrew asked him privately,
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ odi ke’ Pungu’ Zaitun,
Yoh mo’ gulu’ de’ topat de’ ngaduap Boli Topa’. Petrus, Yakobus, Yohanes
duoh Andreas mo’ nog tudu’ Yesus, ngan-e ya’ sikian sadi’-e tudu’-E.

pairs.source: Tell us, when shall these things be? and what [shall be] the sign when all these things shall be fulfilled?
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ sikian in-e, “Tanon tudu’ ko’ih sinia’ so’ oni’ de’ muno’
ya’ jadi? Oni tanda-tanda sua’ oni’ de’ muno’ mo’ ya’ jadi, sa’ ko’ih pu’an-e?”

pairs.source: And Jesus answering them began to say, Take heed lest any [man] deceive you:
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Silalu jaga-jaga, ma’ sape ingan obuah nipu oda’
nya’a pakai pingajal de’ salah!

pairs.source: For many shall come in my name, saying, I am [Christ]; and shall deceive many.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ bogo’ nya’a de’ ya’ nog pakai adon
Oku’ yohmo’ sina nang, ‘Oku’ leh Laja Pinyilamat’, yoh mo’ nipu nya’a
de’ bogo’.

pairs.source: And when ye shall hear of wars and rumours of wars, be ye not troubled: for [such things] must needs be; but the end [shall] not [be] yet.
pairs.target:
Simo’ ingan ngojit sowo’ polang duoh gah-gah polang, ma’ ya’
tolu. Sua’ oni’ de’ muno’ ya’ jadi. Pak-e alua’ di’-e kiamat.

pairs.source: For nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom: and there shall be earthquakes in divers places, and there shall be famines and troubles: these [are] the beginnings of sorrows.
pairs.target:
Bangsa de’
ni’ ya’ nyelang bangsa de’ bokon. Negli de’ ni’ ya’ lawan negli de’ bokon.
Daki-daki-e ya’ ogi’ topat de’ tiguyang tigusuak, sua’ nya’a ya’ sibolok.   
Pak-e sua’ oni’ de’ muno’ jadin pu’un nya’a ya’ mulai jola’ so’ sua’-e de’
ya’ jadi. Samah koda’ dayung bitiia’ de’ mulai noman to’in-e monam ya’
mila’.

pairs.source: But take heed to yourselves: for they shall deliver you up to councils; and in the synagogues ye shall be beaten: and ye shall be brought before rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony against them.
pairs.target:
Pak-e ingan masim-masim ati-ati! Nya’a ya’ takap ingan duoh toban ke’
Pengadilan Agama Yahudi. Yoh ya’ pijola’ ingan de’ topat-topat simayang
agama Yahudi. Yoh toban ingan ngaduap piayuh-piayuh duoh laja-laja.
Sua’ oni’ de’ muno’ ya’ obuah ingan, dop-e ingan pinuna’-pinuna’ Oku’.
Inoh leh onu-e sa’ ingan tapod magah Gah de’ Paguh tudu’ odop-e de’
muno’.

pairs.source: And the gospel must first be published among all nations.
pairs.target:
Gah de’ Paguh inoh halus lobih dio’ nye’ magah-e tudu’ sua’
bangsa takal onu kiamat alua’ di’-e nog.

pairs.source: But when they shall lead [you], and deliver you up, take no thought beforehand what ye shall speak, neither do ye premeditate: but whatsoever shall be given you in that hour, that speak ye: for it is not ye that speak, but the Holy Ghost.
pairs.target:
Simo’ ingan obuah takap duoh
obuah toban ke’ topat nya’a bilituang, ma’ bigaduh oni in sina de’ ya’ nang
ingan. Pak-e tanon negeh oni in de’ tanon Iyang Topa’ tudu’ ingan takal
inoh. Sibonal-e idoh di’-e so’ odop ingan de’ tanon in inoh, Iyang Topa’ leh
de’ oda’ ingan tanon-e.

pairs.source: Now the brother shall betray the brother to death, and the father the son; and children shall rise up against [their] parents, and shall cause them to be put to death.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh ya’ ogi’ nya’a de’ ngin madih-e oda’
nya’a ngabos-e. Sama’ ngin onak-e de’ nya’a oda’ ngabos-e. Wat noh geh
onak-e ngin pingoma-e, oda’ nya’a ngabos-e.

pairs.source: And ye shall be hated of all [men] for my name’s sake: but he that shall endure unto the end, the same shall be saved.
pairs.target:
Bogo’ nya’a de’ ya’ bu’ui
tudu’ ingan dop-e ingan jadin pinuna’-pinuna’ Oku’. Pak-e nya’a de’ taan
naan nog piobua’ idip-e yoh leh de’ ya’ silamat.”

pairs.source: But when ye shall see the abomination of desolation, spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought not, (let him that readeth understand,) then let them that be in Judaea flee to the mountains:
pairs.target:
“Ingan ya’ ninga’ oni’ de’ sisi’ nya’a da’-a duoh oni’ de’ oda’ nya’a
kobos tulah de’ ya’ mujuag daang Boli Topa’ ngan-e ya’ ka’is-e, topat
de’ di’-e so’on yoh molot daang-e. (Nya’a de’ basa itih halus bonal-bonal
ngiloti hal itih.) Takal inoh ulang-ulang de’ lo’o de’ propinsi Yudea halus
bikoduh buu ke’ dolod-dolod.

pairs.source: And let him that is on the housetop not go down into the house, neither enter [therein], to take any thing out of his house:
pairs.target:
Ayua de’ ogi’ de’ tun bungan boli-e, ma’
tiya’ ya’ muun kalik oni’ kaang boli, lasu’ negeh bikoduh buu.

pairs.source: And let him that is in the field not turn back again for to take up his garment.
pairs.target:
Nya’a
de’ alua’ kiloja de’ umoh-e, ma’ tiya’ ya’ moli’ mit pimakai-e.

pairs.source: But woe to them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days!
pairs.target:
Takal onu
inoh, todah mun sino’-sino’ nya’a de’ balut duoh de’ alua’ sidua’ onak-e.

pairs.source: And pray ye that your flight be not in the winter.
pairs.target: Bidoa leh tudu’ Topa’, sa’ oni’ de’ muno’ di’-e nog takal musim modud.

pairs.source: For [in] those days shall be affliction, such as was not from the beginning of the creation which God created unto this time, neither shall be.
pairs.target:
Dop-e takal inoh nya’a ya’ sukup jola’-e, de’ doi’ onu nya’a obuah-e,
mulai so’ sibungas Topa’ nai dunia nog adin. Susah jola’ inoh di’-e tiya’ ya’
obuah dunia.

pairs.source: And except that the Lord had shortened those days, no flesh should be saved: but for the elect’s sake, whom he hath chosen, he hath shortened the days.
pairs.target:
Simo’ Topa’ di’-e sagot onu jola’ inoh, doi’ nya’a de’ taan
bitaan idip. Pak-e Topa’ masi’ tudu’ nya’a de’ pilih-E oda’ nuna’ odop-E,
yoh ngan-e sagot onu-e.

pairs.source: And then if any man shall say to you, Lo, here [is] Christ; or, lo, [he is] there; believe [him] not:
pairs.target:
Takal inoh, simo’ ogi’ nya’a nang, ‘Ninga’ Laja Pinyilamat ogi’ dati’,
ogi’ danih,’ ma’ ya’ bisaya’ tudu’-e.

pairs.source: For false Christs and false prophets shall rise, and shall shew signs and wonders, to seduce, if [it were] possible, even the elect.
pairs.target:
Dop-e nya’a de’ ngaku’ odop-e Laja  Pinyilamat duoh nabi-nabi pibula’ ya’ nog. Iyoh bogo’ nai oni’ de’ ilan
nya’a ngan-e ya’ nipu nya’a, nog nya’a de’ bisaya’ tudu’ Topa’ de’ mo’
pilih-E, tado’-tado’-e ya’ obuah nipu geh.

pairs.source: But take ye heed: behold, I have foretold you all things.
pairs.target:
Jadin ma’ tau’-tau’ bisaya’, sua’-e mo’ dio’ Ku’ tanon-e tudu’ ingan
takal-e alua’ di’-e jadi.”

pairs.source: But in those days, after that tribulation, the sun shall be darkened, and the moon shall not give her light,
pairs.target:
“Pak-e takal-e mo’ mokua’ onu-onu nya’a jola’ inoh, boton onu
ya’ mopung, bulan di’-e tiya’ jawa’.

pairs.source: And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.
pairs.target:
Bitang-bitang obua’ luluh duoh
kuasa-kuasa de’ ogi’ de’ longit obua’ tiguyang.

pairs.source: And then shall they see the Son of man coming in the clouds with great power and glory.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh nya’a ya’ ninga’ Onak Manusia nog de’ abun pakai kuasa-e
de’ ayuh duoh jawa’-e de’ telang.

pairs.source: And then shall he send his angels, and shall gather together his elect from the four winds, from the uttermost part of the earth to the uttermost part of heaven.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ oda’ malaikat-malaikat odi nguluk nya’a de’ mo’ pilih-e oda’
nuna’ odop-e, de’ ogi’ de’ sua’ tun dunia itih, so’ nyuang bumi nog tubon
longit.

pairs.source: Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When her branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near:
pairs.target:
Bilajal leh so’ silita tongon ara. Takal da’an-da’an-e mo’ dodot duoh
mulai ngilotad, onu mo’ ya’ loga’.

pairs.source: So ye in like manner, when ye shall see these things come to pass, know that it is nigh, [even] at the doors.
pairs.target:
Wat inoh geh mo’ ingan ninga’ mo’ ogi’ tanda-tanda de’ tanon Ku’
ti’-e, inoh loti-e mo’ sinok onu-e. Duam-e ya’ nog.

pairs.source: Verily I say unto you, that this generation shall not pass, till all these things be done.
pairs.target:
Ngojit bonal-bonal-e!
Sua’ oni’ de’ muti’ ya’ jadi takal nya’a de’ idip adin alua’ di’-e sua’-e
kobos.

pairs.source: Heaven and earth shall pass away: but my words shall not pass away.
pairs.target:
Longit duoh tana’ ya’ musuap, pak-e pingunang Ku’ totap ogi’
silama’-lama’-e.”

pairs.source: But of that day and [that] hour knoweth no man, no, not the angels which are in heaven, neither the Son, but the Father.
pairs.target:
“Pak-e sinia’ onu-e duoh sinia’ takal-e ya’ jadi doi’ nya’a de’ pu’an,
malaikat de’ siluga tuang doh geh di’-e pu’an-e. Pak-e jok-e Sama’ de’
siluga de’ pu’an. Onak-E tuang idoh geh di’-e pu’an-e.

pairs.source: Take ye heed, watch and pray: for ye know not when the time is.
pairs.target:
Ma’ tau’-tau’ duoh silalu jaga-jaga! Dop-e ingan di’ ingan pu’an sinia’
takal-e.

pairs.source: [For the Son of man is] as a man taking a far journey, who left his house, and gave authority to his servants, and to every man his work, and commanded the porter to watch.
pairs.target:
Onak Manusia ya’ nog samah koda’ nya’a de’ ya’ buu togan
boli-e. Takal-e alua’ di’-e buu, yoh mo’ bikutung kiloja tudu’ kuli-kuli-e
oda’ ngatul boli-e. Yoh sibaya tudu’ nya’a de’ tukang jaga tiban-e, ma’
sape yoh ya’ komut kiloja-e nog nya’a de’ kaku’ boli pali’. Mokua’ inoh ke
yoh mo’ odi ke’ topat de’ juua’.

pairs.source: Watch ye therefore: for ye know not when the master of the house cometh, at even, or at midnight, or at the cockcrowing, or in the morning:
pairs.target:
Inoh leh ngan nye’ silalu jaga singonu
singalom, dop-e di’ ingan pu’an sinia’ takal-e nya’a de’ kaku’ boli inoh ya’
nog. An onu ngumi, an tuluap ngalom, an suam-suam pagi, an takal boton   
onu mo’ tumu’.

pairs.source: Lest coming suddenly he find you sleeping.
pairs.target:
Sa’-e simo’ iyoh tang-tang nog, ma’ sape iyoh nog ninga’
ingan alua’ bo’os.

pairs.source: And what I say unto you I say unto all, Watch.
pairs.target:
Oni de’ tanon Ku’ tudu’ ingan, Ku’ tanon geh tudu’
sua’ nya’a: Ma’ tau’-tau’ duoh silalu jaga-jaga!”

pairs.source: After two days was [the feast of] the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put [him] to death.
pairs.target:
Duwoh onu lagi’ ulang Yahudi ya’ nyamut Onu Ayuh Paskah duoh
nyamut Onu Ayuh Kueh de’ doi’ Ragi-e. Pimipin-pimipin agama
Yahudi de’ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu agama Yahudi ya’ takap duoh ya’ ngabos
Yesus. Pak-e odop-e de’ muno’ dolia’-e oda’ nya’a pu’an oni de’ ya’ nai-e.

pairs.source: But they said, Not on the feast [day], lest there be an uproar of the people.
pairs.target:
