Yoh mo’ bipokat di’-e takap Yesus daang onu ayuh, in odop-e de’ muno’,
“Ma’ sape oni’ de’ ya’ nai oto’ oda’ nya’a de’ bogo’ nang liuak daluag-e.”

pairs.source: And being in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at meat, there came a woman having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard very precious; and she brake the box, and poured [it] on his head.
pairs.target:
Yesus alua’ lo’o de’ kupua’ Betania, iyoh mo’ odi boli Simon, nya’a
de’ dio’ so’ kano’ obuah onam kulit de’ bijakit. Takal odop-e de’ muno’
julah-e man, ogi’ ni’ na’an dayung nog toban ni’ jobul inyua’ wangi de’
maal loga-e, duoh jobul-e tuang maal geh. Yoh mo’ mugat tungua’ jobul
inoh yohmo’ duwan inyua’ inoh de’ tun bak Yesus.

pairs.source: And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made?
pairs.target:
Pak-e ogi’ kudu-kudu
na’an nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’ mo’ malah, daang-e sina tipan odop-e, “Nai oni
sa’at inyua’ de’ maal wat inoh?

pairs.source: For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and have been given to the poor. And they murmured against her.
pairs.target:
Lobih paguh nye’ jua negeh inyua’ wangi
inoh! Loga-e samah duoh gaji nya’a kiloja de’ ni’ sowa’. Duit-e tapod nye’
bikutung tudu’ nya’a de’ sotok!” Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ malah tudu’ dayung
inoh.

pairs.source: And Jesus said, Let her alone; why trouble ye her? she hath wrought a good work on me.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Tanah negeh! Doi’ nye’ jola’
malah tudu’-e. Iyoh nai oni’ de’ paling paguh-e sa’an Oku’.

pairs.source: For ye have the poor with you always, and whensoever ye will ye may do them good: but me ye have not always.
pairs.target:
Dop-e nya’a
de’ sotok, silalu ogi’ sinok ingan, sinia’ sija’-e ingan tapod tulung-e. Pak-e
Oku’ di’ ku’ silama’-lama’-e ya’ duoh ingan.

pairs.source: She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying.
pairs.target:
Dayung itih mo’ nai oni de’
tapod yoh nai-e tudu’ Oku’, iyoh mo’ dio’ ngiyua’ gonan-Ku’ takal Ku’ alua’
idip. Inoh samah geh iyoh ngiyua’ todang Ku’ takal Ku’ kobos.

pairs.source: Verily I say unto you, Wheresoever this gospel shall be preached throughout the whole world, [this] also that she hath done shall be spoken of for a memorial of her.
pairs.target:
Natong
bonal-bonal-e! Daki sija’-e nya’a magah Gah de’ Paguh tentang Oku’ de’
tun dunia itih, wat inoh geh nya’a silita oni de’ mo’ nai dayung itih. Sa’
nya’a silalu natong oni’ de’ mo’ nai-e tudu’ Oku’ adin.”

pairs.source: And Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve, went unto the chief priests, to betray him unto them.
pairs.target:
Yudas Iskariot, ni’ na’an so’ simoong duwoh pinuna’ Yesus inoh, mo’
odi tudu’ pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh ngan-e ya’ nyelah Yesus
tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And when they heard [it], they were glad, and promised to give him money. And he sought how he might conveniently betray him.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sukup doon-e ngojit oni’
de’ tanon-e, yoh mo’ bipokat ya’ ngin duit tudu’ Yudas. Yudas mo’ kalik
wat olan ngan-e ya’ nyelah Yesus tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And the first day of unleavened bread, when they killed the passover, his disciples said unto him, Where wilt thou that we go and prepare that thou mayest eat the passover?
pairs.target:
Takal onu ke’ ni’-e nya’a nyamut Onu Ayuh Kueh de’ doi’ Ragi-e,
daang onu inoh nya’a mulai simoliah domba ngan-e ya’ nyamut Onu Ayuh
Paskah. Pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ bisikian tudu’ Yesus, “Gulu, daki topat so’
oto’ ya’ man nyamut Onu Ayuh Paskah? Sa’ ko’ih sidia pinguman de’ topat
inoh.”

pairs.source: And he sendeth forth two of his disciples, and saith unto them, Go ye into the city, and there shall meet you a man bearing a pitcher of water: follow him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ pait duwoh na’an pinuna’-e yohmo’ sibaya
tudu’-e, “Odi kaang kota. Danih ingan ya’ bitapod duoh ni’ na’an dali de’
toban kobuk de’ punua’ oda’ pi’in, nye’ mo’ ponu bituna’ duoh-e.

pairs.source: And wheresoever he shall go in, say ye to the goodman of the house, The Master saith, Where is the guestchamber, where I shall eat the passover with my disciples?
pairs.target:
Takal
iyoh molot kaang boli, nye’ mo’ tanon tudu’ nya’a de’ kaku’ boli, ‘Gulu
sikian daki aluang boli topat Iyoh duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E ya’ man nyamut
Onu Ayuh Paskah?’

pairs.source: And he will shew you a large upper room furnished [and] prepared: there make ready for us.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ kaku’ boli inoh mo’ ya’ tanon tudu’ ingan,
ogi’ ni’ aluang de’ longah de’ ayuh, de’ mo’ sua’-e siap oni’ daang-e. Dano’
leh ingan sidia pinguman ngan to’ nyamut Paskah.”

pairs.source: And his disciples went forth, and came into the city, and found as he had said unto them: and they made ready the passover.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ odop-e de’ duwoh ngojit sibaya Yesus, yoh mo’ odi molot
kaang kota. Dano’ yoh bitapod duoh nya’a, bonal-bonal samah koda’ de’
tanon Yesus. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sidia pinguman ngan-e nyamut Onu
ayuh Paskah dano’.

pairs.source: And in the evening he cometh with the twelve.
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ngalom, Yesus duoh pinuna’-E de’ simoong duwoh
na’an mo’ odi ke’ boli inoh.

pairs.source: And as they sat and did eat, Jesus said, Verily I say unto you, One of you which eateth with me shall betray me.
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ julah-e man, Yesus
mo’ sina, “Natong bonal-bonal-e! Ogi’ ni’ na’an so’ ingan de’ muti’ de’ ya’
nyelah Oku’ tudu’ musuh-musuh Ku’. Odop-e ogi’ man samah-samah duoh
Oku’.”

pairs.source: And they began to be sorrowful, and to say unto him one by one, [Is] it I? and another [said, Is] it I?
pairs.target:
Takal-e ngojit sina Yesus inoh, pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ susah kila-e.
Yoh mo’ masim-masim sina nang, “Oku’ keh idoh, Gulu?”

pairs.source: And he answered and said unto them, [It is] one of the twelve, that dippeth with me in the dish.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Ogi’ odop-e dati’, so’ simoong duwoh na’an
pinuna’ Ku’ itih, de’ man ni’ pingian samah-samah duoh Oku’.

pairs.source: The Son of man indeed goeth, as it is written of him: but woe to that man by whom the Son of man is betrayed! good were it for that man if he had never been born.
pairs.target:
Onak
Manusia tok ya’ kobos, nuna’ de’ mo’ obuah nulis daang Kitab, pak-e nya’a   
de’ nyelah Iyoh ya’ tulah idip-e. Lobih paguh mo’-e yoh di’-e obuah mila’
daang dunia itih.”

pairs.source: And as they did eat, Jesus took bread, and blessed, and brake [it], and gave to them, and said, Take, eat: this is my body.
pairs.target:
Takal odop-e de’ muno’ alua’ man, Yesus mo’ mit kueh, yohmo’
bisukul tudu’ Topa’. Iyoh mo’ nyipiak kutung tudu’ pinuna’-E daang-e in-e,
“Mit nye’ mo’ man-e, itih gonan Ku’.”

pairs.source: And he took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave [it] to them: and they all drank of it.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ mit sakil de’ ogi’ pi’in anggul daang-e, yoh mo’
bisukul tudu’ Topa’. Mokua’ inoh Iyoh mo’ ngin tudu’ sua’ pinuna’-E nuak
so’ sakil inoh.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, This is my blood of the new testament, which is shed for many.
pairs.target:
Yoh mo’ sina lagi, “Itih doya’ Ku’, doya’ de’ nogap janyi
Topa’ duoh manusia, doya’ de’ soyang sa’an nya’a de’ bogo’.

pairs.source: Verily I say unto you, I will drink no more of the fruit of the vine, until that day that I drink it new in the kingdom of God.
pairs.target:
Natong
bonal-bonal-e! Tok idoh di’ Ku’ tiya’ nuak pi’in so’ bua’ anggul nog onu
Oku’ nuak so’ bua’ anggul de’ ba’uh takal Topa’ nog militah jadin Laja.”

pairs.source: And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh odop-e de’ muno’ ngilagu mudi Topa’ yohmo’ odi ke’
Pungu’ Zaitun.

pairs.source: And Jesus saith unto them, All ye shall be offended because of me this night: for it is written, I will smite the shepherd, and the sheep shall be scattered.
pairs.target:
Takal-e alua’ daang olan, Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E,
“Sua’ ingan ya’ buu togan Oku’, dop-e ogi’ de’ nulis daang Kitab, ‘Topa’ ya’
ngabos nya’a de’ tukang jaga koming domba-e, yoh mo’ koming domba-e
ya’ buu kati’ kanih.’

pairs.source: But after that I am risen, I will go before you into Galilee.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal Oku’ ya’ pali’ idip, Oku’ ya’ dio’ kajon
ingan de’ Galilea.”

pairs.source: But Peter said unto him, Although all shall be offended, yet [will] not I.
pairs.target:
Petrus mo’ in-e nyawot Yesus, “Oku’ idoh! Simo’ nya’a buu togan
Ingan, oku’ totap idoh!”

pairs.source: And Jesus saith unto him, Verily I say unto thee, That this day, [even] in this night, before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot Petrus, in-E, “Natong bonal-bonal-e! Ngalom itih
geh takal babang siuak alua’ di’-e bitadu duwoh sidoh, mu’u mo’ taluh
sidoh sukan nang odop mu’ di’ mu’ piluh Oku’.”

pairs.source: But he spake the more vehemently, If I should die with thee, I will not deny thee in any wise. Likewise also said they all.
pairs.target:
Pak-e Petrus isin-isin in-e, “Simo’ oku’ tipaksa suwa’ kobos duoh
Ingan, idoh geh di’ ku’ sukan nang odop ku’ di’ ku’ piluh Ingan.”
Pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus de’ bokon tuang inoh geh in-e.

pairs.source: And they came to a place which was named Gethsemane: and he saith to his disciples, Sit ye here, while I shall pray.
pairs.target: Yesus duoh pinuna’-pinuna’-E nog ke’ topat de’ adon Getsemani. Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, “Gulu’ dati’ dio’, Oku’ ya’ odi bidoa.”

pairs.source: And he taketh with him Peter and James and John, and began to be sore amazed, and to be very heavy;
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ngija’ Petrus, Yakobus duoh Yohanes odi duoh odop-E.
Yesus sikiya nyam kila-E tolu, otin-e ulih-ulih susah.

pairs.source: And saith unto them, My soul is exceeding sorrowful unto death: tarry ye here, and watch.
pairs.target:
Iyoh mo’ in-e tudu’
odop-e de’ taluh inoh, “Ulih-ulih nyam susah otin Ku’ sape ya’ kobos nyam
Ku’ oda’-e. Lo’o kajon dati’ ma’ ya’ bo’os!”

pairs.source: And he went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass from him.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ ponu mua’ ju’an-e so’ odop-e de’ muno’. Yoh mo’ gulu’
bikunyug nog jowin-E obuah tana’, ngan-e bidoa. Daang doa-E, Iyoh mitia’
tudu’ Topa’, mo’-e tapod sa’ susah jola’ di’-e obuah odop-E.

pairs.source: And he said, Abba, Father, all things [are] possible unto thee; take away this cup from me: nevertheless not what I will, but what thou wilt.
pairs.target:
Iyoh bidoa
in-e, “Oi Sama’ Ku’! Sua’ oni’ tapod Ingan nai-e. Oku’ mitia’ sa’ Ingan oda’
Oku’ lopas so’ susah jola’ itih. Pak-e nai negeh koda’ de’ la’an Ingan, idoh
di’-e koda’ de’ la’an Oku’.”

pairs.source: And he cometh, and findeth them sleeping, and saith unto Peter, Simon, sleepest thou? couldest not thou watch one hour?
pairs.target:
Mokua’ bidoa Yesus mo’ pali’ tudu’ pinuna’-E de’ taluh na’an inoh.
Iyoh mo’ ninga’ odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ bo’os, yohmo’ in-e tudu’ Simon
Petrus, “Simon, bo’os yeh mu’u neh? Idoh di’ mu’ taan nijon boton mu’
ni’ jam negeh?”

pairs.source: Watch ye and pray, lest ye enter into temptation. The spirit truly [is] ready, but the flesh [is] weak.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, in-e, “Silalu
jaga-jaga duoh bidoa, sa’ di’ ingan nai oni’ de’ ja’at. Otin kila ingan la’an-e
ya’ nai oni’ de’ bonal, pak-e gonan ingan de’ di’-e taan.”

pairs.source: And again he went away, and prayed, and spake the same words.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ odi lagi’ mua’ ju’an-e so’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E, yohmo’
bidoa samah koda’ in de’ ti’-e.

pairs.source: And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) neither wist they what to answer him.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ bidoa, Yesus pali’ lagi’ tudu’
pinuna’-pinuna’-E. Odop-e de’ muno’ obua’ bo’os, dop-e di’-e tiya’ taan
nijon boton-e. Takal Yesus guyang odop-e de’ muno’ yohmo’ sina tudu’-e,
odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ di’-e tiya’ pu’an oni in-e ya’ nyawot Yesus.

pairs.source: And he cometh the third time, and saith unto them, Sleep on now, and take [your] rest: it is enough, the hour is come; behold, the Son of man is betrayed into the hands of sinners.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ pali’ ke’ taluh sidoh-e. Iyoh mo’ in-e tudu’
odop-e de’ muno’, “Alua’ bo’os keh ingan? Moh tiya’! Ninga’ Onak Manusia
obuah nyelah tudu’ nya’a de’ bidosa.

pairs.source: Rise up, let us go; lo, he that betrayeth me is at hand.
pairs.target:
Mokat tiya’, ja’ to’ buu. Ninga’!
Nya’a de’ ya’ nyelah Oku’ mo’ nog!”

pairs.source: And immediately, while he yet spake, cometh Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.
pairs.target:
Takal Yesus alua’ sina, tang-tang mun Yudas nog. Yudas itih ni’ na’an
so’ simoong duwoh pinuna’ Yesus. Yudas nog samah-samah duoh nya’a
de’ bogo’ de’ toban podang duoh pakung. Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi
de’ ayuh, gulu-gulu agama duoh pimipin ulang Yahudi de’ bokon de’ pait
odop-e de’ muno’ oda’ odi sa’-e takap Yesus.

pairs.source: And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead [him] away safely.
pairs.target:
Yudas, nya’a de’ nyelah   
Yesus, mo’ dio’ tanon tudu’ nya’a de’ muno’ in-e, “Nya’a de’ sium ku’ tia’
inoh leh odop-E. Takap Iyoh nye’ mo’ ngawal toban buu.”

pairs.source: And as soon as he was come, he goeth straightway to him, and saith, Master, master; and kissed him.
pairs.target:
Takal Yudas nog yoh mo’ lasu’ odi tudu’ Yesus yoh mo’ in-e “Gulu!”
Yoh mo’ sium Yesus.

pairs.source: And they laid their hands on him, and took him.
pairs.target:
Ayua de’ muno’ lasu’ takap-E yohmo’ bikagong
duoh-E.

pairs.source: And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
pairs.target:
Ni’ na’an so’ ayua de’ nuna’ Yesus nyitak podang-e, yoh mo’
lasu’ kawiang podang-e nyopa’ kuli pimipin agama Yahudi de’ paling ayuh.
Kojit-e mo’ lasu’ sopial.

pairs.source: And Jesus answered and said unto them, Are ye come out, as against a thief, with swords and [with] staves to take me?
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ in-e tudu’ ayua de’ nog takap odop-E,
“Ba’ ingan nang Oku’ pinyamun? Ingan nog sape toban podang, toban
pakung ngan ingan takap Oku’.

pairs.source: I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and ye took me not: but the scriptures must be fulfilled.
pairs.target:
Tibilang konu Oku’ samah-samah ngajal
de’ awah Boli Topa’ de’ jowin ingan, pak-e doi’ nak ingan takap Oku’ dano’.
Pak-e adin takap leh Oku’, sa’-e bonal-bonal samah koda’ de’ obuah nulis
daang Kitab.”

pairs.source: And they all forsook him, and fled.
pairs.target: Mokua’ inoh sua’ pinuna’-E bikoduh buu togan Iyoh.

pairs.source: And there followed him a certain young man, having a linen cloth cast about [his] naked [body]; and the young men laid hold on him:
pairs.target:
Takal inoh, ogi’ ni’ na’an onak muda’ de’ jok-e bisabuak kain ngan-e
nutu gonan-e bituna’ duoh Yesus. Ayua de’ muno’ ya’ nyonguam takap-e.

pairs.source: And he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked.
pairs.target: Kain de’ gonan-e mo’ lusut yoh mo’ bikoduh buu sitagual.

pairs.source:
And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes.
  54	And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire.
  55	And the chief priests and all the council sought for witness against Jesus to put him to death; and found none.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh ayua de’ muno’ toban Yesus odi ke’ boli pimipin
agama de’ paling ayuh. Yohmo’ sua’ pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi de’
ayuh, pimipin-pimipin Yahudi de’ bokon duoh gulu-gulu agama tikuluk
dano’. Pak-e Petrus nuna’ Yesus so’ juua’ nog ke’ limang boli pimipin agama
Yahudi de’ paling ayuh. Iyoh mo’ gulu’ ngosah nya’a de’ jaga simadi-e
ngunuh sinok opui. Pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh duoh sua’
nya’a de’ ogi’ daang pengadilan agama kalik bukti ngan-e ya’ nyalah Yesus
sa’-e tapod ngukum Yesus oda’ kobos, pak-e doi’-e nak tapod salah Yesus.

pairs.source: For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together.
pairs.target:
Bogo’ nya’a de’ mokat nang sina pibula’-e ngan-e nyalah Yesus, pak-e
oni’ de’ nang odop-e de’ muno’ di’-e ni’ in.

pairs.source: And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying,
pairs.target:
Yohmo’ kudu-kudu na’an odop-e de’ muno’ mujuag nang sina pibula’
napo Yesus in-e,

pairs.source: We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.
pairs.target:
“Ko’ih mo’ ngojit Yoh itih sina, ‘Oku’ ya’ pilubuh Boli
Topa’ itih de’ obuah nai tongan manusia. Daang taluh onu Oku’ ya’ kajuag
de’ ba’uh de’ di’-e tongan manusia de’ nai.’ ”

pairs.source: But neither so did their witness agree together.
pairs.target:
Pak-e oni’ de’ nang nya’a
de’ muno’ tuang idoh geh di’-e ni’ in.

pairs.source: And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, saying, Answerest thou nothing? what [is it which] these witness against thee?
pairs.target:
Pimipin agama de’ paling ayuh mokat mujuag de’ uun odop-e de’
muno’. Iyoh mo’ sikian tudu’ Yesus in-e, “Idoh di’ mu’ ya’ nyawot sina
nya’a de’ muno’ de’ napo Mu’u neh?”

pairs.source: But he held his peace, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, and said unto him, Art thou the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?
pairs.target:
Pak-e Yesus lo’o ja’-e, di’-e nyawot-e. Pimipin agama de’ paling ayuh
sikian ni’ sidoh lagi’ in-e, “Podo Mu’u yeh Laja Pinyilamat Onak Topa’ de’
nyomah to’?”

pairs.source: And Jesus said, I am: and ye shall see the Son of man sitting on the right hand of power, and coming in the clouds of heaven.
pairs.target:
Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Bonal, Oku’ leh Odop-E. Sua’ ingan ya’ ninga’
Onak Manusia gulu’ nua’ to’uh Topa’ de’ Ayuh Kuasa-E. Yohmo’ ingan ya’
ninga’ Iyoh ya’ nog daang abun!”

pairs.source: Then the high priest rent his clothes, and saith, What need we any further witnesses?
pairs.target:
Pimipin agama de’ paling ayuh inoh mo’ notak pimakai-e, yoh in-e,
“Dusah tiya’ to’ sikian tudu’ nya’a de’ bokon neh!

pairs.source: Ye have heard the blasphemy: what think ye? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.
pairs.target:
Ingan mo’ ngojit sina-E
de’ nguyat Topa’. Oni wat oto’ ya’ duoh Iyoh itih?”
Yohmo’ sua’ nya’a de’ muno’ situju Yesus halus obuah ukum ngabos.

pairs.source: And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh kudu-kudu na’an nya’a mulai nguja’-E. Nya’a de’ muno’
mo’ kuab jowin Yesus yoh mo’ bibokut duoh-E daang-e in-e tudu’-E, “Suba
sobot, osi de’ bokut Mu’u tih?” Nya’a de’ jaga dano’ suwa’ bitapal duoh-E.

pairs.source: And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there cometh one of the maids of the high priest:
pairs.target:
Takal Petrus alua’ ogi’ gulu’ de’ limang boli pimipin agama de’ paling
ayuh, ogi’ ni’ na’an kuli-e de’ dayung nog kano’.

pairs.source: And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him, and said, And thou also wast with Jesus of Nazareth.
pairs.target:
Takal-e ninga’ Petrus
gulu’ ngunuh kibangoh gonan-e sinok opui, yoh mo’ bonal-bonal ngibotoh
jowin Petrus. Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Bah idoh di’-e ingan itih de’ silalu nuna’
Yesus ulang Nazaret inoh neh?”

pairs.source: But he denied, saying, I know not, neither understand I what thou sayest. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crew.
pairs.target:
Pak-e yoh mo’ sukan-e. Iyoh mo’ in-e, “Oku’ di’ ku’ pu’an oni de’ nang
mu’ inoh.” Mokua’ inoh Petrus mo’ buu ke’ limang de’ sinok tiban pagal
boli pimipin agama de’ paling ayuh. Takal inoh geh babang siuak bitadu.

pairs.source: And a maid saw him again, and began to say to them that stood by, This is [one] of them.
pairs.target:
Takal kuli de’ dayung inoh ninga’ Petrus lagi’, yoh mo’ in-e tudu’
nya’a de’ ogi’ dano’, “Iyoh itih ulang de’ silalu bituna’ duoh Yesus.”

pairs.source: And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely thou art [one] of them: for thou art a Galilaean, and thy speech agreeth [thereto].
pairs.target:
Pak-e
Petrus alua’ geh sukan-e. Alua’ di’-e tuui mokua’ inoh, nya’a dano’ in-e
lagi’ tudu’ Petrus, “Di’ mu’ tiya’ ponai sukan-e. Mu’u pasti so’ ayua de’
muno’ dop-e mu’u ulang Galilea.”

pairs.source: But he began to curse and to swear, [saying], I know not this man of whom ye speak.
pairs.target:
Petrus mo’ sina bisupah in-e, “Doi’ ku’ piluh osi de’ nang ingan inoh
neh! Asal ku’ pibula’, tanah sa’ Topa’ ngukum oku’!”

pairs.source: And the second time the cock crew. And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him, Before the cock crow twice, thou shalt deny me thrice. And when he thought thereon, he wept.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh babang siuak bitadu ke’ duwoh sidoh-e. Petrus mo’
gos nyam-e natong sina Yesus de’ dio’, de’ in-E, “Alua’ di’ babang siuak
bitadu duwoh sidoh, mu’u mo’ taluh sidoh sukan nang odop mu’ di’ mu’
piluh Oku’.” Mokua’ inoh kila Petrus mo’ ngilobu’ yohmo’ si’ian.

pairs.source: And straightway in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried [him] away, and delivered [him] to Pilate.
pairs.target:
Suam-suam pagi ayua pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh duoh ayua
pimipin ulang Yahudi de’ bokon baya gulu-gulu agama Yahudi,
sua’ odop-e de’ muti’ mo’ sipakat. Yoh mo’ oda’ nya’a mokos Yesus, mokua’
inoh yoh mo’ matak Yesus toban tudu’ gubelnul de’ propinsi Yudea de’
adon Pilatus.

pairs.source: And Pilate asked him, Art thou the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto him, Thou sayest [it].
pairs.target:
Gubelnul Pilatus mo’ sikian tudu’ Yesus in-e, “Podo tok Mu’u
laja ulang Yahudi?” Yesus mo’ nyawot-e, “Mu’u de’ sobot nang inoh.”

pairs.source: And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.
pairs.target:
Ayua pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh mo’ nuduh nang Yoh bogo’ nai
oni’ de’ ja’at.

pairs.source: And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answerest thou nothing? behold how many things they witness against thee.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Pilatus sikian lagi’ tudu’ Yesus, “Ngojit, bogo’
oni’ de’ nuduh odop-e de’ muno’ tudu’ Mu’u. Oni nai di’ mu’ nyawot-e?”

pairs.source: But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled.
pairs.target: Pak-e ni’ doi’ geh sina-e de’ nyawot Yesus, yoh ngan Pilatus ilan-e.

pairs.source: Now at [that] feast he released unto them one prisoner, whomsoever they desired.
pairs.target:
Mo’ adat-e bilang Onu Ayuh Paskah, Pilatus pilopas ni’ na’an nya’a
de’ obuah jel nuna’ de’ pilih nya’a de’ bogo’.

pairs.source: And there was [one] named Barabbas, [which lay] bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ ni’ na’an nya’a de’ adon
Barabas. Iyoh obuah jel samah-samah duoh ayua nya’a de’ lawan kerajaan
Romawi, dop-e ayua de’ muno’ mo’ ngabos nya’a takal nya’a nai liuak
daluag-e.

pairs.source: And the multitude crying aloud began to desire [him to do] as he had ever done unto them.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ bogo’ de’ tikuluk dano’ mo’ mitia’ tudu’ Pilatus oda’
pilopas ni’ na’an so’ jel, nuna’ adat-e.

pairs.source: But Pilate answered them, saying, Will ye that I release unto you the King of the Jews?
pairs.target:
Pilatus mo’ sikian tudu’ nya’a de’
bogo’, “Podo ingan mitia’ oda’ oku’ pilopas laja ulang Yahudi inoh sa’an
ingan?”

pairs.source: For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him for envy.
pairs.target:
Dop-e Pilatus mo’ pu’an pimipin-pimipin agama ulang Yahudi
de’ ayuh de’ muno’ nyelah Yesus tudu’ odop-e, dop-e yoh sinia’ tudu’ Yesus.

pairs.source: But the chief priests moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.
pairs.target:
Pak-e ayua pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh mo’ kibangoh kila nya’a
de’ bogo’ oda’ pilopas Barabas sa’an odop-e.

pairs.source: And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will ye then that I shall do [unto him] whom ye call the King of the Jews?
pairs.target:
Pilatus mo’ sikian lagi’ ke’
duwoh sidoh-e tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Mo’-e wat inoh, oni wat ku’ ya’
duoh nya’a de’ nang ingan laja ulang Yahudi inoh?”

pairs.source: And they cried out again, Crucify him.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ sina daang-e nang bogan-e, “Masak Iyoh tun
salip!”

pairs.source: Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil hath he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.
pairs.target:
Pilatus sikian lagi’ tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Pak-e oni wat oni’ de’
ja’at de’ nai-E?” Odop-e de’ muno’ makin dolas nang bogan-e, “Masak Iyoh
tun salip!”

pairs.source: And [so] Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged [him], to be crucified.
pairs.target:
Pilatus mo’ pilopas Barabas, sa’ di’ nya’a tiya’ nang liuak daluag-e.
Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ oda’ sidadu-sidadu-e pijola’ Yesus duoh masak tun
salip.

pairs.source: And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band.
pairs.target:
Sidadu-sidadu Roma mo’ toban Yesus kaang boli topat gubelnul
militah. Yoh mo’ mogan sua’ sidadu de’ bokon oda’ tikuluk dano’.

pairs.source: And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his [head],
pairs.target:
Ayua
sidadu de’ muno’ pasang jubah walna ungu tudu’ Yesus, duoh na’ mahkota
de’ nai-e pakai da’an koyuh de’ biloja’ de’ bak Yesus.

pairs.source: And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’
mo’ pula’-pula’ mudi Yesus, daang-e in-e, “Idip laja ulang Yahudi!”

pairs.source: And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing [their] knees worshipped him.
pairs.target:
Ayua
sidadu de’ muno’ makung bak Yesus pakai sikuud, ogi’ geh odop-e de’
nguja’ Yesus. Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ gulu’ bikunyug de’ sulung jowin Yesus
pula’-pula’ pimodo tudu’-E.

pairs.source: And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.
pairs.target:
Takal-e mokua’ adoh-adoh wat-e duoh Yesus,
odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ buka’ jubah-E de’ walna ungu inoh, yoh mo’ pali’
pasang bojuh odop Yesus. Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ toban buu ngan-e ya’
nyalip-E.

pairs.source: And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.
pairs.target:
Takal-e de’ lopot olan, sidadu de’ muno’ mo’ paksa ni’ na’an nya’a
de’ adon Simon oda’ golong salip Yesus. Simon itih tuang-e nog so’ kupua’
ya’ molot ke’ kota. Iyoh nya’a so’ Kirene, sama’ Aleksander duoh Rufus.

pairs.source: And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.
pairs.target:
Sidadu-sidadu de’ muno’ mo’ toban Yesus ke’ topat de’ adon Golgota,
loti-e, “Topat Tikuluak.”

pairs.source: And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received [it] not.
pairs.target:
De’ dano’, ogi’ nya’a de’ ya’ ngin pi’in anggul
de’ sapul-e duoh potok koyuh de’ sobot-e nang Mur, de’ tapod oda’ nya’a
di’-e sikiya noman gonan-e monam, pak-e Yesus dolia’-e nuak-e.

pairs.source: And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take.
pairs.target:
Mokua’
inoh, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ mabak pasak de’ tongan po’on Yesus de’ tun
koyuh salip. Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ bikutung pimakai Yesus pakai ngundi,
sa’-e pu’an osi de’ so’on bojuh-E duoh osi de’ so’on jubah-E.

pairs.source: And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.
pairs.target:
Nya’a nyalip
Yesus inoh takal pukul pili’i pagi.

pairs.source: And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
pairs.target:
De’ tun salip-E ogi’ tulis de’ nopia
nya’a, ngan-e sobot luban nya’a nyalip Yesus de’ in-e, “Laja ulang Yahudi.”

pairs.source: And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ duwoh na’an pinyamun de’ obuah nyalip bibaya-baya duoh Yesus.
Ni’ na’an nua’ to’uh-E, ni’ na’an nua’ boit-E.

pairs.source: And the scripture was fulfilled, which saith, And he was numbered with the transgressors.
pairs.target:
Oni’ de’ obuah Yesus inoh,
mo’ bonal-bonal jadi samah duoh de’ mo’ obuah nulis daang Kitab, de’
in-e, “Nya’a mo’ nang Iyoh samah duoh ulang ja’at.”

pairs.source: And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, thou that destroyest the temple, and buildest [it] in three days,
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ ngilusu’ topat inoh mo’ adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus, daang-e
kuting bak-e, yohmo’ in-e, “No mey-e, patut Mu’u nang odop Mu’ ya’
pilubuh Boli Topa’, duoh ya’ pali’ kajuag ba’uh daang taluh onu

pairs.source: Save thyself, and come down from the cross.
pairs.target:
Suba
muun so’ tun salip, nyilamat odop Mu’!”

pairs.source: Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save.
pairs.target:
Watnoh geh pimipin-pimipin agama Yahudi de’ ayuh duoh gulu-gulu
agama Yahudi suwa’ geh adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus. Odop-e de’ muno’
mo’ sina tipan odop-e, “Nya’a de’ bokon Iyoh nyilamat-e, pak-e Iyoh di’-e
taan nyilamat Odop-E sadi’-e!

pairs.source: Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him.
pairs.target:
Simo’ Iyoh tok-tok Laja Pinyilamat ulang
Israel, tanah sa’-e muun so’ salip, sa’ oto’ ninga’-E, oto’ mo’ bisaya’.” Wat
inoh geh pinyamun de’ suwa’ obuah nyalip samah-samah duoh Yesus,
suwa’ geh adoh-adoh in-e duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.
pairs.target:
Takal uun onu pukul simoong duwoh, sua’ pulou mo’ mopung, nog
pukul taluh ngumi.

pairs.source: And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, Eloi, Eloi, lama sabachthani? which is, being interpreted, My God, my God, why hast thou forsaken me?
pairs.target:
Takal pukul taluh ngumi inoh Yesus mo’ nang
bogan-e, in-E, “Eloi, Eloi, lema sabakhtani?” De’ loti-e, “Topa’ Ku’, Topa’
Ku’, oni nai Ingan togan Oku’?”

pairs.source: And some of them that stood by, when they heard [it], said, Behold, he calleth Elias.
pairs.target:
Takal nya’a dano’ ngojit Yesus nang bogan-e, odop-e de’ muno’ mo’
in-e, “Ngojit, Iyoh mogan adon nabi Elia!”

pairs.source: And one ran and filled a spunge full of vinegar, and put [it] on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let alone; let us see whether Elias will come to take him down.
pairs.target:
Ogi’ ni’ na’an so’ odop-e de’
muno’ odi mit lumut de’ nyolap pi’in, yoh mo’ suad daang pi’in anggul de’
masuam, yoh mo’ na’ de’ tubon tisuk koyuh ngan-e nyog de’ boba’ Yesus,
daang-e sina, “Ja’ to’ kajon-e! To’ ninga’-e podo nabi Elia nog pimuun Iyoh
so’ tun salip.”

pairs.source: And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost.
pairs.target: Yesus mo’ nang bogan-e lagi’, mokua’ inoh asong-e mo’ doi’.

pairs.source: And the veil of the temple was rent in twain from the top to the bottom.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh geh tabial daang Boli Topa’ mo’ totak jadin duwoh amal
so’ somu nog dou’.

pairs.source: And when the centurion, which stood over against him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the ghost, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.
pairs.target:
Takal piayuh sidadu Roma de’ mujuag de’ jowin salip Yesus mo’
ninga’ pingobos-E de’ wat inoh, yoh mo’ in-e, “Tok bonal Nya’a itih Onak
Topa’.”

pairs.source: There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;
pairs.target:
Ogi’ geh bala dayung de’ suwa’ ninga’ nya’a nyalip Yesus so’ juua’.
Odop-e de’ muno’ Maria Magdalena, Salome, baya Maria sino’ Yakobus de’
muda’ duoh Yoses.

pairs.source: (Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.
pairs.target:
Dayung-dayung de’ muti’ leh de’ bituna’ duoh Yesus
takal-e de’ Galilea ngan-e tulung-E. Bogo’ geh dayung-dayung de’ bokon
de’ ogi’ dano’ de’ suwa’ nog ke’ Yerusalem samah-samah duoh Yesus.

pairs.source: And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,
Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counseller, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus.
pairs.target:
Takal onu mo’ ya’ ngalom Yusuf so’ kupua’ Arimatea nog.Yusuf
itih suwa’ jadin ayua so’ Pengadilan Agama Yahudi de’ pimodo nya’a da’-e.
Yoh itih tuang suwa’ geh kajon Topa’ ya’ nog militah jadin Laja. Onu inoh,  nya’a mo’ siap-siap ya’ nyamut Onu Sabat. Inoh leh ngan-e yoh maksa-e
ja’-e odop-e odi ngaduap Pilatus, yohmo’ mitia’ todang Yesus ngan-e ya’
ngubul-e.

pairs.source: And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling [unto him] the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.
pairs.target:
Pilatus mo’ ilan-e takal-e ngojit Yesus mo’ kobos. Iyoh mo’ mogan
piayuh sidadu ngan-e ya’ sikian podo Yesus mo’ bonal-bonal kobos.

pairs.source: And when he knew [it] of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.
pairs.target:
Takal-e mo’ ngojit so’ piayuh sidadu inoh nang Yesus mo’ kobos, yoh
mo’ oda’ Yusuf mit todang Yesus.

pairs.source: And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a sepulchre which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the sepulchre.
pairs.target:
Yusuf mo’ milih kain mopu’ ngan-e
ya’ molut todang. Mokua’ inoh yoh mo’ pimuun todang Yesus, yoh mo’
molut-e, yoh mo’ na’ daang kubul gua. Mokua’ inoh yoh pigulai batuh
de’ ayuh ngan-e kuab kubul gua inoh.

pairs.source: And Mary Magdalene and Mary [the mother] of Joses beheld where he was laid.
pairs.target:
Takal inoh ogi’ Maria Magdalena
duoh Maria sino’ Yoses suwa’ ninga’ topat nya’a piguling todang Yesus.

pairs.source: And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the [mother] of James, and Salome, had bought sweet spices, that they might come and anoint him.
pairs.target:
Takal mokua’ onu Sabat, Maria Magdalena, Salome, duoh Maria
sino’ Yakobus odi milih inyua’ wangi de’ ya’ toban-e ke’ kubul gua,
ngan-e ya’ nginyua’ todang Yesus.

pairs.source: And very early in the morning the first [day] of the week, they came unto the sepulchre at the rising of the sun.
pairs.target:
Daang pu’un minggu inoh, suam-suam
pagi takal boton onu mo’ tumu’, odop-e de’ muno’ odi ke’ kubul gua.

pairs.source: And they said among themselves, Who shall roll us away the stone from the door of the sepulchre?
pairs.target:
De’ lopot olan yoh mo’ bisikian si odop-e, “Osi de’ taan gulai batuh de’
kuab kubul gua sa’an oto’?”

pairs.source: And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away: for it was very great.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal-e mo’ sinok kubul gua inoh, yoh
mo’ ninga’ batuh de’ sukup ayuh inoh mo’ tigulai.

pairs.source: And entering into the sepulchre, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were affrighted.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ muno’ mo’
molot kaang kubul gua inoh, yoh mo’ gogoh takal-e ninga’ ogi’ ni’ na’an
onak muda’ de’ pakai bojuh mopu’ gulu’ nua’ to’uh odop-e de’ muno’.

pairs.source: And he saith unto them, Be not affrighted: Ye seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified: he is risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.
pairs.target:
Onak muda’ inoh mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, “Ma’ tolu! Oku’
pu’an nang ingan kalik Yesus ulang Nazaret de’ mo’ obuah nyalib inoh. Iyoh
mo’ doi’ dati’! Iyoh mo’ pali’ idip! Ninga’ itih topat nya’a posan todang-E.

pairs.source: But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goeth before you into Galilee: there shall ye see him, as he said unto you.
pairs.target:
Buu pali’ adin, tanon gah itih tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’-E baya Petrus. In
nye’ tanon tudu’-e, ‘Yesus dio’ odi kajon ingan de’ Galilea. Danih leh ingan
ya’ bitapod duoh Iyoh koda’ de’ mo’ dio’-e tanon-E.’ ”

pairs.source: And they went out quickly, and fled from the sepulchre; for they trembled and were amazed: neither said they any thing to any [man]; for they were afraid.
pairs.target:
Daang kila de’ gogoh duoh sukup tolu-e odop-e de’ muno’ mo’ bikoduh
luah togan kubul gua inoh. Odop-e de’ muno’ di’-e tanon oni-oni-e tudu’
sua’ nya’a de’ tapod-e de’ olan dop-e yoh tolu.

pairs.source: Now when [Jesus] was risen early the first [day] of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ Yesus mo’ pali’ idip, suam-suam pagi de’ pu’un minggu inoh,
Iyoh mo’ bitanga odop-E, sibungas-e tudu’ Maria Magdalena. Iyoh itih leh   
de’ ogi’ onu Yesus kasig ju’ muat munua so’ gonan-e.

pairs.source: [And] she went and told them that had been with him, as they mourned and wept.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Maria
Magdalena mo’ odi tanon tudu’ pinuna’-pinuna’ Yesus de’ alua’ si’ian,
dop-e yoh alua’ susah otin-e.

pairs.source: And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not.
pairs.target:
Pak-e takal odop-e de’ muno’ ngojit so’
Maria Magdalena nang yoh kilin Yesus pali’ mokat idip, odop-e de’ muno’
di’-e bisaya’.

pairs.source: After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ bitanga Odop-E tudu’ duwoh na’an pinuna’-E,
pak-e okon mun jowin-E, takal odop-e de’ duwoh daang pimonu-e so’
Yerusalem odi ke’ kupua’ de’ bokon.

pairs.source: And they went and told [it] unto the residue: neither believed they them.
pairs.target:
Odop-e de’ duwoh mo’ pali’ tudu’
dingan-dingan-e yohmo’ tanon sua’ oni’ de’ kilin-e. Pak-e ayua dingan-e
tuang idoh geh di’-e bisaya’.

pairs.source: Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at meat, and upbraided them with their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they believed not them which had seen him after he was risen.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus sadi’-e lasu’ bitapod duoh simoong ni’ na’an
pinuna’-pinuna’-E takal odop-e de’ muno’ alua’ julah-e man. Yesus mo’
ngalah odop-e de’ muno’, dop-e sua’ odop-e de’ muno’ li’iang bak-e duoh
dolia’-e bisaya’ tudu’ nya’a de’ tanon nang odop-e mo’ ninga’ Yesus takal-e
pali’ idip.

pairs.source: And he said unto them, Go ye into all the world, and preach the gospel to every creature.
pairs.target:
Mokua’ inoh Yesus mo’ sina tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’, in-E, “Kodak
leh nog tubon longit nye’ mo’ magah Gah de’ Paguh so’ Topa’ tudu’ sua’
nya’a.

pairs.source: He that believeth and is baptized shall be saved; but he that believeth not shall be damned.
pairs.target:
Nya’a de’ bisaya’ duoh obuah baptis iyoh ya’ silamat. Pak-e nya’a
de’ di’-e bisaya’ ya’ obuah ngukum.

pairs.source: And these signs shall follow them that believe; In my name shall they cast out devils; they shall speak with new tongues;
pairs.target:
Sua’ nya’a de’ bisaya’ tudu’ Oku’,
Oku’ ngin kuasa tudu’-e oda’ nai oni’ de’ ilan nya’a. Ingan tapod kasig
muat munua daang adon Oku’, ponai nang sina de’ alua’ doi’ sidoh ingan
bilajal-e.

pairs.source: They shall take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them; they shall lay hands on the sick, and they shall recover.
pairs.target:
Mo’ nyam ingan kagian dipoh duoh nuak lasun doi’ geh oni-oni
wat ingan oda’-e. Mo’ nyam ingan toma’ nya’a de’ monam, iyoh tapod
mokua’.”

pairs.source: So then after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God.
pairs.target:
Takal-e mokua’ sina duoh odop-e de’ muno’, Topa’ Yesus mo’ tipa'ad
ke’ siluga. Danih Iyoh mo’ militah samah-samah duoh Topa’ Sama’ de’
siluga.

pairs.source: And they went forth, and preached every where, the Lord working with [them], and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.
pairs.target:
Pinuna’-pinuna’-E mo’ odi ni’ pulou-pulou tanon Gah de’ Paguh so’
Topa’. Odop Topa’ tuang suwa’ geh kiloja samah-samah duoh odop-e de’
muno’. Iyoh ngin-e geh kuasa tudu’ odop-e de’ muno’ sa’-e nai bogo’ oni’
de’ ilan nya’a, sa’-e jadin tanda nang gah de’ tanon-e inoh bonal-bonal so’
Topa’.

pairs.source: One
pairs.target: Ni'

pairs.source: Two
pairs.target: Duoh

pairs.source: Three
pairs.target: Taluh

pairs.source: Four
pairs.target: Pat

pairs.source: Five
pairs.target: Limoh

pairs.source: Six
pairs.target: Nuom

pairs.source: Seven
pairs.target: Ju'
